d GET /tags. Call requests via connectors.proxy("accelo", "/companies"), connectors.proxy("accelo", "/activities"), etc. The SDK handles access token injection and refresh automatically. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"acme-apikey":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Acme API Key",visibility:"staff",vertical:["social-media"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-acme-apikey.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Connect to Acme API Key to access its API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Acme API Key connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("acme-apikey", "/endpoint"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"acme-oauth2":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Acme OAuth",visibility:"staff",vertical:["social-media"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-acme-oauth2.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Acme OAuth to obtain and refresh access tokens via OAuth2.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Acme OAuth connector via the proxy pattern to interact with the API. Common endpoints include: GET /token (fetch access token), POST /token/refresh (refresh token), GET /userinfo (fetch user info), POST /revoke (revoke token). Remember that requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection—use connectors.proxy("acme-oauth2", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"active-campaign":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"ActiveCampaign",visibility:"beta",vertical:["communication"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-active-campaign.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Access and manage your marketing automation, contacts, campaigns, and more.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the ActiveCampaign connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated requests. Common endpoints: GET /api/3/contacts (list contacts), GET /api/3/lists (retrieve all lists), POST /api/3/contacts (create a new contact), and GET /api/3/dealGroups (list deal pipelines). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("active-campaign", "/api/3/contacts"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"activecampaign",package_version:"1.2.5"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"acuity-scheduling":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Acuity Scheduling",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-acuity-scheduling.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage appointments, availability, and webhooks via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use this connector, the agent can call common endpoints like GET /appointment-types, GET /availability/dates, GET /availability/times, POST /appointments, and GET /webhooks via proxies. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refreshing. Use connectors.proxy("acuity-scheduling", "/path") to invoke operations (e.g., connectors.proxy("acuity-scheduling", "/availability/dates")). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},addepar:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Addepar",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-addepar.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access portfolio, users, entities, and more via secure OAuth2.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Addepar connector via the proxy pattern to interact with key endpoints such as: GET /v1/portfolio/query, GET /v1/users/me, GET /v1/entity_types, POST /v1/imports (beta), and GET /v1/users/:id. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection and refresh. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("addepar", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},adobe:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Adobe",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-adobe.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Search, retrieve, license, and manage user assets across Adobe services.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Adobe connector via the proxy pattern. Common endpoints include: GET /Rest/Media/1/Search/Files (search assets), GET /Rest/Media/1/Files (retrieve asset metadata), POST /Rest/Libraries/1/Content/License (license asset), GET /Rest/Libraries/1/Member/LicenseHistory (list past purchases). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 auth injection; call connectors.proxy("adobe","/path") to invoke. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"adobe-commerce":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Adobe Commerce",visibility:"beta",vertical:["commerce"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-adobe-commerce.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Access its REST/GraphQL storefront and admin APIs.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Adobe Commerce connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /rest/V1/products to list products, POST /rest/V1/orders to create an order, GET /rest/V1/customers/{id} to retrieve customer details, GET /graphql to issue GraphQL queries, and GET /rest/V1/adminuisdk/massaction/{requestId} for Admin UI SDK status. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("adobe-commerce", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"adobe-workfront":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Adobe Workfront",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-adobe-workfront.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage projects, tasks, documents, and planning via its REST API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Adobe Workfront connector via the proxy pattern by invoking connectors.proxy("adobe-workfront", "/your/path"). Common useful endpoints include: GET /v15.0/project/search (search for projects), GET /v15.0/task/search (retrieve tasks), GET /v15.0/document/download (download a document), POST /v15.0/project (create a new project), and GET /v15.0/plan/search (planning API search). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 authentication injection. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},adyen:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Adyen",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-adyen.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Initiate, manage payments, payouts, and perform platform operations.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the connector via the proxy pattern to interact with Adyen’s API. Common useful endpoints include: POST /authorise (initiate a payment), POST /capture (capture a payment), POST /refund (refund a payment), POST /payout (submit a payout), GET /stores (list stores via Management API). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth (or API key/basic auth) injection — use connectors.proxy("adyen", "/your/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},affinity:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Affinity",visibility:"beta",vertical:["crm"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-affinity.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Interact with CRM data—lists, opportunities, fields via REST API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Affinity connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints include: GET /v2/opportunities to list opportunities, GET /v2/lists/{listId}/fields to retrieve field metadata, PATCH /v2/lists/{listId}/list-entries/{listEntryId}/fields to update custom field values. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("affinity", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},agentmail:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"AgentMail",visibility:"ga",vertical:["communication"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-agentmail.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Programmatically create and manage AI agent email inboxes.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the AgentMail connector via the proxy pattern to manage inboxes, messages, threads, API keys, and webhooks. Common endpoints include: POST /v0/inboxes (create inbox), GET /v0/inboxes/{inboxId}/messages (list messages), POST /v0/inboxes/{inboxId}/messages (send message), GET /v0/api-keys (list API keys), and POST /v0/webhooks (register webhook). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("agentmail", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},agentphone:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"AgentPhone",visibility:"ga",vertical:["communication"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-agentphone.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Provision phone numbers and make voice or SMS calls with AgentPhone",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the AgentPhone connector via the proxy pattern to manage agents, phone numbers, conversations, calls, and webhooks. Common endpoints include: POST /v1/agents (create agent), POST /v1/numbers (provision phone number with optional agentId), POST /v1/calls/outbound (make outbound call), GET /v1/numbers/:id/messages (list SMS messages), POST /v1/webhooks (register webhook for inbound events), GET /v1/conversations (list conversations), and GET /v1/calls/:id/transcript (get call transcript). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("agentphone", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"https://agentphone.to",apiDocsUrl:"https://docs.agentphone.to"}}},"aimfox-oauth":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Aimfox",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-aimfox-oauth.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Aimfox (OAuth) to access its API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Aimfox (OAuth) connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection and refresh. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("aimfox-oauth", "/endpoint"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},aircall:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Aircall",visibility:"beta",vertical:["ticketing"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-aircall.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access users, calls, webhooks, and integrations via OAuth2.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Aircall connector via the proxy pattern to make authenticated API calls. Common useful endpoints include: GET /v1/users, GET /v1/calls, POST /v1/users/:id/calls, GET /v1/integrations/me, POST /v1/oauth/token. All requests are proxied through the SDK, so authentication is injected automatically. Callbacks to OAuth and token exchange are handled for you—just perform connectors.proxy("aircall", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},airtable:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!0,metadata:{displayName:"Airtable",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-airtable.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"List, retrieve, create, update, and delete records via REST API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Airtable connector via the proxy pattern by calling common endpoints such as GET /v0/{baseId}/{tableName}, GET /v0/{baseId}/{tableName}/{recordId}, POST /v0/{baseId}/{tableName}, PATCH /v0/{baseId}/{tableName}/{recordId}, DELETE /v0/{baseId}/{tableName}/{recordId}. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection. Use connectors.proxy("airtable", "/v0/{baseId}/{tableName}") and adjust path as needed. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},algolia:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Algolia",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-algolia.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Connect to Algolia to search, configure, and manage indices via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Algolia connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: POST /1/indexes/{indexName}/query to search records, GET /1/indexes/{indexName} to get index settings, POST /1/indexes/{indexName}/batch to add or update multiple records. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("algolia", "/1/indexes/{indexName}/query"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"algoliasearch",package_version:"5.44.0"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},amazon:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Amazon",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools","commerce"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-amazon.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage Seller/Vendor operations via the Amazon Selling Partner API",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Selling Partner API (SP-API) via the proxy pattern with automatic OAuth2 authentication. Commonly useful endpoints include: GET /orders/v0/orders, GET /catalog/2022-04-01/items/{asin}, POST /auth/o2/token (to refresh access), GET /reports/2021-06-30/reports, and POST /feeds/2021-06-30/feeds. Requests should be made via connectors.proxy("amazon", "/path"); the SDK handles automatic injection of auth tokens. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"amazon-selling-partner":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Amazon Selling Partner",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools","commerce"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-amazon-selling-partner.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access seller data: orders, inventory, listings, and reports",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use this connector, an AI agent can invoke connectors.proxy("amazon-selling-partner", "/orders/v0/orders") to list orders (GET /orders/v0/orders), connectors.proxy("amazon-selling-partner", "/catalog/v0/items") to search catalog items (GET /catalog/v0/items), connectors.proxy("amazon-selling-partner", "/feeds/2021-06-30/feeds") to create feeds (POST /feeds/2021-06-30/feeds), connectors.proxy("amazon-selling-partner", "/reports/2021-06-30/reports") to request reports (POST /reports/2021-06-30/reports), or connectors.proxy("amazon-selling-partner", "/tokens/2021-03-01/restrictedDataToken") to get restricted data token (POST /tokens/2021-03-01/restrictedDataToken). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 authentication injected. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("amazon-selling-partner", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"amazon-selling-partner-beta":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Amazon Selling Partner (Beta)",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["developer-tools","commerce"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-amazon-selling-partner-beta.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Programmatically access seller data and operations.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Amazon Selling Partner (Beta) connector via the proxy pattern with OAuth2 managed automatically. Common endpoints include: GET /orders/v0/orders (retrieve orders), GET /catalog/v0/items/{itemId} (fetch catalog item), POST /feeds/2021-06-30/feeds (submit a feed), GET /reports/2021-06-30/reports/{reportId} (get report), GET /tokens/2021-03-01/restrictedDataToken (get restricted data token). Note that requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection — just use connectors.proxy("amazon-selling-partner-beta", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},amplitude:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Amplitude",visibility:"alpha",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-amplitude.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Ingest events and interact with analytics and export APIs.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Amplitude connector via the proxy pattern, e.g. connectors.proxy("amplitude", "/httpapi") for sending events (HTTP API V2 POST /httpapi); use connectors.proxy("amplitude", "/export") to retrieve historical event data (GET /export); use connectors.proxy("amplitude", "/taxonomy") to manage event taxonomy (Taxonomy API operations such as DELETE and RESTORE). Requests are auto-authenticated via headers in the SDK proxy. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("amplitude", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},anrok:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Anrok",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-anrok.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Connect to Anrok to calculate and manage sales tax, VAT, and compliance.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Anrok connector via the proxy pattern to perform authenticated API requests. Common endpoints include: GET /products (list Anrok products), POST /tax/calculate (calculate tax), GET /nexus (check nexus exposure), POST /registrations (register in a jurisdiction), and GET /mappings (fetch product ID mappings). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("anrok", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},apaleo:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Apaleo",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-apaleo.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Apaleo to access and manage hospitality data via REST APIs.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Apaleo connector via the proxy pattern to interact with common endpoints such as GET /booking/v1/bookings, POST /booking/v1/bookings, GET /inventory/v1/unit-groups, PATCH /booking/v1/bookings/{id}, and GET /finance/v1/folios/{folioId}/payments. Requests are proxied through the SDK, which automatically injects and refreshes OAuth2 tokens. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("apaleo", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},apify:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Apify",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-apify.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Run actors, manage datasets, and interact with key-value stores.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Apify connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints include: POST /v2/acts/{actorId}/runs to run an actor, GET /v2/actor-runs/{runId} to check run status, GET /v2/datasets/{datasetId}/items to retrieve dataset items, POST /v2/key-value-stores/{storeId}/records to store data. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("apify", "/v2/acts/{actorId}/runs"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"apify-client",package_version:"2.16.0"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},apollo:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!0,metadata:{displayName:"Apollo (API Key)",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-apollo.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Search, enrich, and manage sales contacts and companies via REST API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Apollo connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /api/v1/people/search to find people, POST /api/v1/people/enrich to enrich person data, GET /api/v1/organizations/search to search organizations, POST /api/v1/organizations/enrich to enrich organization data. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("apollo", "/api/v1/people/search"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"apollo-oauth":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Apollo",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-apollo-oauth.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access Apollo’s REST API and act on behalf of users via OAuth 2.0.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Apollo (OAuth) connector via the proxy pattern to interact with Apollo’s REST API. Common endpoints include:\n• GET /v1/people/search — find people matching filters\n• POST /v1/enrichment/people — enrich person data\n• POST /v1/contacts — create a new contact\n• POST /v1/sequences/add_contacts — add contacts to a sequence\nAll requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Use connectors.proxy("apollo-oauth", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"appstle-subscriptions":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Appstle Subscriptions",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-appstle-subscriptions.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage Shopify subscription plans and orders via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Appstle Subscriptions connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /subscriptions (list subscription plans), POST /subscriptions (create a subscription), GET /orders (list subscription orders), PATCH /subscriptions/{id} (update a subscription). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("appstle-subscriptions", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},asana:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Asana",visibility:"alpha",vertical:["ticketing"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-asana.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Asana to manage tasks, projects, workspaces, and team workflows.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Asana connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /api/1.0/workspaces to list workspaces, GET /api/1.0/projects to list projects, GET /api/1.0/tasks?project={project_gid} to list tasks in a project, GET /api/1.0/users/me to get the current user. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("asana", "/api/1.0/tasks?project={project_gid}"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"asana",package_version:"3.0.12"}]}},links:{webUrl:"https://app.asana.com",apiDocsUrl:"https://developers.asana.com/docs"},integrationKeys:{nango:"asana"}}},ashby:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Ashby",visibility:"alpha",vertical:["ats"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-ashby.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Access ATS data such as jobs, candidates, and applications.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use connectors.proxy("ashby", "/path") to interact with Ashby endpoints. Common endpoints include: POST /application.list, GET /job.info, GET /jobPosting.list, POST /candidate.create, and GET /jobBoard.list. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"atlas-so":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Atlas.so",visibility:"beta",vertical:["ticketing"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-atlas-so.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Access conversations, sessions, and support data via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Atlas.so connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /conversations (list conversations), POST /conversations/{conversation_id}/sidebars/create (create sidebar), GET /sessions (list session recordings), GET /sessions/{session_id}/video (get session recording video). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("atlas-so", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},atlassian:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Atlassian",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-atlassian.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access Jira, Confluence, and other cloud APIs via OAuth2.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Atlassian connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. First call GET /oauth/token/accessible-resources to list accessible cloud instances and obtain a cloudId. Then use cloud-scoped paths: GET /ex/jira/{cloudId}/rest/api/3/issue/{issueIdOrKey} to fetch a Jira issue, GET /ex/jira/{cloudId}/rest/api/3/project to list Jira projects, GET /ex/confluence/{cloudId}/wiki/api/v2/pages to list Confluence pages. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection. Example: connectors.proxy("atlassian", "/ex/jira/{cloudId}/rest/api/3/issue/TEST-1"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"jira.js",package_version:"latest"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"atlassian-admin":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Atlassian Cloud Admin",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-atlassian-admin.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Centrally manage your organization via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Atlassian Cloud Admin connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /admin/v1/orgs to list organizations, GET /admin/v1/orgs/{orgId}/users to retrieve users, POST /admin/v1/orgs/{orgId}/events to fetch audit events. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("atlassian-admin", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"atlassian-government-cloud":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Atlassian Government Cloud",visibility:"beta",vertical:["ticketing"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-atlassian-government-cloud.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access Jira, Confluence, and JSM in a FedRAMP-moderate environment.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use this connector, the agent should call common endpoints like GET /rest/api/3/issue, POST /rest/api/3/issue, GET /wiki/rest/api/space, and GET /rest/api/3/project via the proxy. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("atlassian-government-cloud", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},attention:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Attention",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-attention.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage and query your organization’s sales call conversations.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Attention connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API access. Common endpoints: GET /v2/conversations to list conversations, GET /v2/conversations/{id} via get_call_details to retrieve details, POST /mcp/ask_attention to ask an AI-powered question, plus create_snippet, list_teams, get_scorecards under /mcp. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("attention", "/v2/conversations") or connectors.proxy("attention", "/mcp/ask_attention"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},attio:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Attio",visibility:"beta",vertical:["crm"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-attio.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Attio to access and manipulate CRM workspace data via REST API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use the Attio connector via the proxy pattern, perform requests such as GET /v2/objects/companies/records, POST /v2/objects/people/records/query, PATCH /v2/objects/deals/{id}, DELETE /v2/objects/companies/{id}, and POST /v2/objects/companies/records/query. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection—use connectors.proxy("attio", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},auth0:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Auth0",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-auth0.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage authentication, users, clients, sessions, and metadata.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Auth0 connector via the proxy pattern to interact with key OAuth2 and Management API endpoints. Common useful endpoints include:\n• GET /api/v2/users — list or search users. ([auth0.com](https://auth0.com/docs/manage-users/user-accounts/manage-users-using-the-management-api?utm_source=openai))\n• PATCH /api/v2/users/{id} — update a user’s profile or metadata. ([auth0.com](https://auth0.com/docs/manage-users/user-accounts/manage-users-using-the-management-api?utm_source=openai))\n• GET /api/v2/clients — retrieve client application configurations. ([auth0.com](https://auth0.com/docs/authenticate/single-sign-on/api-endpoints-for-single-sign-on?utm_source=openai))\n• PATCH /api/v2/clients/{id} — update client settings or metadata. ([auth0.com](https://auth0.com/docs/manage-users/user-accounts/metadata/manage-metadata-api?utm_source=openai))\n• GET /api/v2/sessions — inspect user sessions (Enterprise plan only). ([auth0.com](https://auth0.com/docs/manage-users/sessions/manage-user-sessions-with-auth0-management-api?utm_source=openai))\nAll requests are proxied through the SDK, which injects OAuth tokens and handles refreshing automatically — use connectors.proxy("auth0", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},autodesk:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Autodesk",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-autodesk.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access Platform Services APIs with OAuth2 authentication.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Autodesk connector via the proxy pattern for common operations such as: GET /authentication/v1/authenticate (POST), POST /data/v1/projects/:projectId/hubs/:hubId/projects (create project), GET /data/v1/projects/:projectId/items/:itemId/versions (list versions), POST /buckets/:bucketKey/objects/:objectName (upload object), GET /derivatives/v2/manifest/:urn (get model manifest); all requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection—use connectors.proxy("autodesk", "/path"); Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},autotask:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"AutoTask",visibility:"beta",vertical:["ticketing"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-autotask.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage PSA entities like tickets, companies, products, and more.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the AutoTask connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /Companies/{id} to retrieve a company, POST /Tickets to create a ticket, GET /ZoneInformation to auto-detect your zone, PATCH /Tickets/{id} to update a ticket. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("autotask", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"@apigrate/autotask-restapi",package_version:"latest"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},avoma:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Avoma",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-avoma.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Access meeting, transcription, notes, recordings, and insights via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Avoma connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /meetings to list meetings, GET /meetings/{meetingId}/insights to fetch insights, GET /transcriptions to list transcriptions, GET /recordings to retrieve recordings, GET /notes to access notes. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection in headers. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("avoma", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},aws:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"AWS",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools","commerce"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-aws.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Programmatically manage support cases and access services via proxy.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use this AWS connector via the proxy pattern. Common useful API endpoints include:\n- POST / (CreateCase)\n- GET / (DescribeCases)\n- POST / (AddCommunicationToCase)\n- GET / (DescribeServices)\n- POST / (RefreshTrustedAdvisorCheck)\nNote that requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh. Use connectors.proxy("aws", "/path") to invoke AWS Support API operations. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},axiom:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Axiom",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-axiom.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Connect to Axiom to ingest, query, and manage datasets via REST API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Axiom connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: POST /v1/ingest/{dataset} to ingest data, GET /v2/annotations to list annotations, GET /v2/datasets to list datasets. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("axiom", "/v1/ingest/{dataset}") or connectors.proxy("axiom", "/v2/annotations"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},bamboohr:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"BambooHR",visibility:"beta",vertical:["hris"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-bamboohr.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Securely access and manage BambooHR employee data via OAuth2.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the BambooHR connector via the proxy pattern to access common endpoints: GET /v1/employees/directory, GET /v1/employees/{employeeId}, POST /v1/employees/{employeeId}/notes, GET /v1/reports/custom, and GET /v1/meta/users. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("bamboohr", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},basecamp:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Basecamp",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-basecamp.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access projects, to-dos, messages, schedules, and documents",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use the Basecamp connector via the proxy pattern, prefer Basecamp 3\'s flat routes: GET /projects.json (list projects), GET /projects/{project_id}.json (get project — includes the dock listing each tool with its id and enabled flag), GET /todolists/{todolist_id}/todos.json (list to-dos in a list), POST /todolists/{todolist_id}/todos.json (create a to-do), GET /messages/{message_id}.json, POST /buckets/{project_id}/message_boards/{board_id}/messages.json (create a message; legacy bucket-scoped form is still required for some collection-create endpoints), GET /people.json (list people in account), GET /my/profile.json (current user). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 auth injection — call connectors.proxy("basecamp", "/path"). The proxy resolves the per-account API base URL (https://3.basecampapi.com/{accountId}) from connection_settings.accountId. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body. Basecamp requires a User-Agent header identifying your app and a contact email/URL on every request, otherwise it returns 400 Bad Request.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},battlenet:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Battle.net",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-battlenet.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Battle.net to access game and profile data using OAuth2.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use this connector via the proxy pattern to call common Battle.net API endpoints. Common useful endpoints include: GET /oauth/userinfo for user info, GET /profile/user/wow for WoW profile, GET /data/wow/item/{itemId} for game data, GET /profile/user/wow/collections/pets for pet collections, and GET /profile/user/wow/collections/mounts for mounts. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection. Use connectors.proxy("battlenet", "/path") for calls. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},beehiiv:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Beehiiv",visibility:"beta",vertical:["communication"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-beehiiv.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage newsletter publications, subscribers, and data via their API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Beehiiv connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /publications/{publicationId} to fetch a publication, GET /subscribers to list subscribers, POST /subscribers to create a subscriber. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key (Bearer token) injection into headers. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("beehiiv", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},bettercontact:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"BetterContact",visibility:"beta",vertical:["crm"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-bettercontact.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Enrich contacts with verified emails and mobile phone numbers.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the BetterContact connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: POST /api/v2/async for creating enrichment jobs; GET /api/v2/async/{id} to fetch results; optionally use webhook parameter in POST /api/v2/async for async callbacks. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection via headers. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("bettercontact", "/api/v2/async"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},bigcommerce:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"BigCommerce",visibility:"beta",vertical:["commerce"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-bigcommerce.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage store data, orders, catalogs, and payments.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the BigCommerce connector via the proxy pattern for common operations such as GET /stores/{store_hash}/v3/catalog/products, GET /stores/{store_hash}/v3/orders, POST /stores/{store_hash}/v3/orders, POST /stores/{store_hash}/v3/payments/access_tokens, and POST /stores/{store_hash}/v3/payments. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 authentication, so you don’t need to handle tokens directly. Use connectors.proxy("bigcommerce", "/path") for all calls. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},bigquery:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Google BigQuery",visibility:"ga",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-bigquery.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Google BigQuery to execute SQL queries on large datasets.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'## SDK setup\nUse the @google-cloud/bigquery SDK through the proxy for authenticated BigQuery requests.\nThe code_snippet in packages.javascript shows the full setup: stub GoogleAuth so the SDK never hits the GCP metadata server,\npoint the BigQuery client at proxyUrl with customEndpoint: true, and use an interceptor that rewrites paths and injects proxy headers via connectors.getProxyHeaders("bigquery").\nWith this setup you can use the native SDK normally: bigquery.getDatasets(), bigquery.query({ query }), bigquery.dataset(id).getTables(), bigquery.dataset(id).table(id).getMetadata(), etc.\nThe proxy resolves the real project ID and OAuth credentials automatically — never specify them in client code.\n\n## CRITICAL: Cost discipline (BigQuery is billed per byte scanned)\nBigQuery charges by the byte. A single SELECT * over a fact table can cost tens of dollars,\nand a dashboard that re-runs a handful of warehouse queries every few seconds — without a cache —\ncan burn five- or six-figure daily bills. Follow these rules on every query:\n- Project exact columns. NEVER `SELECT *` on wide or fact tables. `LIMIT` does not reduce\n  the bytes the warehouse scans for the columns you selected.\n- Scope by the partition / cluster column. Add `WHERE event_date >= ...` (or whichever\n  column the table is partitioned/clustered on) so BigQuery prunes data and bills you for a\n  slice, not the whole table. Without this filter, fact-table reads scan the entire table.\n- Prefer pre-aggregated tables (`*_daily`, `*_summary`) over raw event tables.\n- Aggregate on the warehouse — push `GROUP BY`, `SUM`, `COUNT` into SQL. Do NOT stream raw\n  rows to the client and aggregate in JavaScript.\n- Use `INFORMATION_SCHEMA` for schema discovery (essentially free) rather than running\n  `SELECT *` against the table itself just to see what columns exist.\n- Use `dryRun: true` (`bigquery.createQueryJob({ query, dryRun: true })`) when you are\n  unsure how much a query will scan — the response includes the estimated bytes.\n- For incremental refreshes, persist a high-water-mark cursor (e.g. `last_seen_at`) and\n  filter with `WHERE updated_at > @last_seen` so refresh queries only scan the delta.\n  BigQuery named parameters use the `@name` marker — not `:name` or `$1`.\n\n## CRITICAL: Cache read-only BigQuery responses in your app\nDo NOT call BigQuery on every page load or every poll cycle. Wrap every **read-only**\nBigQuery-backed route in a database-backed response cache (e.g. a Postgres `api_cache`\ntable). "Read-only" means: dashboard / report / explorer routes that run `SELECT`\nqueries (including CTEs that only read), `INFORMATION_SCHEMA` lookups, and other\nidempotent reads.\n\nDo NOT cache:\n- DML routes (`INSERT`, `UPDATE`, `MERGE`, `DELETE`, `TRUNCATE`).\n- DDL routes (`CREATE`, `ALTER`, `DROP`).\n- Job-control / load-job / streaming-insert routes.\n- Anything where the second identical request must still produce a side effect.\n\nCaching a mutating route would silently drop the second execution and return a stale\n"success" — a correctness bug, not a cost win. If a single route can run either\nread-only or mutating SQL (e.g. a generic "execute SQL" endpoint), gate caching on\nthe actual statement: bypass the cache when the parsed statement is anything other\nthan a read.\n\nThe cache key MUST include every dimension that scopes the response, not just the\nroute shape:\n- The connection / connector_config ID (so two different BigQuery connections in the\n  same app never share a cached payload).\n- The org / tenant ID, when the app is multi-tenant.\n- The signed-in user ID, when the route returns user-scoped data or uses user-pass-through\n  credentials.\n- The endpoint path.\n- The normalized query / body params.\n\nA key shaped like `${connectionId}:${orgId}:${userId}:${endpoint}:${normalizedParams}`\nis a safe default. A key that is only `${endpoint}:${normalizedParams}` will silently\nserve org A\'s cached BigQuery result to org B on the next request.\n\nMatch the cache TTL to the lowest auto-refresh interval exposed to the user; a 5-minute\nfloor is recommended. A cache TTL longer than the user-visible refresh interval is also\nfine — it just means "Refresh" temporarily returns the cached payload, which is usually\nwhat you want for cost control.\n\n## Auto-refresh / polling floor\nNever **re-run** a dashboard / report / explorer query against BigQuery more often than\nonce every 5 minutes. This floor applies to query-driven refreshes — auto-refresh\nintervals, `refetchInterval`, `setInterval` loops that re-issue the underlying\n`bigquery.query(...)` / `jobs.insert` call, etc.\n\nIt does NOT apply to short-lived status polling for an in-flight query job. While a\njob is `PENDING` or `RUNNING`, you should poll `jobs.get(jobId)` (or equivalent)\nevery 1–3 seconds (with reasonable backoff) until the job reaches `DONE` — that is\nchecking the status of a single submitted job, not re-running the dashboard query,\nso it does not re-scan bytes and the user is actively waiting on the result.\n\nReal-time dashboards belong on a streaming pipeline + materialized view, not on a\npolling loop against raw BigQuery tables.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"@google-cloud/bigquery",package_version:"7.9.4",code_snippet:'import { BigQuery } from "@google-cloud/bigquery";\nimport { GoogleAuth, OAuth2Client } from "google-auth-library";\n\n// Stub auth so the SDK never uses ADC or the GCP metadata server.\nconst oauth = new OAuth2Client();\noauth.setCredentials({ access_token: "proxy-handled", expiry_date: Date.now() + 86400000 * 365 * 10 });\nconst auth = new GoogleAuth({ authClient: oauth });\nauth.getProjectId = async () => "_";\nauth.getClient = async () => oauth;\n\nconst bigquery = new BigQuery({ projectId: "_", customEndpoint: true, apiEndpoint: proxyUrl, authClient: auth });\n\n// Rewrite paths and inject proxy identity headers on every request.\nbigquery.interceptors.push({\n  async request(reqOpts) {\n    let path = reqOpts.uri.replace(/.*\\/projects\\/[^/]+/, "");\n    if (!path.startsWith("/")) path = "/" + path;\n    reqOpts.uri = proxyUrl + path;\n    const proxyHeaders = await connectors.getProxyHeaders("bigquery");\n    reqOpts.headers = { ...(reqOpts.headers ?? {}), ...proxyHeaders };\n    return reqOpts;\n  },\n});'},{package_name:"google-auth-library",package_version:"9.15.1"}]}},links:{webUrl:"https://cloud.google.com/bigquery",apiDocsUrl:"https://cloud.google.com/bigquery/docs/reference/rest"}}},bird:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Bird",visibility:"beta",vertical:["communication"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-bird.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Send messages, manage contacts, channels, numbers, and accounts",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Bird connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /channels for channel listing, POST /channels/{channelId}/messages to send a message, GET /contacts to list contacts, POST /numbers to purchase a number, and GET /accounts to view account details. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection into headers. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("bird", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"messagebird",package_version:"latest"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},bitbucket:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Bitbucket",visibility:"alpha",vertical:["developer-tools"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-bitbucket.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage repositories, pull requests, projects, and workspaces.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Bitbucket connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /2.0/repositories/{workspace}/{repo_slug} to get a repository, GET /2.0/repositories/{workspace}/{repo_slug}/pullrequests to list pull requests, GET /2.0/workspaces to list workspaces, GET /2.0/user/repositories to list authenticated user repositories. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("bitbucket", "/2.0/repositories/{workspace}/{repo_slug}"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"bitbucket",package_version:"2.2.4"}]}},links:{webUrl:"https://bitbucket.org",apiDocsUrl:"https://developer.atlassian.com/cloud/bitbucket/rest/intro/"},integrationKeys:{nango:"bitbucket"}}},"bitbucket-source-control":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Bitbucket",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-bitbucket-source-control.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access and manage repositories, pull requests, commits, and code search.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:"",packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},bitly:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Bitly",visibility:"beta",vertical:["social-media"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-bitly.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Bitly to shorten links and manage Bitlinks via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use the Bitly connector via the proxy pattern, perform actions such as:\n• POST /v4/shorten – shorten a URL (create a Bitlink)([dev.bitly.com](https://dev.bitly.com/api-reference?utm_source=openai))\n• POST /v4/bitlinks – create a Bitlink with metadata like title, tags([dev.bitly.com](https://dev.bitly.com/api-reference?utm_source=openai))\n• GET /v4/bitlinks/{bitlink} – retrieve Bitlink details([dev.bitly.com](https://dev.bitly.com/api-reference?utm_source=openai))\n• PATCH /v4/bitlinks/{bitlink} – update Bitlink (e.g., long_url, title, tags)([dev.bitly.com](https://dev.bitly.com/api-reference?utm_source=openai))\n• DELETE /v4/bitlinks/{bitlink} – delete a Bitlink([dev.bitly.com](https://dev.bitly.com/api-reference?utm_source=openai))\nRemember that requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection, so you just call connectors.proxy("bitly", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},blackbaud:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Blackbaud",visibility:"beta",vertical:["crm"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-blackbaud.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access SKY API endpoints with OAuth2 authentication.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'The AI agent can interact with Blackbaud’s SKY API via the proxy pattern. Common useful endpoints include:\n- GET /constituents\n- GET /gifts\n- GET /campaigns\n- POST /token (for OAuth2 token retrieval)\nRequests are made through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 auth injection. Use connectors.proxy("blackbaud", "/path") for all calls. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},blandai:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"BlandAI",visibility:"beta",vertical:["ticketing"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-blandai.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Send AI-driven voice calls, manage SIP routing, and interact with agents.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the BlandAI connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: POST /v1/calls to initiate outbound calls, GET /v1/sip to fetch SIP configuration, POST /v1/sip/update to update SIP routing, POST /v1/sip/detach to remove SIP setup. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("blandai", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"bland-ai",package_version:"latest"},{package_name:"@blandsdk/client",package_version:"latest"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},boldsign:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"BoldSign",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-boldsign.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Send, manage, and track e-signature workflows via OAuth2.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use this connector to access BoldSign APIs via OAuth2; common endpoints include GET /v1/document/list, POST /v1/template/send, GET /v1/brand/list, POST /v1/brand/create, and GET /v1/contacts/list. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth token injection. Use connectors.proxy("boldsign", "/path") to invoke endpoints. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},box:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Box",visibility:"alpha",vertical:["wiki","file-storage"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-box.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage files, folders, users, and webhooks via OAuth2 API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Box connector via the proxy pattern to call common endpoints: GET /folders/:id to retrieve folder metadata, POST /files/content to upload files, GET /files/:id/content to download file content, and GET /webhooks to list webhook configurations. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection — call connectors.proxy("box", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""},integrationKeys:{nango:"box"}}},braintree:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Braintree",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-braintree.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage transactions, customers, payment methods, refunds, and more.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Braintree connector via the proxy pattern to access common endpoints such as: POST /graphql (GraphQL endpoint), mutation chargePaymentMethod, mutation refundTransaction, query searchTransactions, mutation createCustomer. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 authentication injection. You should invoke calls like connectors.proxy("braintree", "/graphql") with the appropriate GraphQL payload. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"braintree-sandbox":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Braintree (Sandbox)",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-braintree-sandbox.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Process payments, vault methods, and manage transactions via GraphQL.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Braintree (Sandbox) connector via the proxy pattern. Commonly used API endpoints include: POST /graphql (chargePaymentMethod), POST /graphql (vaultPaymentMethod), POST /graphql (createClientToken), POST /graphql (authorizePaymentMethod), POST /graphql (captureTransaction). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection. Use connectors.proxy("braintree-sandbox", "/graphql") to make calls. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},brave:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Brave",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-brave.svg",authType:"API_KEY",accessType:"global",description:"Perform web, image, video, and LLM-powered search queries.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Brave connector via the proxy pattern to access endpoints such as GET /res/v1/web/search, GET /res/v1/images/search, POST /res/v1/chat/completions, and GET /res/v1/summarizer/summary. Calls are proxied through the SDK, which automatically injects authentication headers. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("brave", "/res/v1/web/search") or similar paths for other endpoints. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},braze:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Braze",visibility:"beta",vertical:["communication"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-braze.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage messaging, users, campaigns, and data via its REST API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Braze connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /campaigns/list to list campaigns, POST /messages/send to send messages to users, GET /email/hard_bounces to retrieve bounced emails. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("braze", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"braze-api",package_version:"2.13.2"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},brevo:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Brevo",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-brevo.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Connect to Brevo to manage contacts, send emails, campaigns, and more.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Brevo connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /account to retrieve account info, POST /contacts to create a contact, POST /smtp/email (or sendTransacEmail via SDK) to send transactional emails, GET /campaigns to list campaigns, DELETE /contacts/{contactId} to delete a contact. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("brevo", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"@getbrevo/brevo",package_version:"latest"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},brex:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!0,metadata:{displayName:"Brex",visibility:"beta",vertical:["banking"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-brex.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access Brex APIs for payments, vendors, transactions, and referrals.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Brex (OAuth) connector via the proxy pattern by calling connectors.proxy("brex", "/path"). The most common endpoints include: GET /v1/vendors, POST /v1/vendors, GET /v1/transfers/{id}, GET /v1/linked_accounts, and GET /v1/referrals (onboarding). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection and refresh. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"brex-staging":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Brex (Staging)",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-brex-staging.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Refer customers and manage staging environment operations.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Brex (Staging OAuth) connector via the proxy pattern to call common endpoints like GET /v1/referrals, POST /v1/referrals, GET /v1/referrals/{id}, POST /v1/referrals/{id}/document_upload. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 auth injection. Use connectors.proxy("brex-staging", "/v1/referrals") or similar paths. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},browserbase:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Browserbase",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-browserbase.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Connect to Browserbase to run cloud-managed headless browsers.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Browserbase connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: POST /v1/fetch to retrieve a single page, POST /v1/search to run a web search. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("browserbase", "/v1/fetch") or connectors.proxy("browserbase", "/v1/search"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{},exampleUsage:{javascript:[{name:"fetch-url",snippet:'import { ReplitConnectors } from "@replit/connectors-sdk";\n\nconst connectors = new ReplitConnectors();\nconst response = await connectors.proxy("browserbase", "/v1/fetch", {\n  method: "POST",\n  headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },\n  body: JSON.stringify({ url: "https://example.com" }),\n});\n\nif (!response.ok) {\n  const text = await response.text().catch(() => "");\n  throw new Error(`HTTP ${response.status}: ${text}`);\n}\n\nconst body = await response.json();\n\nexport const result = { ok: response.ok, keys: Object.keys(body ?? {}) };'},{name:"search-web",snippet:'import { ReplitConnectors } from "@replit/connectors-sdk";\n\nconst connectors = new ReplitConnectors();\nconst response = await connectors.proxy("browserbase", "/v1/search", {\n  method: "POST",\n  headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },\n  body: JSON.stringify({ query: "browserbase headless browser api" }),\n});\n\nif (!response.ok) {\n  const text = await response.text().catch(() => "");\n  throw new Error(`HTTP ${response.status}: ${text}`);\n}\n\nconst body = await response.json();\n\nexport const result = { ok: response.ok, keys: Object.keys(body ?? {}) };'}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"builder-io-private":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Builder.io",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-builder-io-private.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Read or write content using Builder.io’s private API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Builder.io connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /content to fetch content, POST /content to create content, and POST /graphql (Admin API) to manage content structure, assets, or models. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("builder-io-private", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"@builder.io/sdk",package_version:"6.1.2"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"builder-io-public":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Builder.io (Public)",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-builder-io-public.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Fetch content via Content, HTML, GraphQL, and other public APIs.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Builder.io (public) connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints include: GET /api/v3/content/{model}?apiKey=… (Content API), GET /api/v3/html/{model}?apiKey=… (HTML API), POST /api/v3/graphql/{apiKey}?query=… (GraphQL API), and POST /api/v1/write/{model} (Write API requires private key). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("builder-io-public", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},buildium:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Buildium",visibility:"beta",vertical:["accounting","crm"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-buildium.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Access and manage property, tenant, association, and accounting data.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Buildium connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints include: GET /v1/rentals to list rental properties, GET /v1/associations/{associationId} to retrieve an association, POST /v1/associations/owners/{ownerId}/notes to add owner notes. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API-key injection in headers. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("buildium", "/v1/...path..."). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},builtwith:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"BuiltWith",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools","crm","commerce"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-builtwith.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Fetch technology profiles, trends, recommendations, and trust data",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the BuiltWith connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints include:\n- GET /v22/api.json (Domain API) to lookup technologies for one or more domains\n- GET /tag1/api.json (Tags API) to get related domains or attributes by IP or site tags\n- GET /rec1/api.json (Recommendations API) to receive technology recommendations for a site\n- GET /trends/v6/api.json (Trends API) to access technology trend data\n- GET /redirect1/api.json (Redirects API) to retrieve live or historical redirects of a website\nRequests are automatically authenticated via headers and proxied through the SDK. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("builtwith", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},bullhorn:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Bullhorn",visibility:"beta",vertical:["hris"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-bullhorn.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access and manage staffing data via Bullhorn’s REST API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Bullhorn connector via the proxy pattern. Common useful endpoints include: (1) POST /login?access_token=…&version=* to establish a REST session and get BhRestToken and restUrl, (2) GET /entity/{EntityType}/{id}?fields=… to retrieve a specific record, (3) PUT /entity/{EntityType}/{id} to update an entity, (4) GET /query/{EntityType}?where=…&fields=… to query entities, and (5) GET /massUpdate/{EntityType} or POST /massUpdate/{EntityType} for bulk updates. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token/current BhRestToken injection — use connectors.proxy("bullhorn", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"cal-com-oauth":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Cal.com",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-cal-com-oauth.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Cal.com to manage scheduling, calendars, and bookings via OAuth.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use the Cal.com OAuth connector via the proxy pattern: common endpoints include GET /v2/calendars/{calendar}/connect, POST /v2/auth/oauth2/token (for token exchange and refresh), and POST /v2/oauth-clients/{clientId}/users to create managed users. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("cal-com-oauth", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"@calcom/sdk",package_version:"1.0.1"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""},integrationKeys:{nango:"cal-com-oauth"}}},calendly:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Calendly",visibility:"alpha",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-calendly.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Calendly to manage scheduled events, event types, and invitees.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Calendly connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /v2/users/me to get the current user, GET /v2/event_types?user={user_uri} to list event types, GET /v2/scheduled_events to list scheduled events, GET /v2/scheduled_events/{uuid}/invitees to list invitees for an event. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("calendly", "/v2/scheduled_events"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"calendly-js",package_version:"1.0.1"}]}},links:{webUrl:"https://calendly.com",apiDocsUrl:"https://developer.calendly.com/api-docs"},integrationKeys:{nango:"calendly"}}},callrail:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Callrail",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-callrail.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Programmatically access and manage call, company, and message data.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the CallRail connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /v3/a.json (list accounts), GET /v3/a/{account_id}/calls.json (list calls), GET /v3/a/{account_id}/companies.json (list companies), POST /v3/a/{account_id}/form_submissions.json (create form submission). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("callrail", "/v3/a/{account_id}/calls.json"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},candis:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Candis",visibility:"beta",vertical:["accounting"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-candis.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage invoice exports, core data, invoices, and reimbursement items.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Candis connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API access. Common endpoints include: GET /v1/organizations/{organizationId}/imports/{processId} to fetch import status, POST /v1/organizations/{organizationId}/imports/{core-data-type} to create core data entries, GET /v1/organizations/{organizationId}/exports/invoices to retrieve approved invoices. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("candis", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},canny:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Canny",visibility:"beta",vertical:["ticketing"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-canny.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage feedback boards, posts, comments, votes, and changelogs",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Canny connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /boards to list boards, GET /posts/{postID} to fetch a post, POST /posts to create a new post, POST /comments to add a comment, GET /votes to list votes. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("canny", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"canny-sdk",package_version:"1.0.5"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},canva:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Canva",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-canva.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Integrate design workflows, assets, and collaborations via REST APIs.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Canva Connect API via the proxy pattern. Common endpoints include: POST /rest/v1/oauth/token (generate or refresh OAuth2 token), GET /rest/v1/oauth/introspect (check token validity), DELETE /rest/v1/oauth/revoke (revoke OAuth2 token), GET /designs (list or fetch designs), POST /designs (create new design). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection—use connectors.proxy("canva", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"canvas-lms":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Canvas LMS",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-canvas-lms.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage courses, assignments, users, enrollments, files, and more.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Canvas LMS connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints include GET /api/v1/courses to list courses, GET /api/v1/courses/{course_id}/assignments to get assignments, POST /api/v1/courses/{course_id}/assignments to create an assignment, and GET /api/v1/users/{user_id}/enrollments to list enrollments. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("canvas-lms", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""},integrationKeys:{nango:"canvas-lms"}}},certn:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Certn",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-certn.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Connect to Certn to manage background check cases and related resources.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Certn connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /api/v1/cases/ to list cases, POST /api/v1/cases/ to order a new case, GET /api/v1/packages/ to retrieve available screening packages, GET /api/v1/superteams/ to list superteams, GET /api/v1/teams/ to list teams. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("certn", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},chattermill:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Chattermill",visibility:"beta",vertical:["ticketing"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-chattermill.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Send, enrich, and retrieve feedback data programmatically.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Chattermill connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: POST /v1/data/import to send feedback, GET /v1/feedback to retrieve feedback entries, GET /v1/projects to list projects. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection into headers. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("chattermill", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},checkhq:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Check",visibility:"beta",vertical:["accounting"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-checkhq.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage payroll—companies, employees, workplaces, payrolls, and paystubs.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the CheckHQ connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints include:\n- GET /companies to list companies,\n- POST /employees to create employees,\n- POST /payrolls to create payrolls,\n- POST /payrolls/{id}/approve to approve payrolls,\n- GET /employees/{employee_id}/paystubs/{payroll_id} for paystub retrieval (PDF or JSON). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("checkhq", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"checkr-partner":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Checkr Partner",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-checkr-partner.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage partner OAuth flows, accounts, candidates, invitations, and reports.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Checkr Partner connector via the proxy pattern with common endpoints, for example: POST /v1/accounts (Create Partner Account), POST /oauth/tokens (Retrieve access_token), POST /v1/invitations (Create invitation), GET /v1/candidates (List candidates), POST /oauth/deauthorize (Deauthorize token). Remember that requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection; use connectors.proxy("checkr-partner", "/path") to invoke endpoints. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"checkr-partner-staging":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Checkr Partner (Staging)",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-checkr-partner-staging.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Run background check workflows in a test environment.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'When acting as an AI agent using the Checkr Partner (Staging) connector, you can invoke common endpoints like: GET /candidates, POST /candidates, POST /invitations, GET /reports/{id}, and POST /oauth/tokens to retrieve access tokens. These requests are proxied via the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection, so you don’t need to manage authentication manually. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("checkr-partner-staging", "/path") to initiate calls (e.g., connectors.proxy("checkr-partner-staging", "/candidates")). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},chorus:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Chorus",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-chorus.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Retrieve call recordings, transcripts, and metadata for analysis.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Chorus connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /api/v1/calls?startDate={start}&endDate={end} to list calls, GET /api/v1/calls/{callId}/transcript to fetch a call’s transcript, and optionally GET /api/v1/calls/{callId} for call metadata. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("chorus", "/api/v1/...path..."). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"circle-so":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Circle.so",visibility:"beta",vertical:["communication"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-circle-so.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Connect to Circle.so to automate community, member, and event integrations.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Circle.so connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /headless/posts to list posts, POST /headless/comments to create a comment, GET /admin/communities to retrieve communities, and GET /data_api/events to fetch event data. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API-Key auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("circle-so", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"clari-copilot":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Clari Copilot",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-clari-copilot.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Access call recordings, transcripts, users, topics, accounts, and deals",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Clari Copilot connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /calls to fetch call history, GET /call-details?id=CALL_ID for transcripts and analytics, GET /users to list workspace users, GET /v2/topics for topic metadata, POST /create-call to upload external call recordings. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key/password auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("clari-copilot", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},clerk:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Clerk",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-clerk.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage users, sessions, clients, emails, SMS, and invitations server-side.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Clerk connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints include: GET /v1/users (list users), POST /v1/users (create user), GET /v1/sessions (list sessions), POST /v1/sessions (revoke or manage sessions), and GET /v1/invitations (list invitations). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("clerk", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"@clerk/backend",package_version:"latest"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},clickup:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"ClickUp",visibility:"alpha",vertical:["ticketing"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-clickup.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to ClickUp to manage tasks, folders, lists, spaces, and workspaces.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the ClickUp connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /api/v2/team to list workspaces, GET /api/v2/team/{team_id}/space to list spaces, GET /api/v2/space/{space_id}/list to list lists, GET /api/v2/list/{list_id}/task to list tasks in a list, POST /api/v2/list/{list_id}/task to create a task. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("clickup", "/api/v2/team"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"clickup.js",package_version:"2.2.0"}]}},links:{webUrl:"https://app.clickup.com",apiDocsUrl:"https://developer.clickup.com/reference"},integrationKeys:{nango:"clickup"}}},close:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Close",visibility:"beta",vertical:["crm"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-close.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage leads, activities, contacts, and opportunities via REST API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Close connector via the proxy pattern to interact with Close CRM’s REST endpoints. Commonly used endpoints include: GET /v1/lead/, POST /v1/lead/, GET /v1/contact/, POST /v1/activity/note/. Invoke requests through connectors.proxy("close", "/v1/lead/") (or similar paths) — authentication (OAuth2 token) is injected and refreshed automatically. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("close", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},cloudbeds:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Cloudbeds",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-cloudbeds.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage hotel, guest, room, reservation, and payment data via their PMS API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Cloudbeds connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API access. Common endpoints: GET /getHotels to retrieve properties, POST /access_token to obtain or refresh tokens, GET /getReservations to list reservations (or analogous endpoints for guests and rooms). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("cloudbeds", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},cloudflare:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Cloudflare",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-cloudflare.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage zones, DNS records, R2, and rate limiting via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Cloudflare connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API calls. Common endpoints: GET /zones to list zones; POST /zones/{zone_id}/dns_records to create a DNS record; GET /zones/{zone_id}/dns_records to list DNS records; GET /accounts/{account_id}/r2/buckets to list R2 buckets. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("cloudflare", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"cloudflare",package_version:"5.2.0"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},coda:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!0,metadata:{displayName:"Coda",visibility:"beta",vertical:["wiki"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-coda.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Programmatically interact with docs, tables, and rows via its REST API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Coda connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /docs to list documents, GET /docs/{docId}/tables to list tables in a document, and POST /docs/{docId}/rows to insert rows (also PUT /docs/{docId}/rows/{rowId} for updates). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("coda", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},codeclimate:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Code Climate",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-codeclimate.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Access metrics on users, orgs, repos, builds, and test reports via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Code Climate connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /user to fetch the authenticated user, GET /orgs to list organizations, GET /orgs/{org_id}/repos to list repositories, GET /repos/{repo_id}/ref_points to retrieve commit snapshots, and GET /repos/{repo_id}/test_reports/{test_report_id}/test_file_reports to get file-level coverage. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API-Key auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("codeclimate", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},codegen:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Codegen",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-codegen.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Connect to Codegen to create and manage AI-driven developer agents via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Codegen connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: POST /v1/organizations/{org_id}/agent/run to create an agent run, GET /v1/organizations/{org_id}/agent/run/{agent_run_id} to check status, GET /v1/organizations/{org_id}/users to list organization users, and POST /v1/organizations/{org_id}/agent/run/resume to resume a run. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API-key (Bearer) injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("codegen", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},companycam:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"CompanyCam",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-companycam.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage projects, photos, documents, comments, and users.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the CompanyCam connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /v2/projects to list projects, POST /v2/projects to create a project, GET /v2/projects/{project_id}/photos to list photos, POST /v2/projects/{project_id}/photos to add a photo, GET /v2/users/current to retrieve current user. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("companycam", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},confluence:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Confluence",visibility:"ga",vertical:["wiki"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-confluence.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Interact with pages, spaces, content, and search via REST API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use the Confluence connector via the proxy pattern, first retrieve your Atlassian cloud ID by calling GET /oauth/token/accessible-resources (returns an array of {id, url, name}). Then use cloud-scoped paths that include the /ex/confluence/{cloudId}/wiki prefix: GET /ex/confluence/{cloudId}/wiki/api/v2/pages (list pages), GET /ex/confluence/{cloudId}/wiki/api/v2/spaces (list spaces), POST /ex/confluence/{cloudId}/wiki/api/v2/pages (create page), GET /ex/confluence/{cloudId}/wiki/rest/api/content/{id} (retrieve content v1). Example: connectors.proxy("confluence", "/ex/confluence/{cloudId}/wiki/api/v2/pages"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""},integrationKeys:{nango:"confluence"}}},"constant-contact":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Constant Contact",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-constant-contact.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Constant Contact to manage contacts, campaigns, lists, and more.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Constant Contact connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated REST API access. Common endpoints include: GET /v3/contacts to list contacts, GET /v3/contacts/{contact_id} to retrieve a specific contact, POST /v3/contacts to create a contact, PUT /v3/contact_lists/{list_id} to update a contact list, and DELETE /v3/contacts/{contact_id} to delete a contact. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("constant-contact", "/v3/contacts"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"ctct-api-client",package_version:"latest"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""},integrationKeys:{nango:"constant-contact"}}},contactout:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"ContactOut",visibility:"beta",vertical:["crm"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-contactout.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Lookup email, phone, and profile data from LinkedIn and companies.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the ContactOut connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints include: GET /v1/people/linkedin/enrich, POST /v2/people/linkedin/batch, GET /v2/people/linkedin/batch/{job_uuid}, GET /v1/company/search, and GET /v1/email/verify. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("contactout", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},contentful:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Contentful",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-contentful.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Contentful to access and manage content via its APIs.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Contentful connector via the proxy pattern. Common useful endpoints include: GET /spaces/{space_id}/entries, GET /spaces/{space_id}/assets, POST /spaces/{space_id}/entries, PUT /spaces/{space_id}/environments/{environment_id}, GET /spaces/{space_id}/content_types. Requests are automatically authenticated and proxied through the SDK, so you can simply call connectors.proxy("contentful", "/spaces/{space_id}/entries"). Prefer using: connectors.proxy("contentful", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},contentstack:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Contentstack",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-contentstack.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Contentstack to access and manage content via its APIs.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Contentstack OAuth2 connector via the proxy pattern to interact with key REST endpoints: GET /v3/stacks (list stacks), GET /v3/stacks/{stack_uid}/environments (fetch environments), GET /v3/stacks/{stack_uid}/content_types (list content types), POST /apps-api/token (refresh or obtain access token), and GET /v3/stacks/{stack_uid}/entries (fetch entries). All requests are automatically authenticated and proxied through the SDK—prefer using connectors.proxy("contentstack", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},copper:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Copper",visibility:"beta",vertical:["crm"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-copper.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Copper (OAuth) to access Copper CRM data securely via OAuth2.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Copper (OAuth) connector via the proxy pattern. Common endpoints include: GET /developer_api/v1/account (fetch account details), GET /developer_api/v1/leads/{id} (retrieve a lead), POST /developer_api/v1/leads/search (list leads by search), and GET /developer_api/v1/people/{id} (fetch a person). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection—use connectors.proxy("copper", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},coros:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Coros",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-coros.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Coros to access and sync structured workouts and fitness data.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Coros connector via the proxy pattern. Common endpoints include POST /workouts/upload, GET /activities, GET /workouts, GET /sleep, and POST /webhooks. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection. Prefer using connectors.proxy("coros", "/path") for API calls. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"coros-sandbox":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Coros (Sandbox)",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-coros-sandbox.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Interact with Coros APIs in a test environment.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Coros (Sandbox) connector via the proxy pattern. Common useful endpoints include GET /activities, GET /activities/{id}, POST /workouts, GET /profile, DELETE /activities/{id}. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection. Use connectors.proxy("coros-sandbox", "/path") to send requests. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},cursor:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Cursor",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-cursor.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Programmatically create and manage AI-powered coding agents.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Cursor connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints include: GET /teams/members (list team members), GET /settings/repo-blocklists/repos (get admin-level repo blocklists), and GET /me (retrieve metadata about the API key). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("cursor", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"custom-mcp":{hasClient:!0,hasServer:!0,metadata:{verticals:["other"],displayName:"Custom MCP",logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-custom-mcp.svg",stage:"beta",authType:"CUSTOM",connect_ui:{pre_connect_input:"custom",flow:"client_managed"}}},cyberimpact:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Cyberimpact",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-cyberimpact.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage email contacts, groups, mailings, templates via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Cyberimpact connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /contacts to retrieve contacts, POST /contacts to create contacts, POST /contacts/batch to import a batch, GET /groups to list groups, GET /mailings/{id} to retrieve a mailing. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("cyberimpact", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},databricks:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Databricks for Databricks Apps (U2M)",visibility:"alpha",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-databricks.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",connectionCheckFrequency:604800,description:"Execute queries and manage data (Databricks Apps, U2M flow only)",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'## Mode 1 — SDK Proxy (REST API)\nThis mode is recommended for most use cases. It allows you to use the Databricks connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated REST API requests.\nThe proxy handles OAuth credentials and routing automatically — no SDK needed.\nStep 1 — Discover the warehouse ID:\n  GET /api/2.0/sql/warehouses/ → pick the warehouse_id from the response.\nStep 2 — Execute SQL via the Statement Execution API:\n  POST /api/2.0/sql/statements/ with body { "warehouse_id": "<id>", "statement": "<SQL>", "wait_timeout": "50s", "on_wait_timeout": "CONTINUE" }.\n  If status.state is "SUCCEEDED", rows are in result.data_array and column metadata in manifest.schema.columns.\n  If status.state is "PENDING" or "RUNNING", poll GET /api/2.0/sql/statements/{statement_id} until it completes.\nCommon SQL queries: SHOW CATALOGS, SHOW DATABASES, SHOW SCHEMAS, SHOW TABLES IN schema_name,\nDESCRIBE TABLE schema_name.table_name. For row samples, project the specific columns you\nneed and add a partition / cluster filter — see the cost-discipline section below.\n\n## CRITICAL: Cost discipline (Databricks SQL warehouses bill by DBU / warehouse uptime)\nDatabricks SQL warehouses are billed by DBU consumption, which is driven by warehouse\nuptime and warehouse size — not by bytes scanned per query. Bytes scanned still matter\na lot: a query that scans less data finishes faster, which means fewer DBU-seconds on\na warehouse with auto-stop and less risk of waking / keeping warehouses up for a\ndashboard refresh. A `SELECT *` over a wide / fact Delta table keeps the warehouse busy\nlonger and transfers far more data than necessary, and a dashboard that re-runs warehouse\nqueries every few seconds — without a cache — can run up thousands of dollars per day in\nDBU usage. The biggest cost levers are: warehouse size (use the smallest that meets your\nlatency target), Serverless vs Classic (Serverless auto-scales to zero so idle cost drops),\nauto-stop (lower idle timeout if your traffic is bursty), concurrency limits, and query\nduration. Follow these rules on every query:\n- Project exact columns. NEVER `SELECT *` on wide or fact Delta tables. Delta is columnar;\n  selecting only the columns you need cuts query duration (and therefore DBU usage), and\n  `LIMIT` does not undo the bytes read for the columns you selected.\n- Use partition / Z-ORDER columns. Add `WHERE event_date >= ...` (or whichever column the\n  Delta table is partitioned or Z-ordered on) so Databricks prunes data and the query\n  reads a slice instead of the whole table. Less data read → faster query → less DBU time.\n  Without this filter, fact-table reads scan the entire table.\n- Prefer pre-aggregated tables (`*_daily`, `*_summary`) or materialized views / Delta Live\n  Tables over raw event tables.\n- Aggregate on the warehouse — push `GROUP BY`, `SUM`, `COUNT` into SQL. Do NOT stream raw\n  rows to the client and aggregate in JavaScript.\n- Use `INFORMATION_SCHEMA`, `SHOW`, and `DESCRIBE TABLE` for schema discovery rather than\n  running `SELECT *` against the table itself just to see what columns exist.\n- Use Serverless SQL warehouses where possible — they auto-scale to zero and remove the\n  per-minute idle cost. Use the smallest size that meets your latency target.\n- For sample reads while exploring, write `SELECT col_a, col_b FROM t WHERE event_date >=\n  current_date() - INTERVAL 7 DAY LIMIT 5` — not `SELECT * FROM t LIMIT 5`.\n- Lean on Databricks SQL\'s result cache: identical query text against unchanged data\n  returns from cache for ~24 h and skips re-running the query, but it still requires\n  a running SQL warehouse to serve the cached result (the persistent / remote tier is\n  Serverless-only; on Pro / Classic warehouses the local cache is lost when the\n  warehouse stops). Treat it as a query-cost saver, not a "free responses" layer —\n  your app-level response cache (see below) is what actually saves the warehouse\n  from being woken on every poll.\n  Avoid embedding `now()` or other non-deterministic expressions in `WHERE` clauses\n  where you don\'t need to, so identical refreshes can hit the cache.\n- For incremental refreshes, persist a high-water-mark cursor (e.g. `last_seen_at`)\n  and filter with `WHERE updated_at > :last_seen` so refresh queries only scan the\n  delta. Databricks SQL named parameters use the `:name` marker, and the Statement\n  Execution API requires a matching `parameters` entry in the request body — Databricks\n  receives an unresolved placeholder otherwise. The request body looks like:\n    {\n      "warehouse_id": "<id>",\n      "statement": "SELECT id FROM events WHERE updated_at > :last_seen",\n      "parameters": [ { "name": "last_seen", "value": "2026-05-11T10:00:00Z",\n                        "type": "TIMESTAMP" } ],\n      "wait_timeout": "50s", "on_wait_timeout": "CONTINUE"\n    }\n  Pick the `type` that matches the bound column (`TIMESTAMP`, `DATE`, `STRING`, `INT`,\n  `BIGINT`, `BOOLEAN`, etc.).\n\n## CRITICAL: Cache read-only Databricks responses in your app\nDo NOT call Databricks on every page load or every poll cycle. For apps deployed outside\nDatabricks (e.g. on Replit) wrap every **read-only** Databricks-backed route in a\ndatabase-backed response cache (e.g. a Postgres `api_cache` table). "Read-only"\nmeans: dashboard / report / explorer routes that run `SELECT` statements,\n`SHOW` / `DESCRIBE TABLE` / `INFORMATION_SCHEMA` lookups, and other idempotent reads.\n\nDo NOT cache:\n- DML statements (`INSERT`, `UPDATE`, `MERGE`, `DELETE`, `COPY INTO`).\n- DDL statements (`CREATE`, `ALTER`, `DROP`, `GRANT`, `REVOKE`).\n- Statement-execution control endpoints (`POST /api/2.0/sql/statements/{id}/cancel`,\n  status polls via `GET /api/2.0/sql/statements/{id}`, job submissions, app deploys\n  via the Apps API). These are operational flows whose responses must reflect\n  current state.\n- Anything where the second identical request must still produce a side effect.\n\nCaching a mutating route would silently drop the second execution and return a stale\n"success" — a correctness bug, not a cost win. If a single route can run either\nread-only or mutating SQL (e.g. a generic "execute SQL" endpoint), gate caching on\nthe actual statement: bypass the cache when the parsed statement is anything other\nthan a read.\n\nThe cache key MUST include every dimension that scopes the response, not just the\nroute shape:\n- The connection / connector_config ID (so two different Databricks workspaces in the\n  same app never share a cached payload).\n- The org / tenant ID, when the app is multi-tenant.\n- The signed-in user ID, when the route returns user-scoped data or uses user-pass-through\n  credentials (Databricks U2M apps with `sql` scope inject a per-user\n  `x-forwarded-access-token`).\n- The endpoint path.\n- The normalized query / body params.\n\nA key shaped like `${connectionId}:${orgId}:${userId}:${endpoint}:${normalizedParams}`\nis a safe default. A key that is only `${endpoint}:${normalizedParams}` will silently\nserve org A\'s cached Databricks result to org B on the next request.\n\nMatch the cache TTL to the lowest auto-refresh interval exposed to the user; a 5-minute\nfloor is recommended.\n\n### Databricks Apps fallback (no Postgres / no outbound egress)\n\nDatabricks Apps can run with workspace-configured egress controls. The `api_cache`\nPostgres pattern above is the right primary layer when the workspace allows outbound\negress to a managed cache or Postgres — it shares cache entries across replicas, survives\nrestarts, and gives you a single TTL knob. Use it whenever it is available.\n\nWhen the workspace blocks the egress you would need (no managed cache, no Postgres,\nno outbound network), fall back to a small in-process / on-disk response cache inside\nthe app (e.g. an `lru-cache` keyed with the full\n`${connectionId}:${orgId}:${userId}:${endpoint}:${normalizedParams}` shape used\nabove — keep `orgId` in the fallback key so multi-tenant apps do not share cached\nDatabricks results between tenants — with the same 5-minute TTL floor). Accept the\ntrade-offs: cache entries are not shared across app replicas and are lost on restart.\n\nDo NOT treat the Databricks SQL result cache as a substitute for either of the\nabove. It is a useful second-level backstop, but:\n- Hitting either the local or remote SQL result cache still requires a running SQL\n  warehouse, which keeps DBU consumption on the clock.\n- The persistent (remote) result cache is Serverless-only; on Pro / Classic warehouses\n  the local result cache is lost the moment the warehouse stops or restarts.\n- The SQL result cache is per-query-text, so it doesn\'t collapse two simultaneous\n  identical requests from the same app into one call.\n\nLayer in pre-aggregated tables / Delta Live Tables on the data side to keep per-query\nduration small regardless of which cache tier serves any given request.\n\n## Auto-refresh / polling floor\nNever **re-run** a dashboard / report / explorer query against Databricks more often than\nonce every 5 minutes. This floor applies to query-driven refreshes — auto-refresh\nintervals, `refetchInterval`, `setInterval` loops that re-issue the underlying\n`POST /api/2.0/sql/statements/` call, etc.\n\nIt does NOT apply to short-lived status polling for an in-flight statement. While a\nstatement is `PENDING` or `RUNNING`, you should poll `GET /api/2.0/sql/statements/{id}`\nevery 1–3 seconds (with reasonable backoff) until it reaches `SUCCEEDED`, `FAILED`,\n`CANCELED`, or `CLOSED` — that is checking the status of a single statement, not\nre-running the dashboard query, so it does not waste warehouse compute and the user\nis actively waiting on the result.\n\nReal-time dashboards belong on a streaming pipeline + Delta Live Tables, not on a\npolling loop against raw Delta tables.\n\n## Mode 2 — Databricks CLI\nFor CLI operations (apps deploy, genie, workspace exploration), use the CLI proxy wrapper.\nThe token embeds your Replit identity and connection ID. The server validates\nyour identity, injects real Databricks credentials, and proxies the request.\nSecrets never leave the server. The token contains a space so it must be passed\nvia subprocess env (not shell export) to avoid shell parsing issues.\n\n```ts\nimport { ReplitConnectors } from "@replit/connectors-sdk";\nimport { execSync } from "child_process";\n\nconst connectors = new ReplitConnectors();\nconst config = await connectors.getCliConfig("databricks");\nconst args = process.argv.slice(2);\nconst result = execSync(`databricks ${args.join(" ")}`, {\n  encoding: "utf-8",\n  env: {\n    ...process.env,\n    DATABRICKS_HOST: config.host,\n    DATABRICKS_TOKEN: config.token,\n  },\n});\n```\n\nWhen to use each mode:\n  - SDK Proxy: SQL queries, programmatic API calls from code\n  - CLI Proxy: databricks apps deploy, databricks apps init, databricks genie, workspace exploration with CLI',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"https://www.databricks.com",apiDocsUrl:"https://docs.databricks.com/dev-tools/api/latest/"}}},"databricks-m2m":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!0,metadata:{verticals:["developer-tools"],audience:["enterprise"],displayName:"Databricks (Service Principal)",visibility:"alpha",logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-databricks.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Execute queries and manage Databricks data via a Service Principal",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'## Mode 1 — SDK Proxy (REST API)\nThis mode is recommended for most use cases. It allows you to use the Databricks connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated REST API requests.\nThe proxy handles OAuth credentials and routing automatically — no SDK needed.\nStep 1 — Discover the warehouse ID:\n  GET /api/2.0/sql/warehouses/ → pick the warehouse_id from the response.\nStep 2 — Execute SQL via the Statement Execution API:\n  POST /api/2.0/sql/statements/ with body { "warehouse_id": "<id>", "statement": "<SQL>", "wait_timeout": "50s", "on_wait_timeout": "CONTINUE" }.\n  If status.state is "SUCCEEDED", rows are in result.data_array and column metadata in manifest.schema.columns.\n  If status.state is "PENDING" or "RUNNING", poll GET /api/2.0/sql/statements/{statement_id} until it completes.\nCommon SQL queries: SHOW CATALOGS, SHOW DATABASES, SHOW SCHEMAS, SHOW TABLES IN schema_name,\nDESCRIBE TABLE schema_name.table_name. For row samples, project the specific columns you\nneed and add a partition / cluster filter — see the cost-discipline section below.\n\n## CRITICAL: Cost discipline (Databricks SQL warehouses bill by DBU / warehouse uptime)\nDatabricks SQL warehouses are billed by DBU consumption, which is driven by warehouse\nuptime and warehouse size — not by bytes scanned per query. Bytes scanned still matter\na lot: a query that scans less data finishes faster, which means fewer DBU-seconds on\na warehouse with auto-stop and less risk of waking / keeping warehouses up for a\ndashboard refresh. A `SELECT *` over a wide / fact Delta table keeps the warehouse busy\nlonger and transfers far more data than necessary, and a dashboard that re-runs warehouse\nqueries every few seconds — without a cache — can run up thousands of dollars per day in\nDBU usage. The biggest cost levers are: warehouse size (use the smallest that meets your\nlatency target), Serverless vs Classic (Serverless auto-scales to zero so idle cost drops),\nauto-stop (lower idle timeout if your traffic is bursty), concurrency limits, and query\nduration. Follow these rules on every query:\n- Project exact columns. NEVER `SELECT *` on wide or fact Delta tables. Delta is columnar;\n  selecting only the columns you need cuts query duration (and therefore DBU usage), and\n  `LIMIT` does not undo the bytes read for the columns you selected.\n- Use partition / Z-ORDER columns. Add `WHERE event_date >= ...` (or whichever column the\n  Delta table is partitioned or Z-ordered on) so Databricks prunes data and the query\n  reads a slice instead of the whole table. Less data read → faster query → less DBU time.\n  Without this filter, fact-table reads scan the entire table.\n- Prefer pre-aggregated tables (`*_daily`, `*_summary`) or materialized views / Delta Live\n  Tables over raw event tables.\n- Aggregate on the warehouse — push `GROUP BY`, `SUM`, `COUNT` into SQL. Do NOT stream raw\n  rows to the client and aggregate in JavaScript.\n- Use `INFORMATION_SCHEMA`, `SHOW`, and `DESCRIBE TABLE` for schema discovery rather than\n  running `SELECT *` against the table itself just to see what columns exist.\n- Use Serverless SQL warehouses where possible — they auto-scale to zero and remove the\n  per-minute idle cost. Use the smallest size that meets your latency target.\n- For sample reads while exploring, write `SELECT col_a, col_b FROM t WHERE event_date >=\n  current_date() - INTERVAL 7 DAY LIMIT 5` — not `SELECT * FROM t LIMIT 5`.\n- Lean on Databricks SQL\'s result cache: identical query text against unchanged data\n  returns from cache for ~24 h and skips re-running the query, but it still requires\n  a running SQL warehouse to serve the cached result (the persistent / remote tier is\n  Serverless-only; on Pro / Classic warehouses the local cache is lost when the\n  warehouse stops). Treat it as a query-cost saver, not a "free responses" layer —\n  your app-level response cache (see below) is what actually saves the warehouse\n  from being woken on every poll.\n  Avoid embedding `now()` or other non-deterministic expressions in `WHERE` clauses\n  where you don\'t need to, so identical refreshes can hit the cache.\n- For incremental refreshes, persist a high-water-mark cursor (e.g. `last_seen_at`)\n  and filter with `WHERE updated_at > :last_seen` so refresh queries only scan the\n  delta. Databricks SQL named parameters use the `:name` marker, and the Statement\n  Execution API requires a matching `parameters` entry in the request body — Databricks\n  receives an unresolved placeholder otherwise. The request body looks like:\n    {\n      "warehouse_id": "<id>",\n      "statement": "SELECT id FROM events WHERE updated_at > :last_seen",\n      "parameters": [ { "name": "last_seen", "value": "2026-05-11T10:00:00Z",\n                        "type": "TIMESTAMP" } ],\n      "wait_timeout": "50s", "on_wait_timeout": "CONTINUE"\n    }\n  Pick the `type` that matches the bound column (`TIMESTAMP`, `DATE`, `STRING`, `INT`,\n  `BIGINT`, `BOOLEAN`, etc.).\n\n## CRITICAL: Cache read-only Databricks responses in your app\nDo NOT call Databricks on every page load or every poll cycle. For apps deployed outside\nDatabricks (e.g. on Replit) wrap every **read-only** Databricks-backed route in a\ndatabase-backed response cache (e.g. a Postgres `api_cache` table). "Read-only"\nmeans: dashboard / report / explorer routes that run `SELECT` statements,\n`SHOW` / `DESCRIBE TABLE` / `INFORMATION_SCHEMA` lookups, and other idempotent reads.\n\nDo NOT cache:\n- DML statements (`INSERT`, `UPDATE`, `MERGE`, `DELETE`, `COPY INTO`).\n- DDL statements (`CREATE`, `ALTER`, `DROP`, `GRANT`, `REVOKE`).\n- Statement-execution control endpoints (`POST /api/2.0/sql/statements/{id}/cancel`,\n  status polls via `GET /api/2.0/sql/statements/{id}`, job submissions, app deploys\n  via the Apps API). These are operational flows whose responses must reflect\n  current state.\n- Anything where the second identical request must still produce a side effect.\n\nCaching a mutating route would silently drop the second execution and return a stale\n"success" — a correctness bug, not a cost win. If a single route can run either\nread-only or mutating SQL (e.g. a generic "execute SQL" endpoint), gate caching on\nthe actual statement: bypass the cache when the parsed statement is anything other\nthan a read.\n\nThe cache key MUST include every dimension that scopes the response, not just the\nroute shape:\n- The connection / connector_config ID (so two different Databricks workspaces in the\n  same app never share a cached payload). For this M2M connector the service-principal\n  identity is shared across users, so the connection ID is the main scoping dimension.\n- The org / tenant ID, when the app is multi-tenant.\n- The signed-in user ID, when the route returns user-scoped data even though the\n  underlying Databricks call is made as the service principal.\n- The endpoint path.\n- The normalized query / body params.\n\nA key shaped like `${connectionId}:${orgId}:${userId}:${endpoint}:${normalizedParams}`\nis a safe default. A key that is only `${endpoint}:${normalizedParams}` will silently\nserve org A\'s cached Databricks result to org B on the next request.\n\nMatch the cache TTL to the lowest auto-refresh interval exposed to the user; a 5-minute\nfloor is recommended.\n\n### Databricks Apps fallback (no Postgres / no outbound egress)\n\nDatabricks Apps can run with workspace-configured egress controls. The `api_cache`\nPostgres pattern above is the right primary layer when the workspace allows outbound\negress to a managed cache or Postgres — it shares cache entries across replicas, survives\nrestarts, and gives you a single TTL knob. Use it whenever it is available.\n\nWhen the workspace blocks the egress you would need (no managed cache, no Postgres,\nno outbound network), fall back to a small in-process / on-disk response cache inside\nthe app (e.g. an `lru-cache` keyed with the full\n`${connectionId}:${orgId}:${userId}:${endpoint}:${normalizedParams}` shape used\nabove — keep `orgId` in the fallback key so multi-tenant apps do not share cached\nDatabricks results between tenants — with the same 5-minute TTL floor). Accept the\ntrade-offs: cache entries are not shared across app replicas and are lost on restart.\n\nDo NOT treat the Databricks SQL result cache as a substitute for either of the\nabove. It is a useful second-level backstop, but:\n- Hitting either the local or remote SQL result cache still requires a running SQL\n  warehouse, which keeps DBU consumption on the clock.\n- The persistent (remote) result cache is Serverless-only; on Pro / Classic warehouses\n  the local result cache is lost the moment the warehouse stops or restarts.\n- The SQL result cache is per-query-text, so it doesn\'t collapse two simultaneous\n  identical requests from the same app into one call.\n\nLayer in pre-aggregated tables / Delta Live Tables on the data side to keep per-query\nduration small regardless of which cache tier serves any given request.\n\n## Auto-refresh / polling floor\nNever **re-run** a dashboard / report / explorer query against Databricks more often than\nonce every 5 minutes. This floor applies to query-driven refreshes — auto-refresh\nintervals, `refetchInterval`, `setInterval` loops that re-issue the underlying\n`POST /api/2.0/sql/statements/` call, etc.\n\nIt does NOT apply to short-lived status polling for an in-flight statement. While a\nstatement is `PENDING` or `RUNNING`, you should poll `GET /api/2.0/sql/statements/{id}`\nevery 1–3 seconds (with reasonable backoff) until it reaches `SUCCEEDED`, `FAILED`,\n`CANCELED`, or `CLOSED` — that is checking the status of a single statement, not\nre-running the dashboard query, so it does not waste warehouse compute and the user\nis actively waiting on the result.\n\nReal-time dashboards belong on a streaming pipeline + Delta Live Tables, not on a\npolling loop against raw Delta tables.\n\n## Mode 2 — Databricks CLI\nFor CLI operations (apps deploy, genie, workspace exploration), use the CLI proxy wrapper.\nThe token embeds your Replit identity and connection ID. The server validates\nyour identity, injects real Databricks credentials, and proxies the request.\nSecrets never leave the server. The token contains a space so it must be passed\nvia subprocess env (not shell export) to avoid shell parsing issues.\n\n```ts\nimport { ReplitConnectors } from "@replit/connectors-sdk";\nimport { execSync } from "child_process";\n\nconst connectors = new ReplitConnectors();\nconst config = await connectors.getCliConfig("databricks-m2m");\nconst args = process.argv.slice(2);\nconst result = execSync(`databricks ${args.join(" ")}`, {\n  encoding: "utf-8",\n  env: {\n    ...process.env,\n    DATABRICKS_HOST: config.host,\n    DATABRICKS_TOKEN: config.token,\n  },\n});\n```\n\nWhen to use each mode:\n  - SDK Proxy: SQL queries, programmatic API calls from code\n  - CLI Proxy: databricks apps deploy, databricks apps init, databricks genie, workspace exploration with CLI',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"https://www.databricks.com",apiDocsUrl:"https://docs.databricks.com/dev-tools/api/latest/"}}},datadog:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Datadog",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-datadog.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Submit and query metrics, events, dashboards, and monitors.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Datadog connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: POST /api/v1/series to submit custom metrics, GET /api/v1/query to query metrics, POST /api/v1/events to create events, GET /api/v1/dashboard to list dashboards, POST /api/v1/monitor to create monitors. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("datadog", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"@datadog/datadog-api-client",package_version:"latest"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},datev:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Datev",visibility:"beta",vertical:["hris"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-datev.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access and manage accounting, tenants, and configurations.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Datev connector via the proxy pattern to call endpoints like GET /v10/user-tenants, GET /api/configurazioni, GET /connect/userinfo, POST /connect/token, and GET /efat/api/v1/ditte. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 access token injection and license Authorization-Key (and User-Tenant header when required) added under the hood. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("datev", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"datto-rmm":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Datto",visibility:"beta",vertical:["ticketing"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-datto-rmm.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access and manage sites, devices, accounts, and audit data",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Datto connector via the proxy pattern to access key REST API endpoints such as GET /api/v2/account (retrieve account info), GET /api/v2/account/devices (list devices), GET /api/v2/audit/device/{deviceUid} (get device audit logs), POST /api/v2/sites (create a site), and GET /api/v2/account/sites (list sites). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("datto-rmm", "/v2/account/devices"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},deel:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Deel",visibility:"beta",vertical:["hris"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-deel.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage workforce, contracts, people, and webhooks via OAuth2 APIs.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Deel connector via the proxy pattern: for example, to list contracts use GET /rest/v2/contracts; to retrieve people use GET /rest/v2/people; to fetch webhook event types use GET /webhooks/events; to create or refresh OAuth2 tokens use POST /oauth2/tokens; or to authorize use GET /oauth2/authorize. The requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("deel", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"deel-sandbox":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Deel (Sandbox)",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-deel-sandbox.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Test OAuth2-protected endpoints in a safe, isolated environment.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Deel (Sandbox) connector via proxy: proxies automatically inject and refresh OAuth2 tokens. Common endpoints include: GET /contracts, POST /contracts, GET /workers, POST /invoices, GET /timesheets. Perform requests using connectors.proxy("deel-sandbox", "/contracts") (or other paths). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},demodesk:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"DemoDesk",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-demodesk.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Schedule meetings, manage users, and access recording history",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the DemoDesk connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints include: GET /api/v1/demo_templates to list meeting templates, POST /api/v1/scheduled_demos to create meetings, GET /api/v1/demos to list meetings and their statuses, POST /api/v1/externally_recorded_demos to import historical recordings. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API-key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("demodesk", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},devin:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Devin",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-devin.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage AI coding sessions, messages, secrets, and attachments",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Devin connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints include: POST /v1/sessions to create a session, POST /v1/sessions/{session_id}/messages to send a message, GET /v1/sessions/{session_id} to retrieve session details, POST /v1/sessions/{session_id}/attachments to upload attachments, and GET /v1/sessions/{session_id}/attachments/{attachment_id} to download attachments. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("devin", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},dialpad:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Dialpad",visibility:"beta",vertical:["communication"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-dialpad.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Dialpad to manage calls, users, routers, and more via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Dialpad connector via the proxy pattern to interact with Dialpad’s OAuth2-protected API. Common endpoints include: POST /api/v2/call (initiate outbound calls), GET /api/v2/users/me (fetch authenticated user), POST /api/v2/callrouters (create call router), PATCH /api/v2/callrouters/{id} (update call router), DELETE /api/v2/callrouters/{id} (delete call router). Wrap requests using connectors.proxy("dialpad", "/path") so that auth tokens are injected and refreshed automatically. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"dialpad-sandbox":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Dialpad (Sandbox)",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["communication"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-dialpad-sandbox.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access user, company, call, event, and auth management endpoints.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Dialpad (Sandbox) connector via the proxy pattern to interact with sandbox Dialpad APIs. Commonly used endpoints include: GET /api/v2/users/me to retrieve authenticated user info; GET /api/v2/company/ to list company details; POST /oauth2/token to obtain or refresh access tokens; POST /oauth2/deauthorize to revoke tokens; WSS via WebSocket for events (e.g., connecting to wss://platform-websockets-5bwy6zprxa-uc.a.run.app/events/<token>). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection—simply call connectors.proxy("dialpad-sandbox", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},digitalocean:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"DigitalOcean",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-digitalocean.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to DigitalOcean to manage infrastructure and resources via its API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the DigitalOcean connector via the proxy pattern to call common API endpoints such as: GET /v2/droplets (list droplets), POST /v2/droplets (create a droplet), DELETE /v2/droplets/{droplet_id} (destroy a droplet), GET /v2/account (get account info), and POST /v2/domains (create a domain). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("digitalocean", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},discord:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Discord",visibility:"ga",vertical:["social-media"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-discord.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access user info, channels, messages, and OAuth2 flows.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Discord connector via the proxy pattern to call common endpoints—e.g., GET /users/@me to retrieve authenticated user info, GET /channels/{channel.id}/messages to list channel messages, POST /channels/{channel.id}/messages to create messages, GET /channels/{channel.id}/invites to list invites. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection; use connectors.proxy("discord", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""},integrationKeys:{nango:"discord"}}},discourse:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Discourse",visibility:"beta",vertical:["communication"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-discourse.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Connect to Discourse to manage forums via its REST API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Discourse connector via the proxy pattern for API interactions. Common endpoints include: GET /categories to list categories, POST /categories to create a category, POST /t (topics) to create a topic, GET /t/{topic_id} to fetch topic details, and GET /users/{username} to retrieve user info. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key–based authentication. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("discourse", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"discourse2",package_version:"latest"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},dixa:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Dixa",visibility:"beta",vertical:["ticketing"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-dixa.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Connect to Dixa to access and manage your customer support data via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Dixa connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints include: GET /v1/conversations/{conversationId} to fetch a conversation, POST /v1/conversations/{conversationId}/messages to send a message, GET /v1/agents to list agents. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("dixa", "/v1/conversations/{conversationId}"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},document360:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Document360",visibility:"beta",vertical:["wiki"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-document360.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Programmatically manage your knowledge base content via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Document360 connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /projects to list projects, GET /articles/{articleId} to retrieve an article, POST /articles to create a new article. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API token injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("document360", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},docusign:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"DocuSign",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-docusign.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Send envelopes, manage documents, recipients, and templates.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the DocuSign connector via the proxy pattern. Common endpoints include: POST /v2.1/accounts/{accountId}/envelopes (create envelope), GET /v2.1/accounts/{accountId}/envelopes/{envelopeId} (get envelope status), GET /v2.1/accounts/{accountId}/envelopes/{envelopeId}/documents/{documentId} (download document), GET /v2.1/accounts/{accountId}/envelopes/{envelopeId}/recipients (list recipients), and GET /v2.1/accounts/{accountId}/envelopes?from_to_status=[...] (search envelopes). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection—prefer using connectors.proxy("docusign", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"docusign-sandbox":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"DocuSign (Sandbox)",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-docusign-sandbox.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage envelopes, users, and account info via REST and SOAP APIs.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use this connector, your agent can call common endpoints like: GET /oauth/userinfo, GET /accounts/{accountId}/envelopes (list), POST /accounts/{accountId}/envelopes (create), GET /restapi/v2.1/accounts/{accountId}/envelopes/{envelopeId}, and for SOAP use dsapi.asmx via https://demo.docusign.net/api/3.0/dsapi.asmx. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 auth injection—use connectors.proxy("docusign-sandbox", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},drata:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Drata",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-drata.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Automate compliance workflows and manage evidence, controls, and users.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Drata connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /controls to list all controls, GET /evidence to fetch evidence items, POST /evidence to upload evidence, GET /users to list users. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("drata", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},drchrono:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"DrChrono",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-drchrono.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access healthcare data such as patients, appointments, documents, and more.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the DrChrono connector via the proxy pattern, proxies inject OAuth2 tokens automatically. Common endpoints include: GET /api/users/current, GET/POST /api/patients, GET/POST /api/appointments, POST /api/documents, POST /o/token/ to refresh. Use connectors.proxy("drchrono", "/path") for all requests. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},dropbox:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Dropbox",visibility:"alpha",vertical:["wiki","file-storage"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-dropbox.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage files, metadata, uploads, downloads, and account info.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Dropbox connector via the proxy pattern by calling connectors.proxy("dropbox", "/path"). Common endpoints include: POST /2/users/get_current_account, POST /2/files/list_folder, POST /2/files/upload, POST /2/files/download, and POST /2/files/get_metadata. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""},integrationKeys:{nango:"dropbox"}}},"dropbox-sign":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Dropbox Sign",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-dropbox-sign.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Dropbox Sign to manage signature requests, templates, and files.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Dropbox Sign connector via the proxy pattern to perform eSignature operations. Common endpoints include: POST /signature_request/send, GET /signature_request/list, GET /signature_request/files, POST /template/create_embedded_draft, and PUT /api_app/{client_id}. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refreshing—use connectors.proxy("dropbox-sign", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},ebay:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"eBay",visibility:"beta",vertical:["commerce"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-ebay.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Interact with eBay’s RESTful APIs using OAuth2 authentication.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the eBay connector via the proxy pattern. Common useful endpoints include GET /sell/fulfillment/v1/order, GET /buy/browse/v1/item/{item_id}, POST /sell/inventory/v1/inventory_item, DELETE /sell/fulfillment/v1/order/{order_id}, and POST /identity/v1/oauth2/token. The requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection and refresh. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("ebay", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"ebay-sandbox":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"eBay (Sandbox)",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["commerce"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-ebay-sandbox.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Perform OAuth2-authenticated API operations in the sandbox environment.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the eBay (Sandbox) connector via the proxy pattern. Common endpoints include: POST /identity/v1/oauth2/token (client credentials grant), POST /identity/v1/oauth2/token (authorization code grant), POST /identity/v1/oauth2/token (refresh token), GET /buy/inventory/v1/inventory_item, GET /sell/fulfillment/v1/order. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection—use connectors.proxy("ebay-sandbox", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},egnyte:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Egnyte",visibility:"beta",vertical:["file-storage"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-egnyte.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Perform file system, links, and user management operations via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Egnyte connector via the proxy pattern to call common endpoints such as GET /v1/fs/ids/file/{GROUP_ID} (download file), GET /v1/links (list links), GET /v2/users (list users), POST /v1/fs/ids/file/{GROUP_ID} (upload or create file), and DELETE /v1/links/{link_id} (delete link). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 auth injection; use connectors.proxy("egnyte", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},elevenlabs:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"ElevenLabs",visibility:"beta",vertical:["communication","other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-elevenlabs.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Convert text to speech, transcribe audio, and manage voices.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use this connector to interact with ElevenLabs’ API via the proxy pattern. Commonly used endpoints include: GET /v1/models, GET /v1/voices, POST /v1/text-to-speech/{voice_id}, and GET /v1/languages. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic authentication injected into headers. To send a request, use connectors.proxy("elevenlabs", "/v1/text-to-speech/{voice_id}") or similar. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},elevio:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Elevio",visibility:"beta",vertical:["wiki","ticketing"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-elevio.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Connect to Elevio to manage and embed in-app knowledge base articles.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Elevio connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /v1/articles to list articles, POST /v1/articles to create an article, PUT /v1/articles/{id} to update an article, DELETE /v1/articles/{id} to delete an article. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key and JWT auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("elevio", "/v1/articles"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"elevio",package_version:"1.3.8"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"employment-hero":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Employment Hero",visibility:"beta",vertical:["hris"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-employment-hero.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access HR data like employees, payslips, leave, and certifications.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Employment Hero connector via the proxy pattern and common endpoints: GET /v1/organisations/:organisation_id/employees, GET /v1/organisations/:organisation_id/employees/:employee_id/payslips, GET /v1/organisations/:organisation_id/employees/:employee_id/leave_requests, GET /v1/organisations/:organisation_id/employees/:employee_id/work_eligibility, GET /v1/organisations/:organisation_id/certifications. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 bearer token injection and refresh. Use connectors.proxy("employment-hero", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},envoy:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Envoy",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-envoy.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage workplace data like locations, employees, invites, desks, and more.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Envoy connector via the proxy pattern. Common useful endpoints include:\n- GET /v1/locations (list locations)\n- GET /v1/employees (list employees)\n- POST /v1/invites (create an invite)\n- GET /v1/desks (list desks)\n- GET /v1/reservations (list reservations)\nRequests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection—prefer using: connectors.proxy("envoy", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"epic-games":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Epic Games",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-epic-games.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access OAuth-protected Epic Online Services and related APIs.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Epic Games connector via the proxy pattern to call common endpoints, for example: GET /account/v1/account/me, GET /friends/v1/users/{userId}/friends, GET /presence/v1/users/{userId}/presence, POST /game/v1/matchmaking/search, GET /store/v1/catalog/items. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh. Use connectors.proxy("epic-games", "/path") for all calls. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},eventbrite:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Eventbrite",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-eventbrite.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage events, venues, organizations, attendees, tickets and more.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Eventbrite connector via the proxy pattern. The most common useful API endpoints include: GET /v3/organizations/:organization_id/events/, GET /v3/events/:event_id/, GET /v3/venues/:venue_id/events/, and GET /v3/events/:event_id/attendees/ (plus listing ticket classes or orders). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 authentication injection—simply call connectors.proxy("eventbrite", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},exa:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Exa",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-exa.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Power AI search, crawling, similarity, answer, and research APIs.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Exa connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints include: POST /search (web search with content), POST /findSimilar (retrieve similar pages), POST /answer (AI-generated direct answers), and POST /contents (get parsed HTML from results). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("exa", "/search"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"exa-js",package_version:"latest"}]},exampleUsage:{javascript:[{name:"search",snippet:'import { ReplitConnectors } from "@replit/connectors-sdk";\n\nconst connectors = new ReplitConnectors();\nconst response = await connectors.proxy("exa", "/search", {\n  method: "POST",\n  headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },\n  body: JSON.stringify({ query: "Latest research in LLMs", numResults: 3 }),\n});\n\nif (!response.ok) {\n  const text = await response.text().catch(() => "");\n  throw new Error(`HTTP ${response.status}: ${text}`);\n}\n\nconst body = await response.json();\n\nif (!Array.isArray(body.results) || body.results.length === 0) {\n  throw new Error("Expected at least one search result");\n}\n\nexport const result = { count: body.results.length, first: body.results[0]?.url };'},{name:"answer",snippet:'import { ReplitConnectors } from "@replit/connectors-sdk";\n\nconst connectors = new ReplitConnectors();\nconst response = await connectors.proxy("exa", "/answer", {\n  method: "POST",\n  headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },\n  body: JSON.stringify({ query: "What is the capital of France?" }),\n});\n\nif (!response.ok) {\n  const text = await response.text().catch(() => "");\n  throw new Error(`HTTP ${response.status}: ${text}`);\n}\n\nconst body = await response.json();\n\nif (typeof body.answer !== "string" || body.answer.length === 0) {\n  throw new Error("Expected a non-empty answer string");\n}\n\nexport const result = { answer: body.answer.slice(0, 100), citations: Array.isArray(body.citations) ? body.citations.length : 0 };'}]}},links:{webUrl:"https://exa.ai",apiDocsUrl:"https://exa.ai/docs"}}},"exact-online":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Exact Online",visibility:"beta",vertical:["accounting"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-exact-online.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access accounting, CRM, and ERP data via REST endpoints.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Exact Online connector via the proxy pattern. Common useful endpoints include: GET /api/v1/{division}/crm/Accounts, GET /api/v1/{division}/salesinvoice/SalesInvoices, POST /api/v1/{division}/salesinvoice/SalesInvoices, GET /api/v1/{division}/crm/Contacts, GET /api/v1/{division}/current/Me. The connector handles OAuth2 automatically — tokens are injected and refreshed under the hood, and your requests are proxied through the SDK. For example, use connectors.proxy("exact-online", "/api/v1/{division}/crm/Accounts") to make calls. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},exist:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Exist",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-exist.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Exist to read and write personal analytics data via OAuth2.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Exist connector via the proxy pattern. Common API endpoints include: GET /api/2/attributes/with-values/, GET /api/2/averages/, GET /api/2/correlations/combo/, POST /api/2/auth/simple-token/, POST /api/1/attributes/update/. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("exist", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},facebook:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Facebook",visibility:"beta",vertical:["social-media"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-facebook.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access user data, pages, posts, and other Graph API endpoints.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Facebook connector via the proxy pattern to interact with the Graph API. Common useful endpoints include: GET /me (retrieve current user profile), GET /me/friends (list friends), GET /{page_id}/posts (fetch page posts), POST /{page_id}/feed (publish a post), GET /search (search across Graph entities). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection—use connectors.proxy("facebook", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},factorial:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Factorial",visibility:"beta",vertical:["hris"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-factorial.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access HR resources like employees, documents, and custom resources.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Factorial connector via the proxy pattern to interact with key endpoints such as GET /resources/employees/employees, GET /resources/documents/documents, GET /resources/documents/folders, GET /resources/custom_resources/resources, and GET /resources/custom_resources/schemas. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh. To invoke, use: connectors.proxy("factorial", "/resources/employees/employees") (adjust the path as needed). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},fairing:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Fairing",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-fairing.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Retrieve and manage post-purchase survey response data via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Fairing connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints (based on available documentation and use cases): GET /survey-responses (to list responses), GET /survey-responses/{id} (to get a single response), POST /data-sync (to initiate custom data export), GET /integrations (to list integrations). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("fairing", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},falai:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"fal.ai",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-falai.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Queue model inference requests via a hosted queue service.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the fal.ai connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: POST /{model_id} to submit a new inference request to the queue, GET /{model_id}/requests/{request_id}/status to check request status, GET /{model_id}/requests/{request_id} to fetch completed results, and PUT /{model_id}/requests/{request_id}/cancel to cancel queued requests. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("falai", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"@fal-ai/client",package_version:"latest"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},fanvue:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Fanvue",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-fanvue.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access creator data, chats, posts, followers, media, and insights",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use this connector, employ the proxy pattern: requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 auth injection. Commonly used API endpoints include GET /users/me (fetch current user), GET /chats (list chats), POST /chats (send message), GET /insights (retrieve metrics), and POST /posts (create post). Use connectors.proxy("fanvue", "/path") to invoke Fanvue API paths with auth injected automatically. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"fathom-oauth":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Fathom",visibility:"beta",vertical:["communication","streaming"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-fathom-oauth.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access meeting insights, transcripts, summaries, and action items",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Fathom (OAuth) connector via the proxy pattern to fetch meeting data. Common useful endpoints include: GET /external/v1/meetings (list meetings), GET /external/v1/meetings?include_transcript=true (list meetings with transcripts), GET /external/v1/recordings/{recording_id}/transcript (get full transcript), and GET /external/v1/meetings?include_action_items=true (list meetings with action items). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection and refreshing. Use connectors.proxy("fathom-oauth", "/path") for all requests. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},fellow:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Fellow",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-fellow.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Access meeting transcripts, notes, action items, and more.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Fellow connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /api/users/me to get the authenticated user; GET /api/meetings to list meetings; GET /api/notes to retrieve notes; POST /api/notes to create a note. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection via headers. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("fellow", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"fiber-ai":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Fiber AI",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-fiber-ai.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Connect to Fiber AI to enrich people, company, and job data via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Fiber AI connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints include POST /v1/email-to-person/single (reverse email lookup), POST /v1/search/person (search person), POST /v1/search/company (search company), and POST /v1/verify/email (email verification). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("fiber-ai", "/v1/search/person"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},figma:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Figma",visibility:"alpha",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-figma.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access and interact with design files, comments, users, projects, and more.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Figma connector via the proxy pattern to access common endpoints like GET /v1/me (fetch authenticated user), GET /v1/files/:file_key (retrieve file data), GET /v1/projects/:project_id/files (list files in a project), GET /v1/files/:file_key/versions (retrieve file versions), and GET /v1/images/:file_key (generate images). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh. Use connectors.proxy("figma", "/path") to call the API. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""},integrationKeys:{nango:"figma"}}},fillout:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Fillout",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-fillout.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access forms and submissions via OAuth-authenticated API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Fillout (Oauth) connector via the proxy pattern to access common endpoints such as: GET /v1/api/forms, GET /v1/api/forms/{formId}/submissions, POST /v1/api/forms/{formId}/submissions, POST /public/oauth/accessToken, DELETE /public/oauth/invalidate. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection — invoke using connectors.proxy("fillout", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},findymail:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"FindyMail",visibility:"beta",vertical:["crm"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-findymail.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Find and verify professional email addresses quickly.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the FindyMail connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints include POST /api/search/name (find by name & domain), POST /api/search/domain (find by domain), POST /api/search/linkedin (find by LinkedIn URL), POST /api/verify (verify email), and POST /api/search/phone (find phone by LinkedIn URL). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection in headers. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("findymail", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"findymail-ts",package_version:"1.0.1"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},firecrawl:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Firecrawl",visibility:"beta",vertical:["enrichment"],audience:["paid"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-firecrawl.svg",authType:"API_KEY",accessType:"global",blueprint:{agentInstructions:"",packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},fireflies:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Fireflies",visibility:"beta",vertical:["communication"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-fireflies.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Access meeting transcripts, summaries, action items, and uploads.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Fireflies connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API access. Common endpoints include GET /graphql (for queries like transcripts, summaries), POST /graphql (for mutations such as uploadAudio), and POST /graphql (for live meeting actions like addToLiveMeeting). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("fireflies", "/graphql"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"@firefliesai/api-sdk",package_version:"1.0.0"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},firstbase:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Firstbase",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-firstbase.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Connect to Firstbase to manage users, assets, catalog, and orders.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Firstbase connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /scim/v2/Users to list users, POST /scim/v2/Users to onboard, GET /api/inventory to view inventory, GET /api/catalog/skus to view catalog, POST /api/orders to place orders. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("firstbase", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},fiserv:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Fiserv",visibility:"beta",vertical:["banking"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-fiserv.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Connect to Fiserv to access Fiserv APIs via API key authentication.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Fiserv connector via the proxy pattern for API calls. Common endpoints include: POST /omnipay/financial/adjustments/v1.0/post-adjustment (to post financial adjustments), GET /sandbox/exp/v1/authorisations (to request authorisations), and other OmniPay endpoints under the base URL. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("fiserv", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},fitbit:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Fitbit",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-fitbit.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access user activity, sleep, heart rate, and profile data.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Fitbit connector via the proxy pattern to call endpoints such as GET /1/user/-/profile.json (Get Profile), GET /1/user/-/activities/heart/date/today/1d.json (Heart Rate), GET /1/user/-/sleep/date/today/1d.json (Sleep Logs), and GET /1/user/-/activities/date/today.json (Daily Activity); requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh; prefer using: connectors.proxy("fitbit", "/path"); Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},float:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Float",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-float.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Programmatically manage scheduling, people, projects, and time data.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Float connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /people to list team members, GET /projects to list projects, POST /logged-time to log time entries. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("float", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},folk:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Folk",visibility:"beta",vertical:["crm"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-folk.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage people, companies, deals, notes, reminders, and interactions",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Folk connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /people to list all people, GET /companies to list companies, POST /deals to create a deal, GET /notes to fetch notes, POST /reminders to create a reminder. Authentication is handled automatically via headers when using the SDK. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("folk", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},fortnox:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Fortnox",visibility:"beta",vertical:["accounting"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-fortnox.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access accounting, invoicing, vouchers, orders, and supplier data",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Fortnox connector via the proxy pattern with automatic OAuth2 injection. Common endpoints include GET /customers (list customers), POST /orders (create an order), POST /vouchers (create a voucher), GET /articleurlconnections (list article URL connections), and POST /supplierinvoiceexternalurlconnections (create supplier invoice URL connection). Construct calls like: connectors.proxy("fortnox", "/customers") or connectors.proxy("fortnox", "/orders"). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},freeagent:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"FreeAgent",visibility:"beta",vertical:["accounting"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-freeagent.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage invoices, contacts, clients, and accounting data.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the FreeAgent connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /v2/invoices to list invoices, POST /v2/invoices to create invoice, GET /v2/invoices/{id}/pdf to retrieve invoice PDF, GET /v2/clients to list practice clients (for accountancy practice), GET /v2/invoices/{id} to get invoice details. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("freeagent", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"freeagent-sandbox":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"FreeAgent (Sandbox)",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["accounting"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-freeagent-sandbox.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access and manage your accounting data in the sandbox environment.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the FreeAgent (Sandbox) connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /v2/companies to list companies, GET /v2/invoices to retrieve invoices, POST /v2/contacts to create a contact. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("freeagent-sandbox", "/v2/companies"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""},integrationKeys:{nango:"freeagent-sandbox"}}},freshbooks:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"FreshBooks",visibility:"beta",vertical:["accounting"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-freshbooks.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access and manage accounting, invoicing, clients, time entries, and more.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the FreshBooks connector via the proxy pattern to issue calls such as: GET /accounting/account/{accountId}/invoices/invoices, POST /accounting/account/{accountId}/users/clients, GET /timetracking/business/{businessId}/time_entries, GET /auth/api/v1/users/me, and POST /accounting/account/{accountId}/systems/gateways. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh. Use connectors.proxy("freshbooks", "/path") for all calls. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},freshsales:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Freshsales",visibility:"beta",vertical:["crm"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-freshsales.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage CRM entities like leads, contacts, and sales activities.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Freshsales connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common useful endpoints include: GET /api/leads/view/{view_id}, GET /api/contacts/{id}, POST /api/contacts, PUT /api/leads/{id}. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("freshsales", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"freshsales",package_version:"0.3.0"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},freshteam:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Freshteam",visibility:"beta",vertical:["hris"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-freshteam.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Access HR data like employees, teams, time-offs, and more.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Freshteam connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints include: GET /api/employees to list employees; POST /api/employees to create an employee; GET /api/teams to list teams; GET /api/time_offs to list time-off requests; POST /api/time_offs to create time-off requests. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key header injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("freshteam", "/api/employees"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"@freshworks/api-sdk",package_version:"latest"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},front:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Front",visibility:"beta",vertical:["ticketing"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-front.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage conversations, contacts, messages, and triggers in Front",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Front connector via the proxy pattern to call common endpoints such as:\n• GET /contacts — List Contacts\n• POST /contacts — Create Contact\n• POST /conversations/search/{query} — Search Conversations\n• POST /applications/{application_uid}/events — Trigger Application Event\n• POST /inboxes/{inbox_id}/imported_messages — Import Message\nRequests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refreshing. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("front", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},fullenrich:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"FullEnrich",visibility:"beta",vertical:["crm"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-fullenrich.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Connect to FullEnrich to enrich B2B contact and company data via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the FullEnrich connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: POST /enrich for contact enrichment, POST /reverse (or Reverse Email Lookup) for identifying person by email, GET /search for querying contacts or companies—all proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("fullenrich", "/enrich") (or "/reverse" or "/search"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},gamma:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Gamma",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-gamma.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Programmatically generate presentations, documents, posts, and sites",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Gamma connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: POST /v1.0/generations (generate content), POST /v1.0/create-from-template (remix from template), GET /v1.0/themes (list themes), GET /v1.0/folders (list folders). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("gamma", "/v1.0/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"gebruder-weiss":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Gebrüder Weiss",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-gebruder-weiss.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Book shipments, get rates, track packages, and generate labels",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Gebrüder Weiss connector via the proxy pattern to perform common tasks: POST /freightPrices/list (get rates), GET /services/list (list carrier services), POST /queries (create bookings and generate labels), GET /bookings/{reference} (track shipments). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 auth injection — prefer using: connectors.proxy("gebruder-weiss", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},gem:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Gem",visibility:"beta",vertical:["ats"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-gem.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Access and manage team data via RESTful API with API key auth.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Gem connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated REST API requests. Common endpoints: GET /v0/users to list users, GET /v0/users/{id} to get user details, POST /v0/users to create a new user, PUT /v0/users/{id} to update a user, DELETE /v0/users/{id} to delete a user. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection in headers. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("gem", "/v0/users"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"@gem.co/api",package_version:"latest"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"ghost-content":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Ghost",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-ghost-content.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Fetch public posts, pages, tags, authors, tiers, and settings.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Ghost Content connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /posts/ to browse posts; GET /posts/{id}/ to fetch a post by ID; GET /tags/ to list tags. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("ghost-content", "/posts/"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"@tryghost/content-api",package_version:"latest"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},github:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"GitHub",visibility:"ga",vertical:["developer-tools","ticketing"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-github.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",connectionCheckFrequency:82800,description:"Connect to GitHub to manage repositories, issues, pull requests, and more.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the GitHub connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /repos/{owner}/{repo} to get a repository, GET /repos/{owner}/{repo}/issues to list issues, GET /repos/{owner}/{repo}/pulls to list pull requests, GET /user/repos to list authenticated user repositories. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("github", "/repos/{owner}/{repo}"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"@octokit/rest",package_version:"21.1.1"}]}},links:{webUrl:"https://github.com",apiDocsUrl:"https://docs.github.com/en/rest"},integrationKeys:{nango:"github"}}},"github-source-control":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"GitHub",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-github-source-control.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",connectionCheckFrequency:82800,description:"Access repositories, issues, pull requests, and authorizations.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:"",packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},gitlab:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"GitLab",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools","ticketing"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-gitlab.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to GitLab to manage projects, issues, merge requests, and more.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use the GitLab connector via the proxy pattern, you can leverage common API endpoints such as: GET /projects, GET /projects/:id/issues, GET /projects/:id/merge_requests, POST /projects/:id/issues, and GET /user (or /oauth/userinfo). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh. Use connectors.proxy("gitlab", "/path") to make calls. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""},integrationKeys:{nango:"gitlab"}}},"gitlab-source-control":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"GitLab",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools","ticketing"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-gitlab-source-control.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access projects, repositories, issues, and user data via OAuth2.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:"",packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},glyphic:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Glyphic",visibility:"beta",vertical:["communication"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-glyphic.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Access call recordings, transcripts, and deal insights via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Glyphic connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /v1/test/ping to verify connectivity; GET /calls to list call recordings; GET /calls/{id}/transcript to fetch a call transcript. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("glyphic", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},gong:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Gong",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["communication","streaming"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-gong.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage calls, transcripts, users, CRM data, and Engage flows via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Gong connector via the proxy pattern to interact with Gong’s API endpoints. Common useful endpoints include: GET /v2/users, GET /v2/calls/{id}/transcript, POST /v2/calls (upload a call), POST /v2/flows to list Engage flows, POST /v2/crm/integrations (register CRM integration). Remember that requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 authentication injection. Use connectors.proxy("gong", "/v2/…") to make requests. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"gong-oauth":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Gong",visibility:"beta",vertical:["communication","streaming"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-gong-oauth.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access Gong APIs using OAuth2 with automatic token injection and refresh.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use this connector, call common endpoints such as GET /v2/flows (list Engage flows), GET /v2/flows/folders (list flow folders), POST /v2/flows/prospects/assign (assign prospects to a flow), POST /v2/flows/prospects/unassign-flows-by-crm-id (unassign by CRM ID), and POST /oauth2/generate-customer-token (exchange code or refresh token). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection — use connectors.proxy("gong-oauth", "/path"). Prefer using: connectors.proxy("gong-oauth", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},google:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Google",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["communication","developer-tools","social-media"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-google.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access Google APIs using OAuth2 with automatic token handling.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Google connector via the proxy pattern. Common endpoints include: GET /drive/v3/files for listing Drive files; POST /oauth2/v4/token to exchange or refresh tokens; GET /oauth2/v3/userinfo to fetch user profile info. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection—use connectors.proxy("google", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"google-calendar":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Google Calendar",visibility:"ga",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-google-calendar.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Retrieve, create, update, and manage calendars and events.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Google Calendar connector via the proxy pattern by calling connectors.proxy("google-calendar", "/path")—requests are automatically authenticated with OAuth2 tokens injected and refreshed by the SDK. Commonly useful API endpoints include: GET /calendars/{calendarId}/events, POST /calendars/{calendarId}/events, PATCH /calendars/{calendarId}/events/{eventId}, GET /users/me/calendarList, POST /calendars/{calendarId}/acl. Note that the proxy returns a raw response object—use .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""},integrationKeys:{nango:"google-calendar"}}},"google-docs":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Google Docs",visibility:"ga",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-google-docs.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Google Docs to create, read, and update documents.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use the Google Docs connector, call common REST endpoints such as POST /v1/documents (create a blank document), GET /v1/documents/{documentId} (retrieve a document), and POST /v1/documents/{documentId}:batchUpdate (apply updates). You can also use POST /v1/documents/{documentId}:batchUpdate for rich editing operations. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refreshing — simply use connectors.proxy("google-docs", "/v1/documents/{path}"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""},integrationKeys:{nango:"google-docs"}}},"google-drive":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Google Drive",visibility:"ga",vertical:["wiki","file-storage"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-google-drive.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Google Drive to manage files and documents.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Google Drive connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /drive/v3/files to list files, GET /drive/v3/files/{fileId} to get file metadata, POST /upload/drive/v3/files to upload files. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection and refresh. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("google-drive", "/drive/v3/files"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"googleapis",package_version:"148.0.0"}]}},links:{webUrl:"https://drive.google.com",apiDocsUrl:"https://developers.google.com/drive"},integrationKeys:{nango:"google-drive"}}},"google-mail":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Gmail",visibility:"ga",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-google-mail.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage messages, drafts, labels, threads, and more via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Gmail connector via the proxy pattern: you can call endpoints like GET /gmail/v1/users/me/messages (list messages), GET /gmail/v1/users/me/messages/{messageId} (get a message), POST /gmail/v1/users/me/messages/send (send a message), GET /gmail/v1/users/me/labels (list labels), POST /gmail/v1/users/me/drafts (create a draft). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("google-mail","/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""},integrationKeys:{nango:"google-mail"}}},"google-play":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Google Play",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-google-play.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage app publishing, purchases, and subscriptions via OAuth2.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Google Play connector via the proxy pattern. Common endpoints include POST /androidpublisher/v3/applications/{packageName}/edits (insert edit), POST /androidpublisher/v3/applications/{packageName}/edits/{editId}:commit (commit edit), GET /androidpublisher/v3/applications/{packageName}/purchases/subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/tokens/{token} (check subscription), POST /androidpublisher/v3/applications/{packageName}/orders/{orderId}:refund (refund order), and GET /androidpublisher/v3/applications/{packageName}/reviews (list reviews) ([developers.google.com](https://developers.google.com/android-publisher/api-ref/rest?utm_source=openai)). Remember that requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection — use: connectors.proxy("google-play", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"google-sheet":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Google Sheets",visibility:"ga",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-google-sheet.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Read, write, and modify spreadsheet data via REST API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use the Google Sheets connector via the proxy pattern, you can call common endpoints like: POST /v4/spreadsheets (create spreadsheet), GET /v4/spreadsheets/{spreadsheetId} (get spreadsheet), POST /v4/spreadsheets/{spreadsheetId}:batchUpdate (apply updates), POST /v4/spreadsheets/{spreadsheetId}/values/{range}:append (append values), GET /v4/spreadsheets/{spreadsheetId}/values:batchGet (retrieve multiple ranges). Use connectors.proxy("google-sheet", "/v4/spreadsheets/{spreadsheetId}/values/{range}:append") to make requests — authentication and token refresh are handled automatically. Prefer using connectors.proxy("google-sheet", "/path") for all calls. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""},integrationKeys:{nango:"google-sheet"}}},"google-slides":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Google Slides",visibility:"ga",vertical:["other"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-google-slides.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Google Slides to create and manage presentations.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Google Slides connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Under the hood this connector uses Google Drive OAuth, so all requests go through the Drive API. Common endpoints: GET /drive/v3/files?q=mimeType%3D%27application/vnd.google-apps.presentation%27 to list presentations, GET /drive/v3/files/{fileId} to get presentation metadata, GET /drive/v3/files/{fileId}/export?mimeType=application/pdf to export a presentation. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection and refresh. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("google-slides", "/drive/v3/files?q=mimeType%3D%27application/vnd.google-apps.presentation%27"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"googleapis",package_version:"148.0.0"}]}},links:{webUrl:"https://slides.google.com",apiDocsUrl:"https://developers.google.com/slides"},integrationKeys:{nango:"google-slides"}}},gorgias:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Gorgias",visibility:"beta",vertical:["commerce"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-gorgias.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage tickets, messages, customers via RESTful OAuth2 API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use the Gorgias connector via the proxy pattern, common API endpoints include: GET /api/tickets (list tickets), POST /api/tickets (create ticket), GET /api/tickets/{ticket_id}/messages (list ticket messages), POST /-/messages or /api/customers (create or update customers). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 authentication, so use: connectors.proxy("gorgias", "/path"). The proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},grafana:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Grafana",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-grafana.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage dashboards, folders, data sources, and annotations via its HTTP API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Grafana connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints include: GET /api/dashboards/uid/:uid to retrieve a dashboard; POST /api/dashboards/db to create or update a dashboard; POST /api/folders to create a folder; GET /api/datasources to list data sources; POST /api/annotations to create an annotation. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection into headers. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("grafana", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},grain:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Grain",visibility:"beta",vertical:["streaming","communication"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-grain.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access and manage your Grain meeting data via OAuth2.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Grain connector via the proxy pattern to access meeting data endpoints. Common useful endpoints include:\n- GET /_/public-api/me  (retrieve authenticated user info)\n- GET /_/public-api/meetings (list meetings)\n- GET /_/public-api/meetings/{meetingId} (get meeting details)\nRequests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("grain", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},granola:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Granola",visibility:"beta",vertical:["wiki"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-granola.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Access and manage meeting notes and metadata via its Enterprise API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Granola connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /notes to list meeting notes, GET /notes/{id} to retrieve a specific note, POST /notes/{id}/enhance or similar to trigger enhancement (depending on API capabilities), GET /folders or /notes?folder={folder_id} to filter by folder. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection — use connectors.proxy("granola", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},greenhouse:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!0,metadata:{displayName:"Greenhouse",visibility:"beta",vertical:["ats"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-greenhouse.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access and manipulate recruiting data via the Harvest v3 API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use Greenhouse (OAuth) via the proxy pattern to call common endpoints such as GET /v3/applications, GET /v3/candidates, GET /v3/jobs, POST /v3/applications, and PATCH /v3/candidates. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("greenhouse", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"greenhouse-harvest-partner":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Greenhouse Harvest",visibility:"beta",vertical:["ats"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-greenhouse-harvest-partner.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access and manage recruiting data via OAuth2.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Greenhouse Harvest Partner connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /v3/users to list users; GET /v3/candidates to get candidate data; GET /v3/jobs to list job openings. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("greenhouse-harvest-partner", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""},integrationKeys:{nango:"greenhouse-harvest-partner"}}},"greenhouse-ingestion":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Greenhouse (Ingestion API)",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["ats"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-greenhouse-ingestion.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Submit and retrieve candidate/prospect data.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Greenhouse Ingestion API connector via the proxy pattern and target common endpoints such as GET /v1/partner/candidates, POST /v1/partner/candidates, GET /v1/partner/current_user, GET /v1/partner/jobs, and GET /v1/partner/prospect_pools. All requests are proxied through the SDK with OAuth2 credentials injected and refreshed automatically. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("greenhouse-ingestion", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},grist:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Grist",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-grist.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Connect to Grist to manage documents, tables, records, and SQL queries.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Grist connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /docs/{docId} (get document metadata), POST /docs (create document), GET /docs/{docId}/download (download document content as SQLite), POST /workspaces/{workspaceId}/docs (create empty document). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("grist", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"grist-api",package_version:"latest"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},gumroad:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Gumroad",visibility:"beta",vertical:["commerce"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-gumroad.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Retrieve products, sales, subscribers, and verify licenses.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Gumroad connector via the proxy pattern: three common endpoints are GET /products, GET /sales, POST /licenses/verify (also GET /sales/:id, GET /subscribers). The OAuth token is automatically injected and refreshed. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("gumroad", "/products") or connectors.proxy("gumroad", "/sales"), etc. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},gusto:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Gusto",visibility:"beta",vertical:["hris"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-gusto.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage embedded payroll operations, companies, locations, and employees.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Gusto connector via the proxy pattern for common payroll integration tasks. Among the most useful API endpoints are: POST /v1/partner_managed_companies (create a company), GET /v1/companies/{company_id} (retrieve company info), POST /v1/companies/{company_id}/locations (add a location), GET /v1/locations/{location_id} (fetch location details), and POST /oauth/token (exchange tokens). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 authentication injection — simply call connectors.proxy("gusto", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"gusto-demo":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Gusto (Demo)",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-gusto-demo.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access and manage demo payroll, company, and employee data.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Gusto (Demo) connector via the proxy pattern. Common API endpoints include:\n- POST /v1/partner_managed_companies (create demo company)\n- POST /v1/partner_managed_companies/{company_uuid}/accept_terms_of_service (accept TOS)\n- POST /v1/companies/{company_uuid}/employees (create employee)\n- GET /v1/companies/{company_uuid}/employees (list employees)\n- POST /oauth/token (exchange authorization or refresh token) ([docs.gusto.com](https://docs.gusto.com/embedded-payroll/v2024-03-01/docs/getting-started?utm_source=openai))\nRequests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("gusto-demo", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},harvest:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Harvest",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-harvest.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage time entries, tasks, clients, projects, and more.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To interact with Harvest’s API (v2) via the proxy pattern, use common endpoints such as: GET /v2/time_entries, POST /v2/time_entries, PATCH /v2/time_entries/{TIME_ENTRY_ID}, GET /v2/projects, GET /v2/clients. Remember that requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 access token injection — prefer using: connectors.proxy("harvest", "/v2/time_entries"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"health-gorilla":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Health Gorilla",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-health-gorilla.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Retrieve and manage clinical data via FHIR-based secure APIs.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Health Gorilla connector via the proxy pattern to access key FHIR endpoints. Common useful endpoints include: GET /fhir/R4/DocumentReference/$p360-retrieve (Patient360 retrieval), GET /fhir/R4/Patient/$everything (comprehensive patient record), POST /fhir/R4/Requisition (lab order submission), GET /fhir/R4/Subscription (list subscriptions), and GET /oauth/userinfo (retrieve user info). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 auth injection; simply call connectors.proxy("health-gorilla", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"helpscout-mailbox":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Help Scout Mailbox",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-helpscout-mailbox.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage conversations, mailboxes, threads, users, and more.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Help Scout Mailbox connector via the proxy pattern to perform API operations. Commonly used endpoints include: GET /v2/conversations (list conversations), GET /v2/mailboxes/{mailboxId} (get mailbox details), GET /v2/conversations/{conversationId}/threads (list conversation threads), GET /v2/users/{userId} (get user), and GET /v2/customers (list customers). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("helpscout-mailbox", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},hex:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Hex",visibility:"alpha",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-hex.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Programmatically list, run, and manage projects in your Hex workspace.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Hex connector via the proxy pattern by calling connectors.proxy("hex", "/path"). Common endpoints include: GET /projects (list projects), POST /projects/{project_id}/runs (trigger a run), GET /projects/{project_id}/runs (list or check status), PATCH /data-connections/{id} (rotate data connection credentials), and DELETE /projects/{project_id}/runs/{run_id} (cancel a run). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API-key-based authentication injected in headers. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},heygen:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"HeyGen",visibility:"beta",vertical:["streaming"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-heygen.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Generate AI-based videos, translate or manage avatars and voices.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the HeyGen connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: POST /v1/video_agent/generate , POST /v2/video/generate , GET /v1/video_status.get , GET /v2/avatars , GET /v2/voices . All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("heygen", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},heyreach:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"HeyReach",visibility:"beta",vertical:["social-media"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-heyreach.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage LinkedIn outreach campaigns, leads, conversations, and statistics.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the HeyReach connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: POST /public/auth/CheckApiKey to validate your API key, POST /public/campaigns/GetAll to list campaigns, POST /public/inbox/GetConversations to fetch conversation threads, POST /public/campaigns/AddLeadsToCampaign (or V2) to add leads to a campaign. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("heyreach", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},highlevel:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"HighLevel",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-highlevel.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access CRM, messaging, calendar, payments, and webhook APIs.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the HighLevel connector via the proxy pattern. Common endpoints include GET /contacts/, POST /contacts/, GET /conversations/, POST /appointments/, GET /payments/. The SDK handles OAuth2 authentication and token refresh automatically, so you don’t need to manage auth headers. Prefer using connectors.proxy("highlevel", "/path") in your code. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"highlevel-white-label":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"HighLevel (White Label)",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-highlevel-white-label.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access CRM data and workflows via OAuth2.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the HighLevel (White Label) connector via the proxy pattern. Common endpoints include: GET /contacts, POST /contacts/search, GET /appointments, POST /conversations/send, GET /opportunities. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection—use connectors.proxy("highlevel-white-label", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},holded:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Holded",visibility:"beta",vertical:["accounting","crm"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-holded.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage billing, CRM, projects, team, and accounting data.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Holded connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /contacts to list contacts, POST /contacts to create a contact, GET /documents to list documents, POST /documents to create a document. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("holded", "/contacts") or connectors.proxy("holded", "/documents"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},hover:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Hover",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-hover.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Automate property capture workflows and retrieve 3D measurement data.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use the Hover connector via the proxy pattern, leverage its key endpoints: POST /api/v1/blueprints (upload blueprints), POST /api/v1/jobs (create a job), GET /api/v3/jobs (list jobs), GET /api/v3/jobs/{job_id} (get job details), GET /api/v2/jobs/{job_id}/measurements.json or V3 artifacts (retrieve measurement data). All requests are automatically authenticated and proxied through the SDK—use connectors.proxy("hover", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},hubspot:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"HubSpot",visibility:"ga",vertical:["ticketing","crm"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-hubspot.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage contacts, companies, deals, tickets, and marketing campaigns.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the HubSpot connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /crm/v3/objects/contacts to list contacts, GET /crm/v3/objects/companies to list companies, GET /crm/v3/objects/deals to list deals, GET /crm/v3/objects/tickets to list tickets. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("hubspot", "/crm/v3/objects/contacts"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"@hubspot/api-client",package_version:"12.0.0"}]}},links:{webUrl:"https://www.hubspot.com",apiDocsUrl:"https://developers.hubspot.com/docs/api/overview"}}},icypeas:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Icypeas",visibility:"beta",vertical:["crm"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-icypeas.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Connect to Icypeas to find and verify emails and search leads.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Icypeas connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: POST /find-people to search leads, POST /email-verification to verify an email, POST /email-search or /domain-search for searching emails or domains. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection via headers. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("icypeas", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"incident-io":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Incident.io",visibility:"beta",vertical:["ticketing"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-incident-io.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Create, list, and manage incidents programmatically.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the incident.io connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: POST /v1/incidents (create an incident), GET /v2/incidents (list incidents), GET /v2/incidents/{id} (get incident by ID), GET /v1/severities (list severities), GET /v1/incident_statuses (list statuses). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection — prefer using: connectors.proxy("incident-io", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},instagram:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Instagram",visibility:"ga",vertical:["social-media"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-instagram.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access business/creator media, profile, publishing, and insights",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Instagram connector via the proxy pattern for common tasks. Typical useful endpoints include: GET /me?fields=id,username,account_type (to fetch account info); GET /{ig-user-id}/media?fields=id,caption,media_url,permalink (to list media); POST /{ig-user-id}/media (to create a media container); POST /{ig-user-id}/media_publish (to publish media); GET /{ig-user-id}/insights?metric=impressions,reach (to fetch insights). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection — use connectors.proxy("instagram", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},instantly:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Instantly",visibility:"beta",vertical:["communication"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-instantly.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage cold-email campaigns, accounts, and leads via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Instantly connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /v2/campaigns to list campaigns; GET /v2/campaigns/{campaign_id}/leads to list leads; POST /v2/campaigns to create a campaign. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic bearer-token auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("instantly", "/v2/campaigns"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},intercom:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Intercom",visibility:"beta",vertical:["ticketing"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-intercom.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage users, companies, and conversations in Intercom",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Intercom connector via the proxy pattern by calling connectors.proxy("intercom", "/path"). Most useful API endpoints include: GET /users (list users), POST /users (create or update user), GET /companies (list companies), GET /conversations (list conversations), GET /me (retrieve authenticated admin/app info). Your requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection and refreshing. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},intuit:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Intuit",visibility:"beta",vertical:["accounting"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-intuit.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Intuit to access its API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Intuit connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection and refresh. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("intuit", "/endpoint"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},ironclad:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Ironclad",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-ironclad.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Launch workflows, manage contracts, and access entity records",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Ironclad connector via the proxy pattern with automatic OAuth token handling. Common endpoints include:\n• GET /workflows – list workflows or view workflow schemas ([developer.ironcladapp.com](https://developer.ironcladapp.com/docs/entity-references-in-workflows-records?utm_source=openai))\n• POST /workflows – launch a workflow synchronously or asynchronously ([developer.ironcladapp.com](https://developer.ironcladapp.com/docs/launch-a-workflow?utm_source=openai))\n• POST /records – create a new record in the repository ([developer.ironcladapp.com](https://developer.ironcladapp.com/docs/create-a-record-1?utm_source=openai))\n• GET /records – retrieve records (e.g., by entity filter) ([developer.ironcladapp.com](https://developer.ironcladapp.com/docs/entity-references-in-workflows-records?utm_source=openai))\n• GET /workflows/{workflowId}?form=launch – retrieve workflow launch form schema ([developer.ironcladapp.com](https://developer.ironcladapp.com/docs/launch-a-workflow?utm_source=openai))\nMake requests using connectors.proxy("ironclad", "/path"). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},itglue:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"IT Glue",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-itglue.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage documentation, configurations, passwords and flexible assets.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the IT Glue connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /organizations to list organizations, GET /configurations/{id} to retrieve a configuration, POST /flexible_assets to create a flexible asset, PATCH /flexible_assets/{id} to update, DELETE /passwords/{id} to delete a password. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("itglue", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},jazzhr:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"JazzHR",visibility:"beta",vertical:["hris"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-jazzhr.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage recruiting resources like applicants, jobs, contacts, and more.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the JazzHR connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /api/v1/applicants to list applicants, GET /api/v1/jobs to retrieve jobs, POST /api/v1/applicants to create an applicant, GET /api/v1/contacts to list contacts. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection via headers. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("jazzhr", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},jira:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Jira",visibility:"ga",vertical:["ticketing"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-jira.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Perform issue, project, webhook, and board operations via REST APIs.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use the Jira connector via the proxy pattern, first retrieve your Atlassian cloud ID by calling GET /oauth/token/accessible-resources (returns an array of {id, url, name}). Then use cloud-scoped paths that include the /ex/jira/{cloudId} prefix: GET /ex/jira/{cloudId}/rest/api/3/issue/{issueIdOrKey}, POST /ex/jira/{cloudId}/rest/api/3/issue, GET /ex/jira/{cloudId}/rest/api/3/project, POST /ex/jira/{cloudId}/rest/api/3/webhook. Example: connectors.proxy("jira", "/ex/jira/{cloudId}/rest/api/3/issue/TEST-1"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"jira-data-center":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Jira Data Center",visibility:"beta",vertical:["ticketing"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-jira-data-center.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage issues, projects, users, workflows, and more via REST APIs.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Jira Data Center OAuth2 connector via the proxy pattern. Common useful endpoints include GET /issue/{issueIdOrKey}, POST /issue, GET /project, PUT /issue/{issueIdOrKey}, and GET /user?username={username}. All requests should be sent via connectors.proxy("jira-data-center", "/issue/{issueIdOrKey}"), which handles automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},jobadder:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Jobadder",visibility:"beta",vertical:["hris"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-jobadder.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage jobs, candidates, placements, and action buttons via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the JobAdder connector via the proxy pattern: automatic OAuth tokens are injected and refreshed. Common endpoints include:\n• GET /candidates/{CANDIDATE_ID} (retrieve a candidate)\n• POST /partners/actions/{type} (create a partner action button)\n• GET /partners/actions (list partner action buttons)\n• PUT /partners/actions/{actionId}/{actionType}/{recordId}/{actionStage} (update action stage)\n• GET /candidates?partnerAction.stage=submitted (fetch candidates with submitted partner actions)\nAlways use connectors.proxy("jobadder", "/path") to make requests through the SDK; authentication is handled automatically. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},jobber:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Jobber",visibility:"beta",vertical:["crm","accounting"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-jobber.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage clients, jobs, quotes, invoices, and scheduling via GraphQL API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use the Jobber connector, invoke the proxy using connectors.proxy("jobber", "/graphql") for all operations—the OAuth token is injected and refreshed automatically. Commonly used operations (via GraphQL POST to /graphql) include: POST /graphql with query { clients { id name } } to list clients, POST /graphql with mutation to create a client, POST /graphql with mutation to create a job or quote, POST /graphql with mutation to archive a client. Use connectors.proxy("jobber", "/graphql"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},jobvite:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Jobvite",visibility:"beta",vertical:["ats"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-jobvite.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Connect to Jobvite to manage recruiting data via API with key-based auth.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Jobvite connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /v2/jobFeed to retrieve job listings, GET /v2/candidates to list candidates, POST /v2/requisition to create a job requisition, GET /v2/requisition/{id} to fetch a requisition. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("jobvite", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},jotform:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Jotform",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-jotform.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Connect to Jotform to manage forms, submissions, questions, and properties.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Jotform connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /user to retrieve user info, GET /form/{formId} to get form details, POST /form/{formId}/questions to add questions, GET /form/{formId}/properties to fetch form properties, POST /form/{formId}/properties to update. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("jotform", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"jotform",package_version:"1.0.1"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},jumpcloud:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"JumpCloud",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-jumpcloud.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage users, systems, directories, and applications via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the JumpCloud connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /systems to list systems, GET /users to list users, POST /applications/{application_id}/import/jobs to trigger user imports; additionally GET /active_directories (v2) and POST /active_directories to manage directories. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("jumpcloud", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"juniper-mist":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Juniper Mist",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-juniper-mist.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Automate network and assurance management via RESTful APIs.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Juniper Mist connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /api/v1/self, GET /api/v1/orgs/{org_id}/sites, GET /api/v1/sites/{site_id}/stats/devices/{device_id}, POST /api/v1/orgs/{org_id}/networktemplates, PUT /api/v1/sites/{site_id}/wlans/{wlan_id}. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API-token injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("juniper-mist", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},justworks:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Justworks",visibility:"beta",vertical:["hris"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-justworks.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access HR, payroll, company, and webhook data securely.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Justworks connector via the proxy pattern to call key endpoints such as: GET /company, GET /members, POST /webhooks, and POST /oauth/revoke. Always use connectors.proxy("justworks", "/v1/path") so that OAuth2 tokens are injected and refreshed automatically. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},kandji:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Kandji",visibility:"beta",vertical:["ticketing"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-kandji.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage Apple devices: info, applications, blueprints, and profiles",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Kandji connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API access. Common endpoints: GET /devices to list devices, GET /devices/{device_id} to get device details, GET /devices/{device_id}/apps to list installed applications, GET /blueprints to list blueprints, GET /profiles or scripts endpoints. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("kandji", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},keap:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Keap",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-keap.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access CRM data and manage contacts, payments, and business profiles.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Keap connector via the proxy pattern to make API calls. Common endpoints include: GET /contacts, GET /contacts/{contact_id}, POST /contacts, POST /payments, GET /business/profile. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("keap", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},kintone:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Kintone",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-kintone.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Perform operations on apps, records, files, and spaces via REST APIs.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use the Kintone connector via the proxy pattern, you can invoke common REST endpoints—e.g., GET /k/v1/records.json to retrieve multiple records, POST /k/v1/record.json to add a record, PUT /k/v1/records.json to update multiple records, GET /k/v1/app.json to fetch app metadata, and POST /k/v1/file.json to upload a file—using connectors.proxy("kintone", "/path"). Requests are proxied through the SDK, which automatically injects and refreshes OAuth tokens. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"kintone-user-api":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Kintone User API",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-kintone-user-api.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage user-related data within a Kintone subdomain.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Kintone User API connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /v1/user.json to retrieve a user, GET /v1/users.json to list users, POST /v1/user.json to create a user, PUT /v1/user.json to update a user. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("kintone-user-api", "/v1/user.json"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"klaviyo-oauth":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Klaviyo",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-klaviyo-oauth.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Call Klaviyo’s server-side APIs with secure OAuth tokens.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Klaviyo OAuth connector via the proxy pattern to access key endpoints. Commonly used endpoints include: GET /oauth/authorize to obtain user authorization, POST /oauth/token to retrieve or refresh access tokens, and POST /oauth/revoke to revoke tokens. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection — implement calls using connectors.proxy("klaviyo-oauth", "/oauth/token") or similar paths. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("klaviyo-oauth", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},klipfolio:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Klipfolio",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-klipfolio.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage data sources, dashboards, Klips, and users via its REST API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Klipfolio connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints include: GET /api/1.0/datasources to list data sources, POST /api/1.0/datasources to create a data source, GET /api/1.0/dashboards to list dashboards, DELETE /api/1.0/datasources/{id} to delete a data source. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("klipfolio", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},knowbe4:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"KnowBe4",visibility:"beta",vertical:["ticketing"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-knowbe4.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Retrieve phishing, training, user, and group data via its REST API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the KnowBe4 connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API access. Common endpoints include: GET /v1/users to list users, GET /v1/groups to list groups, GET /v1/phishing/campaigns/{campaign_id} for phishing campaign details, GET /v1/training/campaigns to list training campaigns, GET /v1/groups/{group_id}/members to list members. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key authentication. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("knowbe4", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},kustomer:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Kustomer",visibility:"beta",vertical:["crm"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-kustomer.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage customer conversations, messages, apps, and more.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Kustomer connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /v1/conversations to list conversations, POST /v1/conversations to create a conversation, GET /v1/messages to list messages, and POST /v1/apps/available to register an app. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection via headers. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("kustomer", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},lagrowthmachine:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"La Growth Machine",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-lagrowthmachine.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Automate lead import, campaign management, and audience workflows.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the La Growth Machine connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: POST /flow/leads to import leads, GET /flow/leads to list leads, POST /flow/campaigns to start a campaign, GET /flow/audiences to retrieve audiences. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("lagrowthmachine", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},lattice:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Lattice",visibility:"beta",vertical:["hris"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-lattice.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Access HR data like users, goals, feedback, reviews via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Lattice connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /v1/users to list users, GET /v1/goals to fetch goals, GET /v1/reviews to retrieve reviews. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection into headers. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("lattice", "/v1/users"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},leadmagic:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"LeadMagic",visibility:"beta",vertical:["crm"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-leadmagic.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Enrich B2B leads with emails, mobile numbers, and company data",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the LeadMagic connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: POST /v1/people/email-validation to verify emails, POST /v1/people/email-finder to locate work emails, POST /v1/people/mobile-finder to obtain mobile numbers, GET /v1/credits to check credit balance, GET /v1/analytics/dashboard for usage insights. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("leadmagic", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},lever:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Lever",visibility:"beta",vertical:["ats"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-lever.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage recruiting data: candidates, opportunities, and requisitions",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Lever connector via the proxy pattern. Common useful endpoints include: GET /contacts/:contact, PUT /contacts/:contact, GET /opportunities, POST /requisition_fields, GET /stages. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection—use connectors.proxy("lever", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"lever-sandbox":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Lever (Sandbox)",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["other"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-lever-sandbox.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access and manage ATS data via Lever’s sandbox API",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use this connector to call common Lever sandbox endpoints such as GET /postings, GET /contacts/:contact, PUT /contacts/:contact, GET /opportunities/:opportunity/applications, and GET /archive_reasons. Invoke requests via the proxy pattern: use connectors.proxy("lever-sandbox", "/postings") or other paths. Authentication is handled automatically—OAuth tokens are injected and refreshed by the SDK. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},linear:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Linear",visibility:"ga",vertical:["ticketing"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-linear.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",connectionCheckFrequency:2592e3,description:"Query issues, projects, cycles, and manage issue tracking via GraphQL.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Linear connector via the proxy pattern to interact with Linear’s GraphQL API. Common API operations include: (1) GET authenticated user details (query viewer { id name email }), (2) GET list of issues (query issues { nodes { id title } }), (3) CREATE an issue (mutation issueCreate), (4) UPDATE an issue (mutation issueUpdate), and (5) LIST projects (query projects { nodes { id name } }). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection—use connectors.proxy("linear", "/graphql", { query: "..." }). Prefer using: connectors.proxy("linear", "/graphql"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},linkedin:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"LinkedIn",visibility:"beta",vertical:["ats","social-media"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-linkedin.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to LinkedIn to access member data, profiles, and social APIs.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use the LinkedIn connector, call common endpoints like GET /v2/me (retrieve member profile), GET /v2/emailAddress?q=members (get member email), GET /rest/people/{personId} (fetch profile details), POST /rest/shares (create a post), and GET /rest/organizations/{organizationId}?projection=... (fetch organization data). All requests go through the SDK and automatically inject OAuth2 tokens. Use connectors.proxy("linkedin", "/path") to proxy calls. Remember: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},linkhut:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"LinkHut",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-linkhut.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to LinkHut to manage and organize your bookmarks via OAuth2.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the LinkHut connector via the proxy pattern. Common endpoints include: GET /posts/get, GET /tags/get, POST /oauth/token, GET /posts/all, GET /tags/list. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection—use connectors.proxy("linkhut", "/path") to make calls. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"loop-returns":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Loop Returns",visibility:"beta",vertical:["commerce"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-loop-returns.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage ecommerce return workflows including creating and reviewing returns.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Loop Returns connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API calls. Common endpoints include: GET /warehouse/return/list (detailed return list), GET /warehouse/return/details (return details), POST /draft-returns (initialize draft return), POST /draft-returns/{id}/submit (submit draft return), POST /warehouse/return/{action} for actions like cancel or process. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("loop-returns", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"loops-so":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Loops.so",visibility:"beta",vertical:["communication"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-loops-so.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage contacts, send events, and transactional emails.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Loops.so connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /v1/api-key to test API key validity; POST /v1/contacts to create a contact; POST /v1/events to send an event; POST /v1/transactional-email to send transactional email. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("loops-so", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"loops",package_version:"latest"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},luma:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Luma",visibility:"beta",vertical:["ticketing"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-luma.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Programmatically manage calendars, events, registrations and analytics.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Luma connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /user to retrieve current user, POST /event/create to create an event, POST /user/audience/import to import audience members. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("luma", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},lumos:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Lumos",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-lumos.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Connect to Lumos to interact with the Lumos Connector API via proxy.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Lumos connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /validate_credentials to validate authentication, GET /accounts to list accounts, POST /entitlements to assign entitlements, PATCH /resources to update resources. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("lumos", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},mailchimp:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Mailchimp",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-mailchimp.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage audiences, campaigns, and ecommerce resources.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Mailchimp connector via the proxy pattern for common actions like GET /3.0/lists (retrieve audience lists), POST /3.0/lists/{list_id}/members (add a subscriber), GET /3.0/lists/{list_id}/members/{subscriber_hash} (get a subscriber), POST /3.0/ecommerce/stores/{store_id}/orders (create an order), PATCH /3.0/ecommerce/stores/{store_id}/orders/{order_id} (update an order). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection. Use connectors.proxy("mailchimp", "/path") for making calls. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},make:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Make",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-make.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage scenarios, teams, data stores, and more via REST API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Make (Integromat) connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /v1/scenarios to list scenarios, GET /v1/teams to list teams, GET /v1/dataStores to retrieve data stores, POST /v1/scenarios to create a scenario. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("make", "/v1/scenarios"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"@makehq/sdk",package_version:"latest"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},manatal:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Manatal",visibility:"beta",vertical:["crm","hris"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-manatal.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Access candidate, job, organization, and webhook data via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Manatal connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /candidates to list candidates, GET /jobs to list jobs, GET /organizations to list organizations, POST /webhooks to create webhooks, GET /webhooks for webhooks settings. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("manatal", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},maximizer:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Maximizer",visibility:"beta",vertical:["crm"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-maximizer.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access CRM data and operations via OAuth2-secured API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Maximizer connector via the proxy pattern to perform authenticated API calls. Common endpoints include: GET /api/Account to list accounts, GET /api/Contact to retrieve contacts, POST /api/Opportunity to create opportunities, PATCH /api/Account/{id} to update an account, DELETE /api/Opportunity/{id} to delete an opportunity. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("maximizer", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"maximizer-on-premise":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Maximizer (On-Premise)",visibility:"beta",vertical:["crm"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-maximizer-on-premise.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access CRM data like cases, contacts, and webhooks.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Maximizer (On-Premise) connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API calls. Common endpoints: GET /ferret/v2/cases to list cases, GET /ferret/v2/contacts to list contacts, POST /Authenticate for token authentication, and Webhooks API endpoints to create webhook subscriptions. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("maximizer-on-premise", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""},integrationKeys:{nango:"maximizer-on-premise"}}},mercury:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Mercury",visibility:"beta",vertical:["accounting"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-mercury.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access accounts, transactions, recipients, ACH, and invoicing.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Mercury OAuth2 connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /api/v1/accounts to list your accounts, GET /api/v1/account/{accountId} to retrieve account details, GET /api/v1/transactions to fetch transaction history, POST /api/v1/invoices to create invoices, and POST /api/v1/ach-payments to initiate ACH payments. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("mercury", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},metabase:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Metabase",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-metabase.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage users, databases, dashboards, and queries via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Metabase connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /api/users to list users, POST /api/database to add a data source, POST /api/dashboard to create dashboards, POST /api/card to create questions (cards), GET /api/collection to fetch collections. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("metabase", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},microsoft:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Microsoft",visibility:"beta",vertical:["communication","developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-microsoft.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access Microsoft 365 services via Microsoft Graph API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Microsoft Graph connector via the proxy pattern. Common endpoints include: GET /me (user profile), GET /users, POST /users (create user), GET /groups, GET /me/messages. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection. To invoke, use connectors.proxy("microsoft", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"microsoft-admin":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Microsoft (Admin)",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["communication","developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-microsoft-admin.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Microsoft (Admin) to manage Microsoft 365/Admin APIs via OAuth2.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Microsoft (Admin) connector via the proxy pattern to call common admin endpoints such as:\n• POST /adminapi/v2.0/{tenantId}/OrganizationConfig\n• POST /adminapi/v2.0/{tenantId}/AcceptedDomain\n• POST /adminapi/v2.0/{tenantId}/Mailbox\n• GET /beta/admin/people/itemInsights (preview)\n• GET /admin/sharepoint/settings?select=isLegacyAuthProtocolsEnabled\nRequests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Use connectors.proxy("microsoft-admin", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"microsoft-fabric":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!0,metadata:{displayName:"Microsoft Fabric",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-microsoft-fabric.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access data engineering, data science, and analytics workloads in Fabric",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'## Mode 1 — SDK Proxy (REST API)\nThis mode is recommended for most use cases. Use the Microsoft Fabric connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated REST API requests.\nThe proxy handles OAuth credentials and routing automatically — no SDK needed.\nCommon endpoints:\n  GET /v1/workspaces — List all workspaces the user has access to.\n  GET /v1/workspaces/{workspaceId}/items — List items in a workspace.\n  GET /v1/workspaces/{workspaceId}/lakehouses — List lakehouses in a workspace.\n  GET /v1/workspaces/{workspaceId}/warehouses — List warehouses in a workspace.\n  POST /v1/workspaces/{workspaceId}/items/{itemId}/jobs/instances?jobType=RunNotebook — Run a notebook.\nPrefer using: connectors.proxy("microsoft-fabric", "/v1/workspaces", { method: "GET" }).\nThe response is a raw Response object, so you need to parse it using the Response.json() method.\n\n## Mode 2 — Rayfin CLI (Microsoft Fabric CLI)\nFor CLI operations against Microsoft Fabric (workspace / item management, deploys, scripted\nflows that the Rayfin CLI already supports), use the CLI proxy wrapper.\n\nUse the SDK helper `connectors.getCliConfig("microsoft-fabric")` to generate the values\nthe Rayfin CLI needs. The helper:\n  - Mints an audience-scoped Replit identity PASETO (via `replit identity create`, with\n    `REPL_IDENTITY` / `WEB_REPL_RENEWAL` as fallbacks).\n  - Looks up the active `microsoft-fabric` connection and encodes the connector name +\n    connection id into the path-based proxy URL.\nSet the returned `config.host` and `config.token` into `RAYFIN_FABRIC_API_URL` and\n`RAYFIN_TOKEN` before invoking the CLI. The server validates the identity, resolves the\nconnection, injects the real Microsoft Fabric OAuth credentials, and proxies the upstream\nrequest. Secrets never leave the server.\n\n```ts\nimport { ReplitConnectors } from "@replit/connectors-sdk";\nimport { execFileSync } from "child_process";\n\nconst connectors = new ReplitConnectors();\nconst config = await connectors.getCliConfig("microsoft-fabric");\nconst args = process.argv.slice(2);\n// execFileSync (argv, not template string) — never pass the joined args\n// through a shell. Rayfin args can contain spaces, quotes, and other\n// metacharacters that a shell would re-interpret before Rayfin sees them.\nconst result = execFileSync("rayfin", args, {\n  encoding: "utf-8",\n  env: {\n    ...process.env,\n    RAYFIN_FABRIC_API_URL: config.host,\n    RAYFIN_TOKEN: config.token,\n  },\n});\n```\n\nNotes on `getCliConfig("microsoft-fabric")`:\n  - `config.host` is the full path-based proxy URL, e.g.\n    `https://connectors.replit.com/api/v2/cli-proxy/microsoft-fabric/<connectionId>`.\n    Routing rides in the URL, so the token does not need to encode the connection id.\n  - `config.token` is the helper-generated Replit identity token. Treat it as opaque:\n    when the SDK can call `replit identity create`, the token is a bare PASETO; when\n    the SDK falls back to `REPL_IDENTITY` / `WEB_REPL_RENEWAL`, it is prefixed (e.g.\n    `repl <paseto>` / `depl <paseto>` / `web <paseto>`) and contains a literal space.\n    Never `echo` it, never interpolate it into a shell command, never assume it is a\n    single space-free word. Always pass it via subprocess `env` (as shown) —\n    `process.env` and `execFileSync` preserve embedded spaces; shell\n    `export RAYFIN_TOKEN=$token` does not.\n  - Requires `@replit/connectors-sdk` with `microsoft-fabric` CLI support. Older\n    SDK versions throw `getCliConfig() is only supported for ...`.\n\nWhen to use each mode:\n  - SDK Proxy: programmatic REST calls from app code (list workspaces / items, run notebooks,\n    read lakehouses / warehouses, etc.).\n  - CLI Proxy: invoking the Rayfin CLI directly from a Repl when an existing CLI workflow,\n    script, or partner integration expects `RAYFIN_FABRIC_API_URL` / `RAYFIN_TOKEN`.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"node-fetch",package_version:"3.3.2",code_snippet:'const response = await connectors.proxy("microsoft-fabric", "/v1/workspaces", { method: "GET" });\nconst data = await response.json();\nconsole.log(data);'}]}},links:{webUrl:"https://app.fabric.microsoft.com",apiDocsUrl:"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/rest/api/fabric/articles/"}}},"microsoft-teams-bot":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Microsoft Teams Bot",visibility:"beta",vertical:["communication"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-microsoft-teams-bot.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Send and receive messages in Teams via the Bot Framework.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Microsoft Teams Bot connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: POST /v3/conversations/{conversationId}/activities to send a message; GET /v3/conversations/{conversationId}/members to list members; POST /v3/conversations to start a new conversation. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("microsoft-teams-bot", "/v3/conversations/{conversationId}/activities"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"@microsoft/teams-ai",package_version:"1.7.4"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""},integrationKeys:{nango:"microsoft-teams-bot"}}},"microsoft-tenant-specific":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Microsoft (Tenant)",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-microsoft-tenant-specific.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Acquire OAuth2 tokens and call Microsoft identity and Graph APIs.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Microsoft (Tenant) connector via the proxy pattern to perform common tenant-level operations such as: GET /v1.0/users, GET /v1.0/groups, POST /v1.0/users, DELETE /v1.0/groups (using Microsoft Graph endpoints). Requests are automatically proxied through the SDK with auth token injection and refresh handled under the hood. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("microsoft-tenant-specific", "/v1.0/<resource>") for all calls. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},mindbody:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Mindbody",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-mindbody.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Access fitness studio data and manage bookings, clients, and webhooks.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Mindbody connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints include: GET /partnergateway/accounts/v1/me to retrieve account info; GET /public/v6/class/classes to list available classes; POST /affiliate/api/v1/locations/{locationId}/classes to book a class; GET /push/api/v1/subscription to fetch webhook subscriptions. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API-Key and auth header injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("mindbody", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"mindbody-api-v6",package_version:"latest"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},minimax:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"MiniMax",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-minimax.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Access multimodal AI for text, speech, video, image, and music",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the MiniMax connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: POST /v1/chat/completions for text generation, POST /v1/audio/synthesis for speech synthesis, POST /v1/video/tasks for creating video generation tasks, GET /v1/video/tasks/{task_id} to check video task status, and POST /v1/files/upload for file handling. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("minimax", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"minimax",package_version:"latest"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},miro:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Miro",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-miro.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Programmatically manage boards, items, teams, and user contexts.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Miro connector via the proxy pattern through connectors.proxy("miro", "/path"). Include common endpoints such as GET /v2/boards to list boards, GET /v2/boards/{BOARD_ID}/items to retrieve board items, POST /v2/boards/{BOARD_ID}/items to create items, PATCH /v2/boards/{BOARD_ID} to update a board, and GET /v2/orgs/{ORG_ID}/teams/{TEAM_ID}/members to list team members. All requests are automatically injected with OAuth tokens and proxied via the SDK. Prefer invoking requests through connectors.proxy("miro", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},missive:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Missive",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-missive.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage conversations, drafts, contacts, and labels via REST API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Missive connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /conversations to list conversations; POST /messages to create or send a message/draft; GET /contacts to list contacts. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("missive", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},mollie:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Mollie",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-mollie.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Mollie to process payments, refunds, and manage orders via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Mollie connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: POST /v2/payments to create a payment, GET /v2/payments/{id} to retrieve payment status, POST /v2/payments/{id}/refunds to refund a payment, POST /v2/orders to create an order, and POST /v2/orders/{id}/shipments to notify shipment. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("mollie", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"@mollie/api-client",package_version:"latest"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"momentum-io":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Momentum.io",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-momentum-io.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Automate sales intelligence and meeting workflows.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Momentum.io connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /v1/meetings to fetch meetings, GET /v1/meetings/{id} to retrieve a meeting, POST /v1/meetings to create a meeting (if supported). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("momentum-io", "/v1/meetings"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"@nangohq/node",package_version:"latest"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},monday:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Monday",visibility:"alpha",vertical:["ticketing"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-monday.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Query and manipulate boards, items, users, and more via GraphQL API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Monday connector via the proxy pattern to interact with the Monday.com GraphQL API. Common endpoints include: POST /v2 to run queries (e.g., fetch boards), POST /v2 to create items, and POST /v2 to update column values. Always send GraphQL queries or mutations as POST to /v2, including query and optional variables in the JSON body. Use connectors.proxy("monday", "/v2") — requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""},integrationKeys:{nango:"monday"}}},mural:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Mural",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-mural.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Mural to manage workspaces, rooms, and murals via REST API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Mural connector via the proxy pattern to call key endpoints such as: GET /workspaces (to list user workspaces), GET /workspaces/{workspaceId}/murals (to list murals in a workspace), POST /murals (to create a new mural), GET /murals/{muralId} (to fetch mural details), and DELETE /murals/{muralId} (to delete a mural). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("mural", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},namely:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Namely",visibility:"beta",vertical:["hris"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-namely.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access and manage HR employee, profile, team, event, and folder data.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Namely connector via the proxy pattern to perform operations such as GET /v1/profiles (list profiles), GET /v1/events (list events), GET /v1/teams (list teams), POST /v1/events (create announcement), and GET /v1/folders (list folders). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 auth injection — use connectors.proxy("namely", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"nano-banana":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Nano Banana",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-nano-banana.svg",authType:"API_KEY",accessType:"global",blueprint:{agentInstructions:"",packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},nationbuilder:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"NationBuilder",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-nationbuilder.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage people, lists, contacts, events, and more.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the NationBuilder connector via the proxy pattern to call NationBuilder\'s API. Common useful endpoints include: GET /api/v1/people (list people), POST /api/v1/people (create person), PUT /api/v1/people/push (upsert person), GET /api/v1/lists (list lists), POST /api/v1/lists (create list). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 auth injection — use connectors.proxy("nationbuilder", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},netsuite:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"NetSuite",visibility:"beta",vertical:["accounting"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-netsuite.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access NetSuite REST APIs using OAuth2 authentication.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the NetSuite (OAuth) connector via the proxy pattern to invoke key REST endpoints. Common endpoints include:\n• GET /services/rest/record/v1/customer — retrieve customer records\n• POST /services/rest/auth/oauth2/v1/token — obtain or refresh access tokens\n• GET /services/rest/record/v1/metadata-catalog — get OpenAPI metadata catalog\n• GET /services/rest/auth/oauth2/v1/userinfo — retrieve user info via OIDC flow\nRequests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth injection; use connectors.proxy("netsuite", "/path") to invoke them. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"ninjaone-rmm-oauth2":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"NinjaOne",visibility:"beta",vertical:["ticketing"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-ninjaone-rmm-oauth2.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to NinjaOne RMM to manage and monitor devices and organizations.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the NinjaOne RMM connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints include GET /api/v2/organizations to list organizations, GET /api/v2/devices to retrieve devices, POST /api/v2/organizations to create an organization. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("ninjaone-rmm-oauth2", "/api/v2/devices"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""},integrationKeys:{nango:"ninjaone-rmm-oauth2"}}},nocrm:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"nocrm.io",visibility:"beta",vertical:["crm"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-nocrm.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Create, manage, and retrieve leads, clients, and related records.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the noCRM.io connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /api/v2/leads to list leads, POST /api/v2/leads to create a lead, GET /api/v2/leads/unassigned to list unassigned leads. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API-key injection in headers. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("nocrm", "/api/v2/leads"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},notion:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Notion",visibility:"ga",vertical:["wiki"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-notion.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Notion to manage pages, databases, and workspace content.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Notion connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. The Notion-Version header is injected automatically by the proxy — never set it manually. Common endpoints: GET /v1/users/me to get the current user, POST /v1/search to search pages and databases, POST /v1/databases/{database_id}/query to query a database, GET /v1/pages/{page_id} to get a page, POST /v1/pages to create a page. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("notion", "/v1/search"). The proxy returns a raw response object — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"@notionhq/client",package_version:"2.3.0"}]}},links:{webUrl:"https://notion.so",apiDocsUrl:"https://developers.notion.com/reference/intro"},integrationKeys:{nango:"notion"}}},"nyne-ai":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Nyne AI",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-nyne-ai.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Connect to Nyne AI to retrieve leads and intent signals via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Nyne AI connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /v1/leads to list leads, GET /v1/leads/{id} to get a lead by ID, POST /v1/signals/search to search intent signals. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("nyne-ai", "/v1/leads"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},odoo:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Odoo",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-odoo.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Perform authenticated API calls via OAuth2 for data access.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Odoo (OAuth) connector via the proxy pattern. The most common API endpoints you will use are: GET /api/oauth2/token (to obtain access tokens), GET /api/partner/rest (to retrieve partner records), POST /jsonrpc (to send JSON-RPC calls), GET /restapi/1.0/common/oauth2/access_token (for REST API OAuth token flow), and GET /api/jwt/token (if JWT auth is supported). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection—use connectors.proxy("odoo", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},okta:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Okta",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-okta.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Okta to manage users, tokens, and OAuth flows.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use the Okta connector, invoke common endpoints for user and OAuth flow management. Useful endpoints include: GET /api/v1/users (list users), POST /oauth2/default/v1/token (obtain token), GET /oauth2/default/v1/userinfo (user info), POST /oauth2/default/v1/revoke (revoke tokens), and GET /api/v1/logs (system logs). Use the proxy pattern via connectors.proxy("okta", "/path") — authentication (OAuth2 tokens) is injected and refreshed automatically by the SDK. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"one-drive-personal":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"OneDrive Personal",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["wiki","file-storage"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-one-drive-personal.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage files and metadata via Microsoft Graph API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the OneDrive Personal connector via the proxy pattern to access common endpoints such as: GET /me/drive (to get drive info), GET /me/drive/root/children (to list root files/folders), POST /me/drive/items/{item-id}/children (to create/upload), GET /me/drive/items/{item-id} (to get metadata), and GET /me/drive/root/delta (to list changed items since last sync). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Use: connectors.proxy("one-drive-personal", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},onedrive:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Microsoft OneDrive",visibility:"ga",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-onedrive.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage and interact with files via Microsoft Graph.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Microsoft OneDrive connector via the proxy pattern to perform common operations such as: GET /me/drive/root/children to list files, GET /me/drive/items/{item-id} to get an item, POST /me/drive/items/{parent-id}/children to upload or create, PATCH /me/drive/items/{item-id} to update properties, and GET /me/drive/root/delta to track changes. Make calls via connectors.proxy("onedrive", "/path") so that OAuth2 authorization is injected and refreshed automatically. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""},integrationKeys:{nango:"onedrive"}}},onlogist:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Onlogist",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-onlogist.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Connect to OnLogist to manage vehicle transfer orders via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the OnLogist connector via the proxy pattern for seamless, authenticated API access. Common endpoints: GET /transportation/orders to list orders, POST /transportation/orders to create a new order, GET /transportation/orders/{id} to retrieve order details, PUT /transportation/orders/{id}/status to update status. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("onlogist", "/transportation/orders"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},oomnitza:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Oomnitza",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-oomnitza.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Interact with its REST API for asset and user management.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Oomnitza connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints include GET /api/v3/assets to list assets, GET /api/v3/users to list users, POST /api/v3/assets to create an asset. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API-key authentication injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("oomnitza", "/api/v3/assets"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"oomnitza-node",package_version:"latest"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"open-hands":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Open Hands",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-open-hands.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Connect to OpenHands to control AI-powered coding agents via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the OpenHands connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /api/v1/projects (list projects), GET /api/options/models (list supported models), POST /api/conversations (start or init a conversation). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API-Key injected in headers. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("open-hands", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},openai:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"OpenAI",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-openai.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Access models for chat, completions, edits, images, moderation, and more.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use the OpenAI connector via the proxy pattern, your agent can call common endpoints such as POST /chat/completions, POST /completions, GET /models, and POST /moderations. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic authentication headers. Use: connectors.proxy("openai", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},ordinal:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Ordinal",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-ordinal.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage posts, analytics, auto-engagements, approvals, and team settings",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Ordinal connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints include:\n• GET /posts to list posts\n• POST /posts to create or schedule a post\n• GET /analytics to retrieve performance data\n• POST /auto-engagements to configure engagements\n• GET /team to view workspace users or settings. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("ordinal", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},osu:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Osu",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-osu.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Osu to access user, beatmap, score, and match data via OAuth2.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Osu connector via the proxy pattern to call its most common endpoints: GET /users/{id}, GET /beatmaps/{id}, GET /scores/{beatmapId}, POST /matches/{id}, and GET /user/recent. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection—prefer using: connectors.proxy("osu", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},oura:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Oura",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-oura.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Oura to fetch health and sleep data via the Oura Cloud API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Oura connector via the proxy pattern to interact with key endpoints like GET /v2/usercollection/daily_sleep, GET /v2/usercollection/daily_readiness, GET /v2/usercollection/daily_activity, GET /v2/usercollection/heartrate, and GET /v2/usercollection/personal_info. All requests are proxied through the SDK, with OAuth2 tokens injected and refreshed automatically. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("oura", "/v2/usercollection/daily_sleep") and similarly for other paths. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},outlook:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Microsoft Outlook",visibility:"ga",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-outlook.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access mail, calendar, contacts, and more via Microsoft Graph.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Microsoft Outlook connector via the proxy pattern by calling connectors.proxy("outlook", "/path"). Common useful API endpoints include GET /v1.0/me/messages (list emails), POST /v1.0/me/messages (create or send messages), GET /v1.0/me/events (list calendar events), POST /v1.0/me/events (create an event), and GET /v1.0/me/contacts (retrieve contacts). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""},integrationKeys:{nango:"outlook"}}},outreach:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Outreach",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-outreach.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access and manage sales data, sequences, prospects, users, and compliance.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use the Outreach connector via the proxy pattern, leverage endpoints such as: GET /api/v2 (root status/info), GET /api/v2/prospects, GET /api/v2/users, POST /oauth/token (to obtain or refresh tokens), and POST /api/v2/complianceRequests. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh. Use connectors.proxy("outreach", "/path") to send requests to Outreach. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},pagerduty:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"PagerDuty",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-pagerduty.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage incidents and alerts via OAuth2-enabled REST APIs.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the PagerDuty connector via the proxy pattern by calling connectors.proxy("pagerduty", "/incidents"), connectors.proxy("pagerduty", "/incidents/{id}"), connectors.proxy("pagerduty", "/incidents/{id}/acknowledge"), connectors.proxy("pagerduty", "/incidents/{id}/resolve"), or connectors.proxy("pagerduty", "/services") (e.g., GET /services, GET /incidents, POST /incidents, PUT /incidents/{id}/resolve). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 authentication injected and refreshed. Prefer using connectors.proxy("pagerduty", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},pandadoc:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Pandadoc",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-pandadoc.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Automate creation, sending, signing, and management of documents.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the PandaDoc connector via the proxy pattern. Common endpoints include: POST /oauth2/access_token (create or refresh OAuth2 token), POST /public/v1/documents (create and send documents), GET /public/v1/documents/{id} (fetch document status), POST /public/v1/documents/{id}/send (send a document), and GET /public/v1/contacts (list contacts). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection — use connectors.proxy("pandadoc", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},paycor:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Paycor",visibility:"beta",vertical:["hris"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-paycor.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access HR, payroll, and employee data via secure OAuth2 API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use Paycor connector via the proxy pattern to call common endpoints like GET /v1/employees, GET /v1/companies/{companyId}, POST /v1/timeEntries, PATCH /v1/employees/{employeeId}, and GET /v1/jobs. Make requests through connectors.proxy("paycor", "/path")—authentication (OAuth2 tokens) and APIM subscription key are injected and refreshed automatically. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"paycor-sandbox":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Paycor (Sandbox)",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["hris"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-paycor-sandbox.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access HR data like employees, paystubs, and direct deposits.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Paycor (Sandbox) OAuth2 connector via the proxy pattern. Commonly used endpoints include: GET /v2/tenants/{tenantId}/employees, GET /v2/employees/{employeeId}/DirectDeposits/{directDepositId}, and GET /v2/employees/{employeeId}/paystubDocumentData. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection and refresh. Use the pattern connectors.proxy("paycor-sandbox", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},payfit:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Payfit",visibility:"beta",vertical:["hris"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-payfit.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access payroll, HR, collaborator and document data via OAuth2.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use this PayFit connector via the proxy pattern to call common endpoints such as GET /companies/{companyId}, GET /companies/{companyId}/documents/{documentId}, GET /collaborators/{id}/payslips (or similar), and POST /companies/{companyId}/collaborators to create collaborators. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refreshing. Use connectors.proxy("payfit", "/path") for each call. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},paypal:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Paypal",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-paypal.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Paypal to manage payments, orders, and payouts via REST API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the PayPal connector via the proxy pattern. Common API endpoints include POST /v2/checkout/orders (Create order), POST /v2/checkout/orders/{order_id}/capture (Capture order), GET /v2/checkout/orders/{order_id} (Show order details), POST /v1/payments/payouts (Create payout batch), and GET /v1/payments/payouts/{id} (Get payout status). These requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("paypal", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"paypal-sandbox":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Paypal (Sandbox)",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-paypal-sandbox.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Test REST API flows using OAuth2 in a safe environment.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use this connector to interact with PayPal Sandbox via the proxy pattern. Common useful endpoints include:\n• POST /v1/oauth2/token (generate or refresh OAuth2 access token)\n• GET /v1/identity/oauth2/userinfo (retrieve user profile info)\n• POST /v2/checkout/orders (create an order)\n• GET /v2/checkout/orders/{order_id} (retrieve order details)\nThe SDK automatically injects and refreshes OAuth2 tokens; you don’t need to manage them manually. Prefer sending requests through the proxy like: connectors.proxy("paypal-sandbox", "/v1/oauth2/token"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},pendo:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Pendo",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-pendo.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage guides, segments, metadata, and feedback programmatically.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Pendo connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API interactions. Common endpoints include: GET /api/v1/engage/guide to retrieve guides, POST /api/v1/engage/segments to create segments, PUT /api/v1/engage/metadata to update metadata, GET /api/v1/feedback to fetch feedback requests, and POST /api/v1/feedback to submit feedback. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("pendo", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},pennylane:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Pennylane",visibility:"beta",vertical:["accounting","banking"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-pennylane.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Automate accounting workflows: customers, invoices, and transactions",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Connect to Pennylane\'s API via the proxy pattern; you can interact with common endpoints such as GET /v2/customers to list customers, POST /v2/invoices to create invoices, GET /v2/suppliers to list suppliers, POST /v2/transactions to create transactions, and GET /v2/me to verify authentication. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh. Use connectors.proxy("pennylane", "/v2/customers") to make calls. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"pennylane-company-api":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Pennylane (Company API)",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["accounting","banking"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-pennylane-company-api.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage company accounting and related resources via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Pennylane Company API connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /api/external/v2/me to fetch current user and company details, GET /api/external/v2/customers to list customers, POST /api/external/v2/customer_invoices to create a customer invoice. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("pennylane-company-api", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},peopledatalabs:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"People Data Labs",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-peopledatalabs.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Connect to People Data Labs to enrich and search person and company data.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the People Data Labs connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /v5/person/enrich for person enrichment, GET /v5/person/search for person search, GET /v5/person/identify for finding matching profiles, GET /v5/company/clean for company cleaner, GET /v5/location/clean for location cleaner. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("peopledatalabs", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"peopledatalabs",package_version:"latest"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},perdoo:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Perdoo",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-perdoo.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage OKRs, KPIs, initiatives, and goal data via GraphQL API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Perdoo connector via the proxy pattern to perform authenticated operations. Common endpoints: POST /graphql to query or mutate OKRs, GET /graphql for data retrieval, and potentially POST /graphql mutations like updateGoal or createInitiative. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API token injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("perdoo", "/graphql"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},perplexity:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Perplexity",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-perplexity.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Perform web-grounded searches and get AI reasoning responses.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Perplexity connector via the SDK’s proxy pattern for authenticated API calls. Common endpoints: POST /search (Search API), POST /sonar (Sonar reasoning model), GET /models (list available models), maybe POST /search/multi-query. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection via headers. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("perplexity", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"perplexity-sdk",package_version:"latest"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"personio-recruiting":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Personio Recruiting",visibility:"beta",vertical:["hris"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-personio-recruiting.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage jobs, candidates, and applications.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Personio Recruiting connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /recruiting/jobs to list jobs, GET /recruiting/candidates to list candidates, POST /recruiting/applications to create an application, POST /recruiting/applications/documents to upload documents, GET /recruiting/applications to retrieve applications. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("personio-recruiting", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},pingone:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"PingOne",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-pingone.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to PingOne to authorize and manage OAuth2 authentication flows.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'For an AI agent using the PingOne connector via the proxy pattern, commonly used endpoints include POST /oauth2/access_token to obtain or refresh tokens, GET /<envID>/as/authorize to initiate authorization, POST /oauth2/introspect to inspect token state, POST /oauth2/token/revoke to revoke tokens, and POST /oauth2/par for pushed authorization requests. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection; use connectors.proxy("pingone", "/path") to make calls. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},pinterest:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Pinterest",visibility:"beta",vertical:["social-media","streaming"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-pinterest.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Read boards and pins, create pins, and manage user accounts.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Pinterest connector via the proxy pattern. Common useful endpoints: GET /v5/boards (list boards), GET /v5/pins (list pins), POST /v5/pins (create a pin), DELETE /v5/pins/{pin_id}, GET /v5/user_accounts (read account info). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("pinterest", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},pipedream:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Pipedream",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-pipedream.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage workflows, event sources, and account data via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Pipedream connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API access. Common endpoints: GET /v1/users/me to get user info; GET /v1/workflows to list workflows; POST /v1/event-sources to create an event source. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("pipedream", "/v1/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},pipedrive:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Pipedrive",visibility:"beta",vertical:["crm"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-pipedrive.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Pipedrive to access CRM data using OAuth2-powered REST API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Pipedrive connector via the proxy pattern to interact with the Pipedrive REST API. Common useful endpoints include: GET /api/v1/deals, POST /api/v1/persons, GET /api/v1/activities, POST /api/v1/notes, and GET /api/v1/activities (v2 beta). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection. Call requests using connectors.proxy("pipedrive", "/api/v1/deals") (or other paths). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},pivotaltracker:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Pivotal Tracker",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-pivotaltracker.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage projects, stories, epics, and activity.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Pivotal Tracker connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API calls. Common endpoints: GET /projects to list projects, GET /projects/{project_id}/stories to list stories, POST /projects/{project_id}/stories to create a story, PUT /projects/{project_id}/stories/{story_id} to update a story. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection into headers. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("pivotaltracker", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"pivotaltracker",package_version:"0.1.3"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},plaid:{hasClient:!0,hasServer:!0,metadata:{verticals:["banking"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],displayName:"Plaid",stage:"ga",description:"Connect to Plaid to access financial data, bank accounts, and transactions.",logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-plaid.svg",links:{webUrl:"https://plaid.com",apiDocsUrl:"https://plaid.com/docs/"},blueprint:{agentInstructions:"Use the @replit/connectors-sdk with the official Plaid SDK to interact with the Plaid API via a secure proxy.\n\nThe getPlaidClient() function returns a fully configured Plaid client that:\n- Uses @replit/connectors-sdk for authentication and proxy routing\n- Works exactly like the official Plaid SDK\n- All credentials are managed securely by the proxy\n\nExample: Get account balances\n\n  const client = await getPlaidClient();\n\n  // Get all linked accounts\n  const accountsResponse = await client.accountsGet({});\n  console.log('Accounts:', accountsResponse.data.accounts);\n\n  // Get account balances\n  const balanceResponse = await client.accountsBalanceGet({});\n  for (const account of balanceResponse.data.accounts) {\n    console.log(account.name + ': $' + account.balances.current);\n  }\n\nExample: Get recent transactions\n\n  const client = await getPlaidClient();\n\n  const response = await client.transactionsGet({\n    start_date: '2024-01-01',\n    end_date: '2024-12-31',\n  });\n\n  for (const txn of response.data.transactions) {\n    console.log(txn.date + ' - ' + txn.name + ': $' + txn.amount);\n  }\n\nSee https://plaid.com/docs/api/ for all available methods.",packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"plaid",package_version:"40.0.0",code_snippet:"import { Configuration, PlaidApi, type PlaidApiInterface } from 'plaid';\n\n// Creates a Plaid client that uses the OpenInt proxy.\n// Auth headers are resolved fresh on every call so tokens never go stale in long-lived processes.\n// All API calls are automatically authenticated - credentials and access_token are injected by the proxy.\n//\n// Usage:\n//   const client = await getPlaidClient();\n//   const accounts = await client.accountsGet({});  // No access_token needed!\n//   const transactions = await client.transactionsGet({ start_date: '2024-01-01', end_date: '2024-12-31' });\n//\nexport async function getPlaidClient(): Promise<PlaidApiInterface> {\n  const proxyHeaders = await getProxyHeaders();\n\n  const configuration = new Configuration({\n    basePath: proxyUrl,\n    baseOptions: {\n      headers: proxyHeaders,\n    },\n  });\n\n  const rawClient = new PlaidApi(configuration);\n\n  // Wrap the client to allow omitting access_token (proxy injects it)\n  return new Proxy(rawClient, {\n    get(target, prop) {\n      const value = (target as any)[prop];\n      if (typeof value === 'function') {\n        return async (request: any = {}, ...args: any[]) => {\n          const patchedRequest = { access_token: '', ...request };\n          return value.call(target, patchedRequest, ...args);\n        };\n      }\n      return value;\n    }\n  }) as PlaidApiInterface;\n}"}]}}}},plain:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Plain",visibility:"beta",vertical:["ticketing"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-plain.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Connect to Plain to access its GraphQL-based customer support API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Plain connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API calls. Common endpoints: POST /graphql/v1 to run GraphQL queries, POST /graphql/v1/schema.graphql to fetch the schema, and POST /graphql/v1 with customerByEmail query to get customer data. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection into headers. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("plain", "/graphql/v1"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},podium:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Podium",visibility:"beta",vertical:["communication"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-podium.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access locations, contacts, messages, and webhook events.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Podium connector via the proxy pattern. Common endpoints include: GET /locations (list locations), GET /locations/{uid} (get a location), GET /contacts (list contacts), GET /contacts/{identifier} (get a contact), POST /webhooks (create a webhook). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection—use connectors.proxy("podium", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},postgres:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!0,metadata:{verticals:["database"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-postgres.svg",stage:"ga"}},posthog:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"PostHog",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-posthog.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Send analytics events, fetch feature flags, and query configurations",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the PostHog connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: POST /capture to send events, GET /decide to retrieve feature flag configurations, GET /array/:token/config for web SDK config, POST /batch for batched events, GET /s for session recordings. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key (Authorization: Bearer) injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("posthog", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"posthog-js",package_version:"latest"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},practicefusion:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"PracticeFusion",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-practicefusion.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access its FHIR-based clinical data via OAuth2.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the PracticeFusion connector via the proxy pattern to call common FHIR endpoints. For example, GET /.well-known/smart-configuration, GET /metadata, GET /Patient, GET /Observation. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection—use connectors.proxy("practicefusion", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},precisefp:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"PreciseFP",visibility:"beta",vertical:["crm"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-precisefp.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access accounts, engagements, templates, users via REST API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the PreciseFP connector via the proxy pattern to interact with its RESTful API. Common endpoints include: GET /api/v2/accounts, GET /api/v2/engagements, GET /api/v2/user, GET /api/v2/user/templates. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("precisefp", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},printful:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Printful",visibility:"beta",vertical:["commerce"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-printful.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage products, orders, mockups, and file library via Printful API",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Printful connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints include GET /products (to list catalog items), GET /orders/{order_id} (to retrieve order details), POST /orders (to create an order), GET /product-templates (to list your templates), and POST /webhooks (to register a webhook). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("printful", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},prive:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Prive",visibility:"beta",vertical:["commerce"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-prive.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Connect to Prive to manage subscriptions via its API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Prive connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /subscriptions to list subscriptions, POST /subscriptions to create a subscription, GET /subscriptions/{id} to retrieve a subscription. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("prive", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},procore:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Procore",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-procore.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Procore to access construction project data via its RESTful API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Procore connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /rest/v1.0/projects to list projects; GET /rest/v1.0/companies/{company_id}/projects to list company projects; GET /rest/v1.0/projects/{project_id}/users to list project users; POST /rest/v1.0/companies/{company_id}/generic_tools to create a Generic Tool; GET /rest/v1.0/companies/{company_id}/generic_tools to list generic tools. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("procore", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"@procore/js-sdk",package_version:"4.3.0"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},productboard:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Productboard",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-productboard.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage products, features, notes, teams, and webhooks via API v2",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Productboard connector via the proxy pattern against Public API v2 (https://api.productboard.com/v2). Common endpoints: GET /entities (list/search products, components, features), POST /entities (create entity), PATCH /entities/{id} (update), GET /notes (list notes), POST /notes (create note), GET /members (list workspace members), GET /teams (list teams), POST /webhooks (create webhook). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("productboard", "/v2/<path>"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body. Productboard Public API v1 is deprecated and will be sunset on July 8, 2026; new integrations should use v2 endpoints.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},prospeo:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Prospeo",visibility:"beta",vertical:["crm"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-prospeo.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Connect to Prospeo to search and enrich B2B contact and company data.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Prospeo connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: POST /enrich-person, POST /bulk-enrich-person, POST /enrich-company, POST /search-person, POST /search-company. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("prospeo", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},pylon:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Pylon",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-pylon.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage support issues, accounts, contacts, and messages via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Pylon connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API access. Common endpoints include: GET /issues to list issues, GET /issues/{issue_id} to fetch an issue, POST /issues to create a new issue, GET /accounts to list accounts, and POST /contacts to create a contact. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("pylon", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},qualtrics:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Qualtrics",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-qualtrics.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage surveys, contacts, distributions, and responses via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'When using this Qualtrics connector, you can call common API endpoints via the proxy. Key endpoints include: GET /surveys to list surveys, GET /surveys/:surveyId to retrieve a survey, POST /distributions to create a distribution (and generate survey links), POST /directories/:dirId/contacts to create a contact, and GET /mailinglists to list mailing lists. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 authentication injection. Use connectors.proxy("qualtrics", "/path") for making API calls. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},quickbase:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Quickbase",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-quickbase.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Add, query, and manage records in your Quickbase applications.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Quickbase connector via the proxy pattern for secure authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: • GET /apps/{appId} to retrieve application details • POST /records to add a record to a table (API_AddRecord) • GET /records/query to query table records. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("quickbase", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"quickbase",package_version:"6.0.0"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},quickbooks:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Quickbooks",visibility:"beta",vertical:["accounting"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-quickbooks.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access and manage company accounting data via its REST API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the QuickBooks connector via the proxy pattern. Common useful endpoints include: GET /v3/company/<realmId>/customer, POST /v3/company/<realmId>/invoice, GET /v3/company/<realmId>/payment, GET /v3/company/<realmId>/vendor, and GET /v3/company/<realmId>/query. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh. Use connectors.proxy("quickbooks", "/path") for calls. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"quiver-ai":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"QuiverAI",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-quiver-ai.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Connect to QuiverAI to generate SVGs and vectorize raster images.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the QuiverAI connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: POST /svgs/generations (generate SVGs from a text prompt), POST /svgs/vectorizations (convert an image to SVG). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("quiver-ai", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{},exampleUsage:{javascript:[{name:"list-models",snippet:'import { ReplitConnectors } from "@replit/connectors-sdk";\n\nconst connectors = new ReplitConnectors();\nconst response = await connectors.proxy("quiver-ai", "/models");\n\nif (!response.ok) {\n  const text = await response.text().catch(() => "");\n  throw new Error(`HTTP ${response.status}: ${text}`);\n}\n\nconst body = await response.json();\nconst models = Array.isArray(body) ? body : body.data;\n\nif (!Array.isArray(models) || models.length === 0) {\n  throw new Error("Expected at least one model in response");\n}\n\nexport const result = { count: models.length, first: models[0]?.id ?? models[0]?.name };'}]}},links:{webUrl:"https://quiver.ai",apiDocsUrl:"https://docs.quiver.ai"}}},ragieai:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Ragie AI",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-ragieai.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Ingest, index, and semantically retrieve multimodal documents.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Ragie connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: POST /documents/raw to upload raw data, GET /documents/{documentId} to check status or retrieve, POST /retrievals to perform semantic search queries. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("ragieai", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"ragie",package_version:"latest"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},ramp:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Ramp",visibility:"beta",vertical:["banking"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-ramp.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Programmatically manage corporate cards, users, and transactions.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Ramp connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /transactions to list transactions, GET /cards to list cards, POST /cards to issue a card, GET /users to list users—these routes provide access to core Ramp objects. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("ramp", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"ramp-sandbox":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Ramp (Sandbox)",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-ramp-sandbox.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Ramp (Sandbox) to manage test users via Ramp’s RESTful API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Ramp Sandbox connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API interactions. Common endpoints include: POST /users to create a user, DELETE /users to delete a user by id, and GET /users to list users. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("ramp-sandbox", "/users"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""},integrationKeys:{nango:"ramp-sandbox"}}},rapidapi:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"RapidAPI",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-rapidapi.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Proxy key-based requests through a unified API gateway.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the RapidAPI connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints include: GET /v1/rest/someEndpoint, POST /v1/rest/anotherEndpoint, GET /v1/rest/listResources. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection in the X-RapidAPI-Key header. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("rapidapi", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},readwise:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Readwise",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-readwise.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage highlights, books, daily reviews, and Reader documents.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Readwise connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /review/ (daily review highlights), GET /highlights/ (list highlights), POST /highlights/ (create highlights), GET /books/{book_id}/ (book detail), GET /list/ (Reader document list). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("readwise", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"readwise-reader":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Readwise Reader",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-readwise-reader.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Connect to Readwise Reader to manage reading documents via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Readwise Reader connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints include: POST /save/ to create a document, GET /list/ to fetch documents, PATCH /update/{document_id}/ to modify a document, DELETE /delete/{document_id}/ to remove a document, and GET /tags/ to list tags. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("readwise-reader", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},reapit:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Reapit Connect",visibility:"beta",vertical:["crm"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-reapit.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage user authentication via OAuth2 for Foundations APIs.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Reapit Connect connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /oauth2/userInfo to fetch user details, POST /token to exchange or refresh tokens, GET /authorize to initiate the OAuth flow. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("reapit", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"@reapit/connect-session",package_version:"latest"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"recall-ai":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Recall.ai",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-recall-ai.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Record, transcribe, and retrieve meeting data via a unified API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Recall.ai connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints include: POST /api/v1/bot to create a meeting bot, GET /api/v1/bot/{bot_id}/transcript to fetch transcripts, POST /api/v1/bot/{bot_id}/output_media/ to send output media, POST /api/v1/sdk_upload/ to initiate a desktop SDK recording, GET /api/v2/calendar-events to list calendar events. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("recall-ai", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"recall_sdk",package_version:"1.3.0"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},recharge:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Recharge",visibility:"beta",vertical:["commerce"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-recharge.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage subscriptions, customers, and charges via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Recharge connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /customers to list customers, POST /customers to upsert a customer, GET /subscriptions to retrieve subscriptions, POST /charges/{id}/process to process a charge, GET /events to fetch recent events. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("recharge", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"@rechargeapps/storefront-client",package_version:"latest"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},recruitcrm:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Recruitcrm",visibility:"beta",vertical:["hris"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-recruitcrm.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Connect to RecruitCRM to manage your recruitment ATS/CRM via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the RecruitCRM connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints include: GET /candidates, POST /candidates, GET /jobs, GET /deals, POST /deals. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection into headers. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("recruitcrm", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},recruitee:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Recruitee",visibility:"beta",vertical:["ats"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-recruitee.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage jobs, candidates, offers, and admin data via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Recruitee connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated requests. Common endpoints: GET /c/{company_id}/offers to list job offers, GET /c/{company_id}/candidates to list candidates, GET /c/{company_id}/admin to fetch current admin info, PATCH /c/{company_id}/offers/{id} to update a job offer. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("recruitee", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},recruiterflow:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Recruiterflow",visibility:"beta",vertical:["hris"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-recruiterflow.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Access ATS data like jobs, candidates, contacts, and deals.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Recruiterflow connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API access. Common endpoints: GET /jobs to list jobs, GET /candidates to fetch candidate records, GET /contacts to retrieve contacts, GET /deals to list deals, POST /candidates to create a candidate. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("recruiterflow", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},reddit:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Reddit",visibility:"beta",vertical:["social-media"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-reddit.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Read and write content, user info, comments, and subreddit data via OAuth2.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Reddit connector via the proxy pattern to access endpoints like GET /api/v1/me, GET /r/{subreddit}/hot, POST /api/submit, GET /user/{username}/about and GET /r/{subreddit}/new. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("reddit", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},refiner:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Refiner",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-refiner.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage survey data, contacts, events, and aggregated reports.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Refiner connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints include: POST /identify-user (identify or create a contact), POST /track-event (track user events), POST /responses (submit survey responses), GET /contacts (list contacts), GET /reporting (get aggregated report data). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("refiner", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"refiner-js",package_version:"1.2.4"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},replicate:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Replicate",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-replicate.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Run, fine-tune, and manage AI model predictions via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Replicate connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints include: POST /v1/predictions to create a prediction, GET /v1/predictions/{prediction_id} to check status or get results, GET /v1/models/{model_owner}/{model_name} to fetch model info, POST /v1/trainings to start fine-tuning, and GET /v1/predictions/{prediction_id}/cancel to cancel. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("replicate", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"replicate",package_version:"latest"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},resend:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!0,metadata:{verticals:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-resend.svg",stage:"ga",authType:"API_KEY"}},"retell-ai":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Retell AI",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-retell-ai.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Connect to Retell AI to manage voice agents, calls, chats, and telephony.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Retell AI connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API calls. Common endpoints: POST /create-agent, POST /create-phone-call (create call), POST /create-chat-completion (generate chat response), plus endpoints like GET /get-chat or GET /get-agent. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("retell-ai", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"retell-sdk",package_version:"latest"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},revenuecat:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"RevenueCat",visibility:"alpha",vertical:["commerce"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-revenuecat.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage subscription products, entitlements, and metrics.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the RevenueCat connector via the proxy pattern (OAuth tokens are injected and refreshed automatically). Common API endpoints include: GET /v1/subscribers/{app_user_id}, GET /v2/projects/{projectId}/customers/{customerId}/subscriptions, POST /v2/projects/{projectId}/apps (app creation), GET /v2/projects/{projectId}/customers (list customers), and GET /metrics or Charts API endpoints for analytics. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection; use connectors.proxy("revenuecat", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"ring-central":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"RingCentral",visibility:"beta",vertical:["ticketing"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-ring-central.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access messaging, call logs, presence, and account configuration.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the RingCentral connector via the proxy pattern to call common endpoints such as GET /restapi/v1.0/account/~/extension/~/message-store, GET /restapi/v1.0/account/~/extension/~/call-log, GET /restapi/v1.0/account/~/service-info, and GET /restapi/v1.0/account/~/extension/~/presence. The connector handles OAuth2 tokens automatically, with requests proxied through the SDK and auth injected seamlessly. To call, use: connectors.proxy("ring-central", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"ring-central-sandbox":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"RingCentral (Sandbox)",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-ring-central-sandbox.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access and interact with messaging, calls, and account APIs.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the RingCentral (Sandbox) connector via the proxy pattern to invoke endpoints such as GET /restapi/v1.0/account/{accountId}/extension (list extensions), GET /restapi/v1.0/account/{accountId}/caller-id (retrieve caller IDs), GET /restapi/v1.0/account/{accountId}/message-store (fetch messages), and GET /restapi/v1.0/restapi (retrieve API versions). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("ring-central-sandbox", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},rippling:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Rippling",visibility:"beta",vertical:["hris"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-rippling.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Interact with HR, IT, finance resources via REST API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Rippling connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /workers to list employees, GET /departments to list departments, POST /companies to create a company, PATCH /employees/{id} to update an employee, DELETE /departments/{id} to remove a department. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("rippling", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"@apideck/node",package_version:"latest"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"rippling-shop-app":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Rippling Shop App",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["hris"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-rippling-shop-app.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Integrate and automate employee provisioning workflows.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Rippling Shop App connector via the proxy pattern to access endpoints like GET /employees, POST /orders, PATCH /licenses, DELETE /accounts (proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection). Prefer using: connectors.proxy("rippling-shop-app", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},rocketlane:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Rocketlane",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-rocketlane.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Access and manage onboarding, projects, tasks, and related resources.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Rocketlane connector via the proxy pattern to make authenticated API calls. Common endpoints: GET /api/1.0/projects/{projectId}, POST /api/1.0/projects, GET /api/1.0/tasks/{taskId}, POST /api/1.0/tasks, POST /api/1.0/projects/{projectId}/archive. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API-key injection in headers. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("rocketlane", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"rocketlane-sdk",package_version:"1.0.4"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},rootly:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Rootly",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-rootly.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage incidents, alerts, teams, and on-call schedules via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Rootly connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /v1/incidents to list incidents, POST /v1/incidents to create an incident, GET /v1/teams to list teams, PATCH /v1/incidents/{id} to update an incident. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("rootly", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},sage:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Sage",visibility:"beta",vertical:["accounting"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-sage.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Sage to access and manipulate accounting data via RESTful API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Sage connector via the proxy pattern with automatic OAuth2 authentication. Common endpoints include GET /businesses, GET /contacts, POST /sales_invoices, GET /transactions, and GET /products. All requests are proxied through the SDK with auth injection—use connectors.proxy("sage", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"sage-hr":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Sage HR",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["hris"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-sage-hr.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Connect to Sage HR to manage employee and HR data via its REST API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Sage HR connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /employees to list employees, GET /employees/{id} to retrieve a specific employee, POST /employees to create a new employee (using your subdomain in the base URL https://{subdomain}.sage.hr). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("sage-hr", "/employees"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"sage-intacct-oauth":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Sage Intacct",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["accounting"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-sage-intacct-oauth.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access and manage Sage Intacct REST API resources securely.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Sage Intacct (OAuth) connector via the proxy pattern. Common useful endpoints include GET /company/configuration, GET /general-ledger/accounts, POST /accounts-payable/bills, GET /accounts-receivable/invoices, and GET /inventory-control/items. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection and refresh. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("sage-intacct-oauth", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"sage-people":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Sage People",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["hris"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-sage-people.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access and manage employee and HR data via REST API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use this connector, issue calls to common endpoints like GET /employees, GET /employees/{id}, POST /employees, PATCH /employees/{id}, DELETE /employees/{id}. Use the SDK’s proxy pattern: connectors.proxy("sage-people", "/employees") etc. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("sage-people", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},salesforce:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Salesforce",visibility:"alpha",vertical:["crm"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-salesforce.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",connectionCheckFrequency:3600,description:"Access CRM data and platform services via REST endpoints.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the jsforce SDK through the proxy for authenticated Salesforce requests. The code_snippet in packages shows the full setup: point the SDK at proxyUrl and inject proxy headers via getProxyHeaders("salesforce"). With this setup you can use the native SDK normally: conn.query("SELECT Id FROM Account"), conn.sobject("Contact").find(), conn.describe("Opportunity"), etc. The proxy resolves the real instance URL and OAuth credentials automatically — never hardcode them in client code.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"jsforce",package_version:"1.11.1",code_snippet:'import jsforce from "jsforce";\n\n// Resolve proxy headers once — they identify this connection to the proxy.\nconst headers = await getProxyHeaders();\n\n// Point jsforce at the proxy; it resolves the real Salesforce instance\n// and injects OAuth credentials on every request automatically.\nconst conn = new jsforce.Connection({\n  instanceUrl: proxyUrl,\n  accessToken: "proxy-managed",\n});\n\n// Inject proxy identity headers into every outgoing HTTP request.\nconst _httpRequest = conn._transport.httpRequest;\nconn._transport.httpRequest = function(req, opts) {\n  req.headers = { ...req.headers, ...headers };\n  return _httpRequest.call(this, req, opts);\n};'}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""},integrationKeys:{nango:"salesforce"}}},"salesforce-experience-cloud":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Salesforce Experience",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-salesforce-experience-cloud.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access community, Chatter, CMS, and user data via Connect APIs.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use this connector, call common endpoints like GET /connect/sites/{siteId}, GET /connect/communities/{communityId}/chatter/users, POST /connect/sites/{siteId}/cms/content, GET /services/data/vXX.0/sobjects/CommunityMember; requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection—use connectors.proxy("salesforce-experience-cloud", "/path"); Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"salesforce-sandbox":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Salesforce (Sandbox)",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-salesforce-sandbox.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Perform REST and Tooling API operations in a sandbox org via OAuth2.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Salesforce (Sandbox) connector via the proxy pattern to access common endpoints such as GET /services/data/v{version}/sobjects/Account (retrieve records), POST /services/data/v{version}/sobjects/Contact (create records), GET /services/data/v{version}/tooling/query/?q=SELECT+Id,SandboxName+FROM+SandboxInfo (list sandboxes), PATCH /services/data/v{version}/tooling/sobjects/SandboxInfo/{ID} (update sandbox), and POST /services/oauth2/token (fetch OAuth token via test.salesforce.com). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection—use connectors.proxy("salesforce-sandbox", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},salesloft:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Salesloft",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-salesloft.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Interact with CRM data via OAuth2-secured REST APIs.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Salesloft connector via the proxy pattern to access key endpoints such as GET /v2/people, POST /v2/accounts, GET /v2/opportunities, POST /v2/external/ids/{external_type}/{object_type}/{external_id}, and GET /v2/external/mappings. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection—simply call connectors.proxy("salesloft", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"salesmsg-oauth2":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Salesmsg",visibility:"beta",vertical:["communication"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-salesmsg-oauth2.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access and manage conversations, messages, and sending via REST API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Salesmsg connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /conversations to list conversations, GET /conversations/{id}/messages to fetch messages of a conversation, POST /conversations/{id}/send to send a message, POST /v2.2/oauth/token/refresh to refresh OAuth2 tokens. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("salesmsg-oauth2", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""},integrationKeys:{nango:"salesmsg-oauth2"}}},schwab:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Schwab",visibility:"beta",vertical:["banking","accounting"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-schwab.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access account data, market info, and trade functionality.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Schwab connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /v1/accounts to retrieve account details, GET /v1/marketdata/quotes for real-time quotes, POST /v1/orders to place trades. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("schwab", "/v1/accounts"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},scrapedo:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Scrape.do",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-scrapedo.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Scrape web pages with anti-bot bypass, proxies, rendering, and retries.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Scrape.do connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated scraping requests. Common endpoints: GET /?url={targetUrl}&token={token} for real-time scraping, POST /api/v1/jobs to create asynchronous jobs, and GET /api/v1/jobs/{jobID} to poll job results. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("scrapedo", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},segment:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Segment",visibility:"alpha",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-segment.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage workspaces, sources, destinations, warehouses, and tracking plans.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use the Segment connector via proxy, common endpoints include: GET /workspaces, GET /sources, GET /destinations, PATCH /sources/{sourceId}/settings, and GET /tracking-plans. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Use connectors.proxy("segment", "/path") to invoke endpoints via the proxy. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},sellsy:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Sellsy",visibility:"beta",vertical:["accounting","crm"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-sellsy.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Sellsy to access contacts, invoices, proposals and more via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Sellsy connector via the proxy pattern to call endpoints such as GET /contacts, POST /contacts, GET /invoices/{id}, POST /invoices, GET /proposals — requests are proxied through the SDK with OAuth2 tokens injected and refreshed automatically. Prefer using connectors.proxy("sellsy", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},semrush:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Semrush",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-semrush.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Access SEO, keyword, domain, backlink, and traffic analytics via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Semrush connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /?type=domain_ranks (Domain Overview), GET /?type=phrase_related (Phrase‐related keywords), GET /?type=backlinks (Backlink Analytics), GET /?type=organic &domain= (Organic Research), GET /?type=keyword_gap (Keyword Gap). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("semrush", "/?type=...&domain=..."). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},sendgrid:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!0,metadata:{verticals:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-sendgrid.svg",stage:"ga",authType:"API_KEY"}},sentry:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Sentry",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-sentry.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage issues, projects, teams, and other resources via its REST API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Sentry connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated REST API requests. Common endpoints: GET /api/0/organizations/{org_slug}/issues/ to list issues, GET /api/0/organizations/{org_slug}/teams/ to list teams, POST /api/0/projects/{org_slug}/{project_slug}/releases/ to create a release (and similarly GET teams, GET projects). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection via headers. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("sentry", "/api/0/organizations/{org_slug}/issues/"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"@sentry/node",package_version:"latest"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},servicem8:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"ServiceM8",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-servicem8.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access and manage jobs, clients, documents via OAuth2.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the ServiceM8 connector via the proxy pattern. Common endpoints include GET /api_1.0/jobs.json, GET /api_1.0/clients.json, POST /api_1.0/jobs.json to create a job, GET /api_1.0/company.json, and GET /api_1.0/vendor.json. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Use connectors.proxy("servicem8", "/path") for all calls. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},servicenow:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"ServiceNow",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-servicenow.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access and manage records via its REST APIs using OAuth2.",setupGuide:{docs_url:"https://www.servicenow.com/community/developer-blog/oauth-2-0-with-inbound-rest/ba-p/2278926",steps:["Open your ServiceNow instance.","Go to System OAuth > Application Registry.","Select New, then choose Create an OAuth API endpoint for external clients.","Save the application record, then copy the generated Client ID and Client Secret.","Use your instance URL to fill in the ServiceNow subdomain field."],fields:{subdomain:{label:"ServiceNow subdomain",help:"Use the first part of your ServiceNow instance URL. For https://acme.service-now.com, enter acme."},client_id:{label:"Client ID",help:"In your ServiceNow instance, go to System OAuth > Application Registry, open the OAuth API endpoint for external clients, and copy the generated Client ID.",source_url:"https://www.servicenow.com/community/developer-blog/oauth-2-0-with-inbound-rest/ba-p/2278926"},client_secret:{label:"Client secret",help:"In the same Application Registry record, copy the generated Client Secret. ServiceNow generates it when the OAuth API endpoint record is saved.",source_url:"https://www.servicenow.com/community/developer-blog/oauth-2-0-with-inbound-rest/ba-p/2278926",generate_url:"https://www.servicenow.com/community/developer-blog/oauth-2-0-with-inbound-rest/ba-p/2278926"}}},blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the ServiceNow connector via the proxy pattern. Common endpoints include GET /api/now/table/incident, POST /api/now/table/incident, PATCH /api/now/table/incident/<sys_id>, DELETE /api/now/table/incident/<sys_id>, and POST /oauth_token.do for token acquisition. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("servicenow", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},sharepoint:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"SharePoint Online",visibility:"ga",vertical:["file-storage","communication"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-sharepoint.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage sites, drives, lists, and pages via the Graph API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the SharePoint Online connector via the proxy pattern. Common useful endpoints include:\n• GET /sites (list sites)\n• GET /drives or GET /drive (retrieve document libraries or default drive)\n• GET /lists (manage lists)\n• GET or POST /sites/{site-id}/pages (manage SharePoint pages)\nRequests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh. Use: connectors.proxy("sharepoint", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""},integrationKeys:{nango:"sharepoint"}}},"shipstation-v2":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Shipstation",visibility:"beta",vertical:["commerce"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-shipstation-v2.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage shipping and inventory workflows via REST API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the ShipStation connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints include: GET /v2/batches to list batches, POST /v2/batches to create batch shipments, GET /v2/carriers to retrieve carrier info. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("shipstation-v2", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},shopify:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Shopify",visibility:"beta",vertical:["commerce"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-shopify.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access store data via authenticated Admin API endpoints.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use the Shopify (OAuth) connector via proxy, your AI agent should perform operations like GET /admin/api/2025-10/products.json, POST /admin/api/2025-10/orders.json, GET /admin/api/2025-10/customers.json, PUT /admin/api/2025-10/themes/active.json, and DELETE /admin/api/2025-10/fulfillments/{fulfillment_id}. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection—just call connectors.proxy("shopify", "/admin/api/2025-10/products.json") rather than constructing auth headers yourself. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("shopify", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"shopify-partner":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Shopify Partner",visibility:"beta",vertical:["commerce"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-shopify-partner.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage partner dashboard data via the Partners API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Shopify Partner connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: POST /{org_id}/api/{version}/graphql.json to query dashboard data (e.g., app events, transactions), POST /{org_id}/api/{version}/graphql.json to create or retrieve Partner API clients, and POST /{org_id}/api/{version}/graphql.json for financials or Expert Marketplace data. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API-key auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("shopify-partner", "/{org_id}/api/{version}/graphql.json"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"shopify-store":{hasClient:!0,hasServer:!0,metadata:{audience:["paid"],verticals:["commerce"],displayName:"Shopify Store",logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-shopify.svg",visibility:"eap",authType:"API_KEY",accessType:"app",description:"Provision a Repl-scoped Shopify store"}},shortcut:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Shortcut",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-shortcut.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Access and manage project data like stories, docs, and groups.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Shortcut connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /api/v3/stories to list stories, POST /api/v3/documents to create a doc, GET /api/v3/groups to list teams, PUT /api/v3/documents/{doc-public-id} to update a doc, GET /api/v3/categories to list categories. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection—prefer using: connectors.proxy("shortcut", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"shortcut-api",package_version:"4.1.3-alpha.1"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},signnow:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"SignNow",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-signnow.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Upload, invite, and manage e-signature documents via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the SignNow connector via the proxy pattern. Common useful endpoints include:\n- POST /oauth2/token (request access token)\n- POST /document (upload a document)\n- PUT /document/{document_id} (add fields or update document)\n- POST /document/{document_id}/invite (send a signature invite)\n- Optional: PUT /template/@{document_id}/bulkinvite (send bulk invites)\nAll requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("signnow", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"signnow-sandbox":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"SignNow (Sandbox)",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-signnow-sandbox.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Upload documents, send signature invites, and manage templates",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the SignNow (Sandbox) connector via the proxy pattern to interact with the SignNow API. Common endpoints include: POST /document (upload a document), PUT /document/{document_id} (add fields or update document), POST /template (create a template), POST /invite/{document_id} (send a signature invite), and GET /document/{document_id}/status (track status). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection—simply use connectors.proxy("signnow-sandbox", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},skio:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Skio",visibility:"beta",vertical:["commerce"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-skio.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage subscriptions, orders, lines, and user data via GraphQL.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Skio connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: “GET /v1/graphql” for querying subscriptions, mutations like addSubscriptionLine or updateSubscriptionLine (e.g., POST GraphQL with addSubscriptionLine), and fetching AddressByPk via query. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("skio", "/v1/graphql"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},slab:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Slab",visibility:"beta",vertical:["wiki"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-slab.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Query your team's knowledge hub via Slab's GraphQL API",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Slab connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: POST /graphql to run queries (e.g., query documents, users, posts), GET /posts to list posts, GET /documents/{id} to fetch a document by ID. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("slab", "/graphql") or connectors.proxy("slab", "/posts") or connectors.proxy("slab", "/documents/{id}"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},slack:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Slack",visibility:"ga",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-slack.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Read and write Slack messages via the Web API (not for Events API apps)",blueprint:{agentInstructions:`Use the Slack connector via the proxy pattern. Common useful Slack Web API endpoints include: GET /conversations.list, POST /chat.postMessage, GET /users.list, POST /conversations.inviteShared, and GET /conversations.history. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection\u2014just call connectors.proxy("slack", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON \u2014 call .json() to parse the response body.

SCOPE \u2014 READ THIS BEFORE USING:
- This connector is ONLY for reading from and writing to Slack via the Web API (outbound calls from your app to Slack).
- This connector is NOT for building a Slack application that receives events from Slack. Do NOT use it to:
  * Handle the Slack Events API (message, app_mention, reaction_added, etc.)
  * Handle slash commands, interactive messages, shortcuts, or modals
  * Build a Slack bot that responds to user events
  * Register event subscription URLs or request verification/signing secrets
- If the user wants any of the above, they need a full Slack application with its own signing secret, verification token, and event subscription URL. This connector does NOT provide those \u2014 do NOT ask the user for a Slack signing secret, client secret, or verification token through this connector. Instead, tell the user to:
  1. Create their own Slack app at https://api.slack.com/apps (they own it and control its scopes, event subscriptions, and signing secret).
  2. Add the app's credentials (signing secret, bot token, client secret, etc.) as custom project secrets on their Repl, and read them via environment variables in their code.
  3. Keep using this connector for any outbound Web API calls from that same app if they want OAuth-managed access tokens, OR use the bot token they got from their own app install directly \u2014 but the event-handling side of the bot must run against their own app's signing secret, which lives in project secrets, not in this connector.`,packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"slack-agent":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!0,metadata:{verticals:["communication"],displayName:"Slack Agent",stage:"beta",logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-slack.svg",accessType:"app"}},"slack-agent-builder":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!0,metadata:{verticals:["communication"],displayName:"Slack Agent Builder",stage:"beta",logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-slack.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",accessType:"app"}},"slack-deployed-agent":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Slack Deployed Agent",visibility:"ga",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-slack.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Slack Deployed Agent to access its API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Slack Deployed Agent connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection and refresh. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("slack-deployed-agent", "/endpoint"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"smartlead-ai":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Smartlead.ai",visibility:"beta",vertical:["communication"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-smartlead-ai.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Automate cold-email campaigns, leads, campaigns, and more via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Smartlead.ai connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /campaigns (list campaigns), POST /campaigns (create campaign), GET /campaigns/{id}/leads (list leads), POST /campaigns/{id}/leads (add lead), DELETE /campaigns/{id}/leads/{leadId} (remove lead). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API-key auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("smartlead-ai", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},smartrecruiters:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Smartrecruiters",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-smartrecruiters.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage jobs, applications, candidates, and other HR data via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the SmartRecruiters connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /v1/companies/{companyIdentifier}/postings to list job postings, POST /postings/{uuid}/candidates to create an application, GET /postings/{uuid}/candidates/{candidateId}/status to retrieve application status. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("smartrecruiters", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},smartsheet:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Smartsheet",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-smartsheet.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access and manage sheets, rows, workspaces, users, and update requests.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Smartsheet connector via the proxy pattern. The Smartsheet API is versioned — all paths must include the `/2.0` prefix. Common useful endpoints include: • GET /2.0/sheets/{sheetId} to retrieve a sheet • POST /2.0/sheets/{sheetId}/rows to add rows • PUT /2.0/sheets/{sheetId}/rows to update rows • GET /2.0/workspaces to list accessible workspaces • GET /2.0/users/me to retrieve the current user. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh. Use connectors.proxy("smartsheet", "/2.0/path") to forward requests. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},snapchat:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Snapchat Ads",visibility:"beta",vertical:["streaming","social-media"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-snapchat.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage Snapchat ad campaigns, ad squads, ads, targeting, and reporting",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the connector following the proxy pattern: prefer using connectors.proxy("snapchat", "/campaigns/{campaign_id}/ads") to list ads under a campaign (GET /campaigns/{campaign_id}/ads), connectors.proxy("snapchat", "/adaccounts/{ad_account_id}/ads") to list ads under an ad account (GET /adaccounts/{ad_account_id}/ads), connectors.proxy("snapchat", "/adsquads/{ad_squad_id}/ads") to manage ads under an ad squad (GET /adsquads/{ad_squad_id}/ads or POST /adsquads/{ad_squad_id}/ads to create), connectors.proxy("snapchat", "/ads/{ad_id}") to retrieve or delete a specific ad (GET or DELETE /ads/{ad_id}), connectors.proxy("snapchat", "/{ad_account_id}/get_ads_by_ids") to fetch multiple ads by IDs (POST). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection and refreshing. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"snipe-it":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Snipe-IT",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-snipe-it.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Programmatically manage IT assets, users, locations, and more.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Snipe-IT connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /hardware to list assets, POST /hardware to create assets, GET /users to list users, GET /locations to list locations. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("snipe-it", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},snowflake:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Snowflake",visibility:"alpha",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-snowflake.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Execute SQL statements and manage resources via REST API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'## SDK setup\nUse the Snowflake connector via the proxy pattern. Common useful API endpoints include:\n- POST /api/v2/statements/ to submit SQL\n- GET /api/v2/statements/{statementHandle} to check status\n- POST /api/v2/statements/{statementHandle}/cancel to cancel execution\nAll requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection — use\nconnectors.proxy("snowflake", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object,\nnot parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.\n\n## CRITICAL: Cost discipline (Snowflake bills warehouse compute time + cloud-services)\nSnowflake charges for warehouse seconds while a query runs. A `SELECT *` over a wide\nor fact table keeps the warehouse running far longer than necessary, and a dashboard\nthat re-runs warehouse queries every few seconds — without a cache — can burn\nthousands of dollars per day. Follow these rules on every query:\n- Project exact columns. NEVER `SELECT *` on wide or fact tables. Snowflake is columnar;\n  selecting only the columns you need is one of the largest cost wins available.\n- Use clustering keys. Add `WHERE <cluster_key> >= ...` (or whichever column the table\n  is clustered on) so Snowflake prunes micro-partitions and scans a slice, not the whole\n  table. Without this filter, fact-table reads scan the entire table.\n- Prefer pre-aggregated tables (`*_daily`, `*_summary`) or materialized views over raw\n  event tables.\n- Aggregate on the warehouse — push `GROUP BY`, `SUM`, `COUNT` into SQL. Do NOT stream\n  raw rows to the client and aggregate in JavaScript.\n- Use `INFORMATION_SCHEMA` (and `SHOW`/`DESCRIBE`) for schema discovery rather than\n  running `SELECT *` against the table itself just to see what columns exist.\n- Use a small warehouse (X-Small / Small) for interactive queries; auto-suspend should\n  be enabled so the warehouse stops running when idle.\n- Lean on Snowflake\'s persisted query result cache: identical query text against\n  unchanged source data returns from the global result cache for up to 24 h. This\n  cache is served from cloud services and does NOT need a running warehouse, so\n  exact-repeat reads are effectively free as long as nothing in the underlying\n  tables has changed and the user has the same role / access. Avoid embedding\n  `CURRENT_TIMESTAMP` or other non-deterministic expressions in `WHERE` clauses\n  where you don\'t need to, so identical refreshes can hit it.\n  The app-level response cache (see below) is still worth having on top: it gives\n  you a single TTL knob you control, collapses simultaneous identical requests into\n  one call, and covers near-identical queries (e.g. params that differ only in\n  whitespace or order) that the result cache treats as distinct.\n- For incremental refreshes, persist a high-water-mark cursor (e.g. `last_seen_at`)\n  and filter with `WHERE updated_at > ?` so refresh queries only scan the delta.\n  Snowflake\'s SQL API uses positional `?` placeholders with a separate `bindings`\n  object — not `:name` or `@name`. The request body looks like:\n    { "statement": "SELECT id FROM events WHERE updated_at > ?",\n      "bindings": { "1": { "type": "TIMESTAMP_NTZ", "value": "2026-05-11 10:00:00" } } }\n  Pick the `type` that matches the bound column (TIMESTAMP_LTZ / TIMESTAMP_TZ /\n  TIMESTAMP_NTZ for timestamps; TEXT, FIXED, BOOLEAN, etc. for other types).\n\n## CRITICAL: Cache read-only Snowflake responses in your app\nDo NOT call Snowflake on every page load or every poll cycle. Wrap every **read-only**\nSnowflake-backed route in a database-backed response cache (e.g. a Postgres `api_cache`\ntable). "Read-only" means: dashboard / report / explorer routes that run `SELECT`\nstatements, `SHOW` / `DESCRIBE` / `INFORMATION_SCHEMA` lookups, and other idempotent\nreads.\n\nDo NOT cache:\n- DML statements (`INSERT`, `UPDATE`, `MERGE`, `DELETE`, `TRUNCATE`, `COPY INTO`).\n- DDL statements (`CREATE`, `ALTER`, `DROP`, `GRANT`, `REVOKE`).\n- Statement-control / status endpoints (`POST /api/v2/statements/...`/cancel,\n  `GET /api/v2/statements/{handle}`). These are operational flows whose responses\n  change as Snowflake processes the statement.\n- Anything where the second identical request must still produce a side effect.\n\nCaching a mutating route would silently drop the second execution and return a stale\n"success" — a correctness bug, not a cost win. If a single route can run either\nread-only or mutating SQL (e.g. a generic "execute SQL" endpoint), gate caching on\nthe actual statement: bypass the cache when the parsed statement is anything other\nthan a read.\n\nThe cache key MUST include every dimension that scopes the response, not just the\nroute shape:\n- The connection / connector_config ID (so two different Snowflake connections in the\n  same app never share a cached payload).\n- The org / tenant ID, when the app is multi-tenant.\n- The signed-in user ID, when the route returns user-scoped data or uses user-pass-through\n  credentials (e.g. Snowflake OAuth with per-user roles).\n- The endpoint path.\n- The normalized query / body params.\n\nA key shaped like `${connectionId}:${orgId}:${userId}:${endpoint}:${normalizedParams}`\nis a safe default. A key that is only `${endpoint}:${normalizedParams}` will silently\nserve org A\'s cached Snowflake result to org B on the next request.\n\nMatch the cache TTL to the lowest auto-refresh interval exposed to the user; a 5-minute\nfloor is recommended.\n\n## Auto-refresh / polling floor\nNever **re-run** a dashboard / report / explorer query against Snowflake more often than\nonce every 5 minutes. This floor applies to query-driven refreshes — auto-refresh\nintervals, `refetchInterval`, `setInterval` loops that re-issue the underlying\n`POST /api/v2/statements/` call, etc.\n\nIt does NOT apply to short-lived status polling for an in-flight statement. While an\nasynchronous statement is still running, you should poll\n`GET /api/v2/statements/{statementHandle}` every 1–3 seconds (with reasonable backoff)\nuntil it returns a terminal `resultSetMetaData`/`data` payload or fails — that is\nchecking the status of a single submitted statement, not re-running the dashboard\nquery, so it does not waste warehouse compute and the user is actively waiting on\nthe result.\n\nReal-time dashboards belong on a streaming pipeline + Snowpipe / dynamic table, not\non a polling loop against raw Snowflake tables.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},splitwise:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!0,metadata:{displayName:"Splitwise",visibility:"beta",vertical:["social-media"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-splitwise.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage expenses, friends, groups, and notifications via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Splitwise connector via the proxy pattern to interact with common endpoints such as GET /get_expenses, POST /create_expense, POST /create_friend, GET /get_notifications, and POST /add_user_to_group. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh. Use: connectors.proxy("splitwise", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},spotify:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Spotify",visibility:"deprecated",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-spotify.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access user data and control playback via RESTful API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use the Spotify connector via the proxy pattern, the agent can call common endpoints such as:\n• GET /v1/me/playlists — get current user’s playlists\n• GET /v1/playlists/{playlist_id}/items — get tracks in a playlist\n• GET /v1/me/player — get current playback state\n• PUT /v1/me/player/play — start/resume playback\n• PUT /v1/me/player/pause — pause playback\nRequests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Use connectors.proxy("spotify", "/path") for all requests. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},sproutsocial:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Sprout Social",visibility:"alpha",vertical:["social-media"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-sproutsocial.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Access and manage social profiles, analytics, posts, and media.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Sprout Social connector via the proxy pattern to interact with key endpoints. Common API calls include: GET /v1/metadata/client, GET /v1/{customerID}/metadata/customer, POST /v1/{customerID}/media/, and GET /v1/{customerID}/metadata/customer/tags. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection—simply use connectors.proxy("sproutsocial", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},squarespace:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Squarespace",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-squarespace.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage commerce and site data via OAuth-protected API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use the Squarespace connector via the proxy pattern, use common endpoints such as: GET /1.0/authorization/website, GET /1.0/commerce/products, GET /1.0/commerce/orders, GET /1.0/commerce/inventory, and GET /1.0/commerce/profiles. The AI agent should send requests proxied through the SDK, where OAuth tokens are automatically injected and refreshed. For example, prefer using: connectors.proxy("squarespace", "/1.0/commerce/orders"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},squareup:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Squareup",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-squareup.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Squareup to authorize and manage seller accounts via OAuth2.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Squareup connector via the proxy pattern to perform OAuth and seller-account operations. Common endpoints include: GET /oauth2/authorize, POST /oauth2/token, POST /oauth2/revoke, and POST /oauth2/token/status. Requests are automatically proxied through the SDK with injected and refreshed OAuth tokens. Use connectors.proxy("squareup", "/oauth2/authorize") (or other paths) for each call. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"squareup-sandbox":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Squareup (Sandbox)",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-squareup-sandbox.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage sandbox OAuth flows and test API calls.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Squareup (Sandbox) connector via the proxy pattern to interact with key endpoints such as: POST /oauth2/authorize, POST /oauth2/token (ObtainToken), POST /oauth2/revoke (RevokeToken), GET /v2/locations, and POST /v2/payments. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth injection. Use: connectors.proxy("squareup-sandbox", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},stackexchange:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Stack Exchange",visibility:"beta",vertical:["wiki","ticketing"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-stackexchange.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access questions, answers, users, and more via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use the Stack Exchange connector via the proxy pattern, your agent can call endpoints like GET /questions, GET /questions/{ids}/answers, POST /questions/{id}/answers/add, GET /users/{ids}, and GET /me via connectors.proxy("stackexchange", "/path"). Authentication is handled automatically by the SDK—OAuth tokens are injected and refreshed behind the scenes. Prefer using connectors.proxy("stackexchange", "/path") for all requests. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},statista:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Statista",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-statista.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Access verified market, industry, and consumer data via REST API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Statista connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /api-reference/discovery (Discovery API for searching statistics), GET /api-reference/data/{statisticId} (Data API for chart values and metadata), POST /api-reference/mcp (Research AI/MCP for AI-driven insights). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection in headers. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("statista", "/api-reference/..." ). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},strava:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Strava (Mobile)",visibility:"beta",vertical:["social-media"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-strava.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access athlete and activity data via OAuth2 on mobile platforms.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use the Strava (Mobile) connector, your AI agent should call commonly used endpoints such as: GET /api/v3/athlete, GET /api/v3/athlete/activities, POST /oauth/token, POST /oauth/deauthorize (all proxied via HTTP).  Use connectors.proxy("strava", "/api/v3/athlete"), connectors.proxy("strava", "/api/v3/athlete/activities"), connectors.proxy("strava", "/oauth/token"), or connectors.proxy("strava", "/oauth/deauthorize").  Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh.  Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"strava-web":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Strava (Web)",visibility:"beta",vertical:["social-media"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-strava-web.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access athlete data, activities, segments, clubs, and uploads",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use the Strava (Web) connector, your AI agent should issue proxied requests to key API endpoints such as: GET /api/v3/athlete, GET /api/v3/activities/{id}, POST /api/v3/activities (upload), POST /oauth/token (refresh), and POST /oauth/deauthorize. Use the SDK’s proxy pattern to handle automatic auth injection: connectors.proxy("strava-web", "/v3/athlete"). Remember requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},stripe:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!0,metadata:{verticals:["commerce"],displayName:"Stripe",logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-stripe.svg",stage:"beta",authType:"API_KEY",accessType:"app"}},"stripe-agent-sandbox":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!0,metadata:{verticals:["commerce"],displayName:"Stripe Agent Sandbox",logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-stripe.svg",stage:"beta"}},"stripe-app":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Stripe App",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-stripe-app.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage Stripe entities (accounts, payments, customers, subscriptions).",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Stripe App connector via the proxy pattern to interact with Stripe’s OAuth-authenticated API endpoints. Common useful endpoints include GET /v1/customers, POST /v1/payment_intents, GET /v1/invoices, POST /v1/subscriptions, and GET /v1/balance. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection — simply call connectors.proxy("stripe-app", "/v1/customers") (or corresponding path). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"stripe-app-sandbox":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Stripe App (Sandbox)",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-stripe-app-sandbox.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage customers, charges, refunds, and subscriptions (test mode)",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Stripe App (Sandbox) OAuth2 connector via the proxy pattern. Common useful endpoints include: GET /v1/customers (list customers), POST /v1/customers (create customer), GET /v1/charges (list charges), POST /v1/payment_intents (create payment intent), POST /v1/refunds (create refund). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection. For calls, use: connectors.proxy("stripe-app-sandbox", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"stripe-express":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Stripe Express",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-stripe-express.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Stripe Express to onboard and manage Express connected accounts.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Stripe Express connector via the proxy pattern to manage Express Connected Accounts. Common useful endpoints include: POST /v1/accounts (create account), POST /v1/account_links (create onboarding link), POST /v1/accounts/{ACCOUNT_ID}/login_links (create login link), GET /v1/accounts/{ACCOUNT_ID} (retrieve account), and POST /v1/accounts/{ACCOUNT_ID}/persons (add person). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection—simply call connectors.proxy("stripe-express", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},supabase:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Supabase",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools","file-storage"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-supabase.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Access and manipulate your project database via RESTful endpoints.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Supabase connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API calls. Common endpoints include GET /rest/v1/{table} for listing rows, POST /rest/v1/{table} to insert, PATCH /rest/v1/{table}?id=eq.{id} to update, DELETE /rest/v1/{table}?id=eq.{id} to delete, and POST /auth/v1/token for refreshing tokens. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("supabase", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"@supabase/supabase-js",package_version:"latest"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"survey-monkey":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"SurveyMonkey",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-survey-monkey.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access surveys, collectors, responses, contacts, and user info",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the SurveyMonkey connector via the proxy pattern. Common useful endpoints include: GET /surveys to list surveys, GET /surveys/{survey_id}/responses to fetch responses, GET /collectors to list collectors, GET /contacts to retrieve contacts, and GET /users/me to get authenticated user details. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 authentication injection—use connectors.proxy("survey-monkey", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},tailscale:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Tailscale",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-tailscale.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Connect to Tailscale to manage your tailnet via API key authentication.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Tailscale connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API interactions. Common endpoints: GET /api/v2/tailnet/{tailnet}/devices, GET /api/v2/tailnet/{tailnet}/keys, GET /api/v2/tailnet/{tailnet}/acl, POST /api/v2/tailnet/{tailnet}/keys, PATCH /api/v2/tailnet/{tailnet}/settings. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("tailscale", "/api/v2/tailnet/{tailnet}/devices"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},tally:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Tally",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-tally.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Connect to Tally to programmatically manage forms and submissions.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Tally connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: POST /forms to create a form, GET /forms to list forms, GET /forms/{formId}/submissions to fetch submissions. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("tally", "/forms"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},teamleader:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Teamleader Focus",visibility:"beta",vertical:["accounting","crm"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-teamleader.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage CRM entities: companies, contacts, deals, and projects",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Teamleader Focus connector via the proxy pattern. Common endpoints include: GET /companies.list, POST /contacts.create, GET /deals.list, POST /projects-v2.create, GET /custom-field-definitions.list. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("teamleader", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},teamtailor:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Teamtailor",visibility:"beta",vertical:["ats"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-teamtailor.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Retrieve and manage recruitment data via API proxy.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Teamtailor connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /jobs to fetch job listings, POST /candidates to create a candidate, GET /candidates/{id} to retrieve candidate details, PATCH /jobs/{id} to update a job, GET /departments or custom-fields endpoints as needed. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("teamtailor", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},teamwork:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Teamwork",visibility:"beta",vertical:["ticketing"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-teamwork.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage projects, tasks, users, and more via its REST API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use this connector, the agent can call common endpoints such as GET /projects/api/v3/projects.json (list projects), GET /projects/api/v3/tasks.json (list tasks), POST /projects/api/v3/projects.json (create project), PATCH /projects/api/v3/tasks/{taskId}.json (update task), and GET /projects/api/v3/people.json (list users). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 auth injection — use connectors.proxy("teamwork", "/path"). For example: connectors.proxy("teamwork", "/projects/api/v3/projects.json"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},terraform:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Terraform",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-terraform.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage infrastructure via Terraform Cloud/Enterprise API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Terraform connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /api/v2/account/details, POST /api/v2/runs, GET /api/v2/workspaces/{workspace_id}/runs. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("terraform", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"@skorfmann/terraform-cloud",package_version:"1.15.0"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"thrivecart-oauth":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"ThriveCart",visibility:"beta",vertical:["commerce"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-thrivecart-oauth.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access and manage ThriveCart account data securely.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the ThriveCart connector via the proxy pattern. Common endpoints include: GET /products to list products, POST /external/subscribe to create event subscriptions (webhooks), GET /orders or GET /transactions for retrieving order data via the API reference. All requests should be proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection by calling connectors.proxy("thrivecart-oauth", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},ticktick:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"TickTick",visibility:"beta",vertical:["ticketing"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-ticktick.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to TickTick to manage tasks, projects, and user info via OAuth2.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the TickTick connector via the proxy pattern. Common useful endpoints include GET /open/v1/project, GET /open/v1/task, POST /open/v1/task (create task), GET /open/v1/user/info, and DELETE /open/v1/task/{id}. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection—use connectors.proxy("ticktick", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"tiktok-accounts":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"TikTok Accounts",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["social-media"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-tiktok-accounts.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access and manage TikTok business account details.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the TikTok Accounts connector via the proxy pattern to interact with TikTok’s Business/Marketing API. Common endpoints include: (1) GET /advertiser/info/ to retrieve account details; (2) GET /campaign/get/ for campaign data; (3) GET /adgroup/get/ for ad group information; (4) GET /ad/get/ for ad performance metrics. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection and refresh. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("tiktok-accounts", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"tiktok-ads":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"TikTok Ads",visibility:"beta",vertical:["social-media"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-tiktok-ads.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage campaigns, ads, ad groups, advertisers, and insights via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the TikTok Ads connector via the proxy pattern to interact with common API endpoints such as: GET /campaign/get/, POST /campaign/create/, GET /adgroup/get/, GET /ads/get/, GET /report/integrated/get/. The connector handles OAuth2 tokens transparently, so no manual auth handling is needed. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("tiktok-ads", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"tiktok-personal":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"TikTok",visibility:"beta",vertical:["social-media"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-tiktok-personal.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access user profile, videos, and content posting via OAuth2.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the TikTok connector via the proxy pattern. Common endpoints include: GET /user/profile, GET /videos/list, POST /video/upload, PUT /video/update. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh. To call an endpoint, use: connectors.proxy("tiktok-personal", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},timely:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Timely",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-timely.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Timely to access and manage time-tracking data via OAuth2.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Timely connector via the proxy pattern. Common useful endpoints include: GET /1.1/:account_id/events, POST /1.1/:account_id/forecasts, POST /1.1/:account_id/day_properties, GET /1.1/:account_id/users, POST /1.1/:account_id/webhooks. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("timely", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},tldv:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"tl;dv",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-tldv.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Import meetings, fetch transcripts, highlights, and manage interactions.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the tl;dv connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated requests. Common endpoints include: POST /v1alpha1/meetings/import to import a meeting from a URL, GET /v1alpha1/meetings/{meetingId}/highlights to retrieve meeting highlights, GET /v1alpha1/meetings/{meetingId}/transcript to fetch the transcript, GET /v1alpha1/meetings/list (or similar) to list meetings. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API-key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("tldv", "/v1alpha1/..." ). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},todoist:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Todoist",visibility:"alpha",vertical:["ticketing"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-todoist.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Todoist to manage tasks, projects, labels, and sections.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Todoist connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /api/v1/tasks to list tasks, GET /api/v1/projects to list projects, GET /api/v1/labels to list labels, GET /api/v1/sections?project_id={project_id} to list sections in a project, POST /api/v1/tasks to create a task. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("todoist", "/api/v1/tasks"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"@doist/todoist-api-typescript",package_version:"3.0.3"}]},exampleUsage:{javascript:[{name:"get-all-projects",snippet:'import { ReplitConnectors } from "@replit/connectors-sdk";\n\nconst connectors = new ReplitConnectors();\nconst response = await connectors.proxy("todoist", "/api/v1/projects");\n\nif (!response.ok) {\n  const text = await response.text().catch(() => "");\n  throw new Error(`HTTP ${response.status}: ${text}`);\n}\n\nconst body = await response.json();\n\nif (!Array.isArray(body.results) || body.results.length === 0) {\n  throw new Error("Expected at least one project");\n}\n\nexport const result = { count: body.results.length, first: body.results[0]?.name };'},{name:"create-task",snippet:'import { ReplitConnectors } from "@replit/connectors-sdk";\n\nconst connectors = new ReplitConnectors();\nconst response = await connectors.proxy("todoist", "/api/v1/tasks", {\n  method: "POST",\n  headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },\n  body: JSON.stringify({ content: "Debug REPL test task - safe to delete" }),\n});\n\nif (!response.ok) {\n  const text = await response.text().catch(() => "");\n  throw new Error(`HTTP ${response.status}: ${text}`);\n}\n\nconst body = await response.json();\n\nif (!body?.id) {\n  throw new Error("Expected task id in response");\n}\n\nexport const result = { id: body.id, content: body.content };'}]}},links:{webUrl:"https://todoist.com",apiDocsUrl:"https://developer.todoist.com/api/v1"},integrationKeys:{nango:"todoist"}}},torii:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Torii",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-torii.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Upload files and sync user and license data via its SaaS management API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Torii connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: POST /v1.0/files/upload to upload a custom integration file, GET /v1.0/files/url to get an upload URL, PUT /v1.0/services/sync/custom to sync the uploaded data. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("torii", "/v1.0/files/upload"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"@toriihq/torii-mcp",package_version:"0.0.8"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},tremendous:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Tremendous",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-tremendous.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Send rewards, manage orders, funding sources, campaigns, and reports.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Tremendous connector via the proxy pattern to interact with common endpoints such as:\n• GET /funding_sources — list available funding sources\n• POST /orders — create a reward order for a recipient\n• GET /orders/{id} — retrieve order details\n• POST /reports — generate a rewards report\n• GET /reports/{id} — retrieve a generated report\nRequests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("tremendous", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"tremendous-sandbox":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Tremendous (Sandbox)",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-tremendous-sandbox.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Send test rewards, orders, products, campaigns, and funding sources",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use the Tremendous (Sandbox) connector via the proxy pattern, you can call the most common endpoints such as GET /orders, POST /orders, GET /products, GET /funding_sources, and GET /campaigns. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh. Use connectors.proxy("tremendous-sandbox", "/orders") and similar for other paths. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},tripo3d:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Tripo3D",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-tripo3d.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Generate 3D models from text and images; texture, rig, and animate meshes.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Tripo3D connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Tripo3D is an async task-based API: submit a task, then poll for results. Common endpoints: POST /task (submit a new generation task — supports types like text_to_model, image_to_model, multiview_to_model, texture_model, animate_rig, convert_model), GET /task/{task_id} (poll task status and retrieve outputs once status is "success"). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("tripo3d", "/task"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{},exampleUsage:{javascript:[{name:"verify-auth",snippet:'import { ReplitConnectors } from "@replit/connectors-sdk";\n\nconst connectors = new ReplitConnectors();\n// Polling a well-formed but non-existent task_id verifies auth without consuming credits.\nconst response = await connectors.proxy("tripo3d", "/task/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000");\n\nif (response.status === 401 || response.status === 403) {\n  const text = await response.text().catch(() => "");\n  throw new Error(`Auth failed: HTTP ${response.status}: ${text}`);\n}\n\nconst body = await response.json().catch(() => ({}));\n\nexport const result = { status: response.status, code: body?.code, message: body?.message };'}]}},links:{webUrl:"https://www.tripo3d.ai",apiDocsUrl:"https://docs.tripo3d.ai/get-started/quick-start.html"}}},tsheetsteam:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"TSheets",visibility:"beta",vertical:["hris"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-tsheetsteam.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to TSheets to access and manage time-tracking data via OAuth2.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the TSheets connector via the proxy pattern to perform API calls—requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Common useful endpoints include: GET /current_user, GET /timesheets, POST /timesheets, GET /reports/current_totals, GET /last_modified_timestamps. Prefer using connectors.proxy("tsheetsteam", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},tumblr:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Tumblr",visibility:"beta",vertical:["social-media","communication"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-tumblr.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Tumblr to access blogs, posts, and user info via OAuth2.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Tumblr connector via the proxy pattern to call common endpoints such as GET /blog/{blog-identifier}/posts, GET /user/info, POST /blog/{blog-identifier}/post, and GET /blog/{blog-identifier}/avatar. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection and token refresh. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("tumblr", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"twenty-crm":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Twenty CRM",visibility:"beta",vertical:["crm"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-twenty-crm.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage CRM records, metadata, and schema via REST or GraphQL.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Twenty CRM connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /rest/people to list people, POST /rest/companies to create a company, GET /rest/metadata/objects to fetch metadata schema. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("twenty-crm", "/rest/people"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"twenty-crm-self-hosted":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Twenty CRM (Self Hosted)",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["crm"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-twenty-crm-self-hosted.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage CRM records, metadata, and schemas.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Twenty CRM (self-hosted) connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /rest/people to list people, POST /rest/companies to create a company, GET /rest/metadata/objects to fetch metadata, PATCH /rest/people/{id} to update a person, DELETE /rest/companies/{id} to remove a company. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API-key auth injected in headers. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("twenty-crm-self-hosted", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},twilio:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!0,metadata:{verticals:["communication"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-twilio.svg",stage:"ga",authType:"API_KEY"}},twinfield:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Twinfield",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-twinfield.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access and manage accounting data via OAuth2-secured SOAP services.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use this connector via the proxy pattern to call Twinfield’s OAuth2-secured SOAP web services. Commonly used endpoints include: POST /webservices/finder.asmx (Finder), POST /webservices/PeriodService.svc (PeriodService), POST /webservices/BankStatementService.svc (BankStatementService), POST /webservices/TransactionBlockedValueService.svc (TransactionBlockedValueService), and POST /webservices/BudgetService.svc (BudgetService). Include AccessToken and CompanyCode in SOAP headers and select the correct cluster URL after validating the access token. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection—use connectors.proxy("twinfield", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},twitch:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Twitch",visibility:"beta",vertical:["social-media","streaming"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-twitch.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access live streams, user profiles, videos, clips, and more.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Twitch connector via the proxy pattern to interact with common Helix API endpoints. For example, you can retrieve the current live streams with GET /helix/streams, get user information with GET /helix/users, fetch VODs using GET /helix/videos, or create a clip via POST /helix/clips. Remember that requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection—simply use connectors.proxy("twitch", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},typeform:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Typeform",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-typeform.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Typeform to create and manage forms and retrieve responses.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use the Typeform connector via the proxy pattern, leverage common endpoints such as: GET /forms (list forms), POST /forms (create a form), GET /forms/{form_id} (retrieve form), PATCH /forms/{form_id} (update form), and GET /forms/{form_id}/responses (retrieve form responses). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh. Use connectors.proxy("typeform", "/path") to make calls. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},typefully:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Typefully",visibility:"beta",vertical:["communication","social-media"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-typefully.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Programmatically create, schedule, and publish social media drafts.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Typefully connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /v2/social-sets to list available social sets, POST /v2/social-sets/{id}/drafts to create or schedule drafts, GET /v2/social-sets/{id}/drafts/{draft_id} to retrieve a draft, and POST /v2/social-sets/{id}/media/upload to upload media. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("typefully", "/v2/social-sets/{id}/drafts"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},uber:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Uber",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-uber.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access driver data, trips, payments, and OAuth2 token management.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Uber connector via the proxy pattern to interact with the Uber API. Common endpoints include:\n• GET /v1/partners/me — retrieve the driver profile\n• GET /v1/partners/trips — list driver trips\n• GET /v1/partners/payments — fetch driver payments\n• POST /v2/token — exchange authorization code or refresh token for access token\n• GET /oauth/v2/authorize — initiate OAuth2 authorization flow\nAll requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Use connectors.proxy("uber", "/path") to send API calls. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"ukg-pro-wfm":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"UKG Pro (Workforce Management)",visibility:"beta",vertical:["hris"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-ukg-pro-wfm.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Authenticate and access WFM APIs via OAuth2.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use this connector, an AI agent should call the following common endpoints: GET /employees/{employeeId}/schedule to fetch an employee’s schedule; GET /timecards/{employeeId} to retrieve timecard data; POST /timestamps to punch in/out; GET /accruals/{employeeId} to get leave balances. Use the proxy pattern: connectors.proxy("ukg-pro-wfm", "/path"). Authentication is injected and refreshed automatically through the SDK proxy. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},unipile:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Unipile",visibility:"beta",vertical:["crm"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-unipile.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Unify messaging, email, and calendar providers in one API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Unipile connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /api/v1/accounts (list connected accounts), GET /api/v1/chats/{chat_id}/messages (retrieve messages), POST /api/v1/chats/{chat_id}/messages (send a message). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("unipile", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"unipile-node-sdk",package_version:"latest"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},upsales:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Upsales",visibility:"beta",vertical:["crm"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-upsales.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Access CRM and marketing automation data via REST API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Upsales connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API access. Common endpoints: GET /crm/contacts, GET /crm/opportunities, POST /marketingAutomation/leads, PATCH /crm/opportunities/{id}, DELETE /crm/contacts/{id}. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("upsales", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},valley:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Valley",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-valley.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Connect to Valley to manage and retrieve campaign data via its API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Valley connector via the proxy pattern to interact with the Valley API. Common endpoints include GET /v1/campaigns/get-all to fetch campaigns, potentially POST /v1/campaigns to create new campaigns, and GET /v1/campaigns/{id} to retrieve a specific campaign. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("valley", "/v1/campaigns/get-all"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},vercel:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Vercel",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-vercel.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Manage deployments, projects, domains, and artifacts via Vercel API",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Vercel connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /v8/deployments to list deployments; POST /v9/projects to create a project; GET /v2/domains to list domains; DELETE /v6/projects/{projectId} to delete a project. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection in headers. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("vercel", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"@vercel/sdk",package_version:"latest"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},vimeo:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Vimeo",visibility:"beta",vertical:["streaming"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-vimeo.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Authenticate and call Vimeo API endpoints securely.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Vimeo connector via the proxy pattern by calling connectors.proxy("vimeo", "/path"). Common useful endpoints include:\n• GET /me — retrieve authenticated user profile\n• GET /videos — list videos in the authenticated user’s account\n• POST /videos — upload a new video (if supported)\n• GET /oauth/authorize — initiate OAuth authorization flow\n• POST /oauth/access_token — exchange code or refresh token for access token\nAll requests are proxied through the SDK, with OAuth tokens injected and refreshed automatically. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},wakatime:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Wakatime",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-wakatime.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access coding activity stats, heartbeats, durations, and projects",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Wakatime connector via the proxy pattern to interact with key endpoints: GET /api/v1/users/current/heartbeats, GET /api/v1/users/current/stats/:range, POST /api/v1/users/current/external_durations, GET /api/v1/users/current/projects. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("wakatime", "/api/v1/users/current/heartbeats") etc. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"wave-accounting":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Wave Accounting",visibility:"beta",vertical:["accounting"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-wave-accounting.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage invoices, items, workspaces, and related resources via OAuth2.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Wave Accounting connector via the proxy pattern. Commonly used endpoints include:\n• GET /resources/accountingInvoice — list invoices\n• POST /resources/accountingInvoice — create invoice\n• GET /resources/accountingInvoiceItem — list invoice items (and POST /resources/accountingInvoiceItem, PATCH /resources/accountingInvoiceItem/:id for invoice item management)\n• GET /resources/genericWorkspace — list workspaces\nRequests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection and refresh. Use connectors.proxy("wave-accounting", "/path") for all calls. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},wealthbox:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Wealthbox",visibility:"beta",vertical:["crm"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-wealthbox.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Wealthbox to interact with CRM data via RESTful endpoints.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Wealthbox connector via the proxy pattern. Common useful endpoints include GET /v1/contacts, GET /v1/me, GET /v1/tasks, GET /v1/opportunities, and GET /v1/projects. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 access token injection and refresh. Use connectors.proxy("wealthbox", "/path") in your requests. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},webex:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Webex",visibility:"beta",vertical:["communication"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-webex.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Webex to manage meetings, messages, spaces, and memberships.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Webex connector via the proxy pattern to interact with Cisco Webex APIs. Common useful endpoints include: POST /v1/meetings (create meeting), GET /v1/meetings (list meetings), POST /v1/messages (post message in a space), POST /v1/memberships (invite user to space), and GET /v1/people (search for users). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("webex", "/path") for making calls. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},webflow:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Webflow",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-webflow.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Webflow to manage sites, CMS, assets, forms, pages, and more.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Webflow connector via the proxy pattern to access key Webflow Data API endpoints such as GET /sites to list sites, GET /collections/{collection_id}/items to list CMS items, POST /sites/{site_id}/assets to create an asset, GET /forms/{form_id}/submissions to retrieve form submissions, and PUT /pages/{page_id}/custom_code to update page custom code. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("webflow", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"whatsapp-business":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"WhatsApp Business",visibility:"beta",vertical:["communication"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-whatsapp-business.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Send and receive messages via Meta’s Cloud API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the WhatsApp Business connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /v{version}/{phone-number-id}/messages to list messages, POST /v{version}/{phone-number-id}/messages to send a message, GET /v{version}/{whatsapp-business-account-id}/message_templates to retrieve templates, GET /v{version}/{phone-number-id}/media to list media, POST /v{version}/{phone-number-id}/media to upload media. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("whatsapp-business", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"whatsapp",package_version:"latest"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},whoop:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Whoop",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-whoop.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access user fitness, sleep, recovery, and cycle data via OAuth2.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Whoop OAuth2 connector via the proxy pattern. Common endpoints include: GET /v2/user/profile/basic, GET /v2/user/measurement/body, GET /v2/cycle, GET /v2/recovery, GET /v2/cycle/{cycleId}/sleep. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic injection and refreshing of authorization tokens. Use the pattern: connectors.proxy("whoop", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},whop:{hasClient:!0,hasServer:!0,metadata:{audience:["paid"],verticals:["commerce"],displayName:"Whop",logoUrl:"https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?domain=whop.com&sz=128",visibility:"eap",authType:"API_KEY",accessType:"app",description:"Create payment plans, checkout configs, and manage Whop subscriptions"}},"wildix-pbx":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Wildix PBX",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-wildix-pbx.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Programmatically manage PBX system features via its WebAPI and OAuth2.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Wildix PBX connector via the proxy pattern to call commonly used endpoints such as GET /pbx/users, POST /pbx/call, GET /pbx/callHistory, POST /pbx/voicemail, and GET /pbx/devices. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refreshing. Use connectors.proxy("wildix-pbx", "/path") to make calls. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},wise:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!0,metadata:{displayName:"Wise",visibility:"beta",vertical:["banking"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-wise.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Access payment, transfer, balance, quote, and recipient APIs.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Wise connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /v1/profiles/{profileId}/balances to list balances, POST /v2/profiles/{profileId}/balance-movements to initiate balance movement, POST /v2/profiles/{profileId}/quotes to create a quote, POST /v1/recipients to create a recipient, POST /v1/transfers to create a transfer. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API-key auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("wise", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},wiseagent:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Wiseagent",visibility:"beta",vertical:["crm"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-wiseagent.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage contacts, team, properties, calls, and tasks via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the WiseAgent connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints include: GET /http/webconnect.asp?requestType=getContacts, GET /http/webconnect.asp?requestType=getTeam, POST /http/webconnect.asp?requestType=webcontact, GET /http/webconnect.asp?requestType=getProperties (or other similar property endpoints), POST /http/webconnect.asp?requestType=calls. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth token injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("wiseagent", "/http/webconnect.asp?requestType=... "). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},wiza:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Wiza",visibility:"beta",vertical:["crm"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-wiza.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Enrich and retrieve B2B contact and company data from LinkedIn",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Wiza connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API access. Common endpoints: POST /api/lists to create an enrichment list, GET /api/lists/{id} to check list status, GET /api/lists/{id}/contacts to retrieve enriched contacts, POST /v1/enrich to perform individual enrichments. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic API key injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("wiza", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},wordpress:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"WordPress",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-wordpress.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Interact with site content and user data via OAuth2-secured REST API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the WordPress connector via the proxy pattern to interact with WordPress.com’s OAuth2-protected REST API; common useful endpoints include: GET /sites/{site_id}/posts, POST /sites/{site_id}/posts/new, GET /me, GET /sites/{site_id}/comments, and GET /sites/{site_id}/media. Requests are automatically proxied through the SDK with OAuth2 token injection and refresh handled for you. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("wordpress", "/sites/{site_id}/posts") (or similar paths). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"workable-oauth":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Workable",visibility:"beta",vertical:["ats"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-workable-oauth.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Interact with recruiting data—jobs, candidates, and related resources.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Workable (OAuth) connector via the proxy pattern. Common endpoints include: GET /spi/v3/jobs, GET /spi/v3/jobs/{shortcode}, GET /​candidates/{id}, GET /jobs/{shortcode}/questions, and GET /jobs/{shortcode}/custom_attributes. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection—use connectors.proxy("workable-oauth", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},workato:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!0,metadata:{verticals:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-workato.svg",stage:"ga",authType:"API_KEY"}},"workday-oauth":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Workday",visibility:"beta",vertical:["hris"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-workday-oauth.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access Workday REST APIs using automatic OAuth2 token injection.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use this connector, the AI agent should invoke common Workday REST API endpoints—e.g., GET /workers, GET /workers/{id}/inboxTasks, GET /purchase_orders or GET /purchase_orders/{id}, and GET /ccx/service/customreport2/{tenant}/{report_path}. Use the connector via the proxy pattern: connectors.proxy("workday-oauth", "/workers"), connectors.proxy("workday-oauth", "/workers/{id}/inboxTasks"), and so on. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("workday-oauth", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},workos:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"WorkOS",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-workos.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Enterprise identity services like SSO, SCIM, and audit logging",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the WorkOS connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: GET /sso/list_connections (list SSO connections), POST /sso/authorize (get authorization URL), GET /sso/get_profile (retrieve user profile), GET /directory_users (list directory users), POST /audit_logs/events (create audit log event). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("workos", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{javascript:[{package_name:"@workos-inc/node",package_version:"8.4.0"}]}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},wrike:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Wrike",visibility:"beta",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-wrike.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage tasks, folders, projects, webhooks, and user data via API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Wrike connector via the proxy pattern. Common endpoints include: GET /tasks, GET /folders, GET /projects (via similar resource paths), GET /contacts (e.g. GET /contacts?me=true), and POST /webhooks. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("wrike", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},x:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"X",visibility:"ga",vertical:["social-media"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-x.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Access public posts, users, spaces, direct messages, lists, and trends.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the X connector via the proxy pattern to interact with X API v2 endpoints: GET /2/users/by/username/{username} (lookup a user by username), GET /2/users/{id} (lookup a user by id), GET /2/users/{id}/tweets (list a user\'s tweets), GET /2/tweets/{id} (lookup a tweet by id), GET /2/tweets/search/recent (search recent tweets), GET /2/tweets/search/stream (filtered stream), POST /2/tweets/search/stream/rules (manage stream rules). All requests are proxied through connectors.proxy("x", "/path") with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("x", "/2/users/by/username/xdevelopers"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{},exampleUsage:{javascript:[{name:"lookup-user-by-username",snippet:'import { ReplitConnectors } from "@replit/connectors-sdk";\n\nconst connectors = new ReplitConnectors();\nconst response = await connectors.proxy("x", "/2/users/by/username/xdevelopers");\n\nif (!response.ok) {\n  const text = await response.text().catch(() => "");\n  throw new Error(`HTTP ${response.status}: ${text}`);\n}\n\nconst body = await response.json();\n\nif (!body?.data?.id || !body?.data?.username) {\n  throw new Error("Expected user data with id and username in response");\n}\n\nexport const result = { id: body.data.id, username: body.data.username, name: body.data.name };'}]}},links:{webUrl:"https://x.com",apiDocsUrl:"https://docs.x.com"}}},xai:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"xAI",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-xai.svg",authType:"API_KEY",description:"Access Grok models for chat, vision, image generation, and management",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the xAI connector via the proxy pattern for authenticated API requests. Common endpoints: POST /v1/chat/completions to generate chat responses; POST /v1/images/generate for image creation; POST /v1/vision/analyze for image understanding; POST /auth/teams/{teamId}/api-keys on the management API to create API keys. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("xai", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},xero:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Xero",visibility:"beta",vertical:["accounting"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-xero.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage accounting, invoices, contacts, payments, and assets.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Xero connector via the proxy pattern by calling connectors.proxy("xero", "/path"). Common useful endpoints include: GET /connections (list connected organisations), GET /accounting/invoices (retrieve invoices), POST /accounting/contacts (create contacts), GET /accounting/accounts (list chart of accounts), and GET /assets (list assets). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 authentication and token injection. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},yahoo:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Yahoo",visibility:"beta",vertical:["social-media"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-yahoo.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Authorize via OAuth 2.0 (OpenID Connect) and access user profile and mail.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Yahoo connector via the proxy pattern to perform OAuth 2.0 flows and API calls. Common endpoints include: 1) GET /oauth2/request_auth (authorization endpoint), 2) POST /oauth2/get_token (token exchange), 3) POST /oauth2/revoke (token revocation), 4) GET /openid/v1/userinfo (retrieve user profile). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic token injection and refresh, e.g. connectors.proxy("yahoo", "/get_token"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},yandex:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Yandex",visibility:"beta",vertical:["social-media"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-yandex.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access user data and Yandex services via OAuth2-protected APIs.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Yandex connector via the proxy pattern to interact with Yandex services. Common endpoints include: GET /v1/pages (Wiki pages retrieval), GET /v2/web/search (Web search), POST /oauth/token (obtain access tokens), GET /oauth/authorize (initiate authorization flow), and GET /endpoints (list Yandex Cloud service endpoints). All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection. Use connectors.proxy("yandex", "/path") to send requests. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},youtube:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"YouTube",visibility:"ga",vertical:["communication"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-youtube.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to YouTube to interact with videos, channels, playlists, and more.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the YouTube connector via the proxy pattern. Proxy through common endpoints like GET /videos, GET /search, POST /playlists, PUT /subscriptions, DELETE /playlistItems. Remember that requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("youtube", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""},integrationKeys:{nango:"youtube"}}},zapier:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Zapier",visibility:"beta",vertical:["developer-tools"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-zapier.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Retrieve and manage user Zaps and workflows via OAuth2.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Zapier connector via the proxy pattern. Common endpoints include: GET /zaps (list a user’s Zaps), POST /zaps (create a new Zap), GET /zaps/{zap_id} (retrieve Zap details), PATCH or POST /zaps/{zap_id} (update a Zap), DELETE /zaps/{zap_id} (delete a Zap). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection. Prefer using: connectors.proxy("zapier", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"zapier-nla":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Zapier NLA",visibility:"disabled",vertical:["other"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-zapier-nla.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"List and execute natural-language-triggered actions via Zapier.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'To use this connector via the proxy pattern, the most common API endpoints are: GET /api/v1/dynamic/exposed to list exposed actions, POST /api/v1/dynamic/exposed/<ACTION_ID>/execute to perform an action with instructions, GET /api/v1/check to validate an access or refresh token. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection, so use connectors.proxy("zapier-nla", "/path"). Prefer using: connectors.proxy("zapier-nla", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},zendesk:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Zendesk",visibility:"alpha",vertical:["ticketing"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-zendesk.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Create, update, list tickets and users via Support API.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use this connector to interact with Zendesk Support APIs via proxies. Common endpoints include: POST /api/v2/tickets to create a ticket; PUT /api/v2/tickets/update_many to update multiple tickets; GET /api/v2/users to list users; POST /api/v2/oauth/tokens to generate OAuth access tokens; GET /api/v2/tickets to list tickets. Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection — use connectors.proxy("zendesk", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"zendesk-sell":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Zendesk Sell",visibility:"beta",vertical:["crm"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-zendesk-sell.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Manage leads, contacts, deals, and more via OAuth2 proxy.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Zendesk Sell connector via the proxy pattern. You can invoke common endpoints such as GET /v2/leads, GET /v2/contacts, POST /v3/deals/search, GET /api/sell/apps, and GET /v3/deals/schema (see Search API and REST API docs). Requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection — calls to connectors.proxy("zendesk-sell", "/path"). Prefer using: connectors.proxy("zendesk-sell", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},zenefits:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Zenefits",visibility:"beta",vertical:["hris"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-zenefits.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access HR, employment, and organizational data via REST APIs.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Zenefits connector via the proxy pattern, e.g., connectors.proxy("zenefits", "/people") to fetch employee data. Common endpoints include: GET /people, GET /departments, GET /locations, GET /companies, and GET /employments. Requests are automatically authenticated and proxied through the SDK with OAuth2 token injection and refresh built-in. Prefer using connectors.proxy("zenefits", "/path") for seamless access. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},zoho:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Zoho",visibility:"beta",vertical:["accounting"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-zoho.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Interact with its services via authenticated REST API calls.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Zoho connector via the proxy pattern by calling connectors.proxy("zoho", "/path"). Common useful endpoints include GET /crm/v2/Leads, POST /crm/v2/Leads, GET /accounts/oauth/v2/token (to refresh tokens), GET /crm/v2/Contacts, and GET /crm/v2/Modules. All requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 token injection and refresh. Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},"zoho-desk":{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Zoho Desk",visibility:"beta",vertical:["ticketing"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-zoho-desk.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Access tickets, contacts, agents, organizations, and more.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Zoho Desk connector via the proxy pattern to access common endpoints such as GET /v1/tickets, GET /v1/contacts, GET /v1/agents, GET /v1/organizations, and POST /v1/accounts/{account_id}/associateProducts. Remember that requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic OAuth2 authentication injection — simply call connectors.proxy("zoho-desk", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""}}},zoom:{hasClient:!1,hasServer:!1,metadata:{displayName:"Zoom",visibility:"alpha",vertical:["streaming"],audience:["paid","enterprise"],logoUrl:"https://cdn.replit.com/openint/_assets/logo-zoom.svg",authType:"OAUTH2",description:"Connect to Zoom to manage users, meetings, recordings, and more.",blueprint:{agentInstructions:'Use the Zoom OAuth2 connector via the proxy pattern to interact with Zoom resources. Common useful endpoints include: GET /users (list users), GET /users/{userId}/meetings (list user’s meetings), POST /users/{userId}/meetings (create meeting), GET /meetings/{meetingId}/recordings (list recordings), DELETE /webhooks/{webhookId} (delete a webhook). Remember: requests are proxied through the SDK with automatic auth injection — use connectors.proxy("zoom", "/path"). Note: the proxy returns a raw response object, not parsed JSON — call .json() to parse the response body.',packages:{}},links:{webUrl:"",apiDocsUrl:""},integrationKeys:{nango:"zoom"}}}},ir=n7.enum(Object.keys(io)).openapi({ref:"core.connector.name"});Object.fromEntries(ir.options.map(e=>[e,e])),e.s(["APP_SCOPED_CONNECTORS",0,["stripe","shopify-store","whop"],"connectorNameToGql",0,function(e){return e.toUpperCase().replace(/-/g,"_")},"gqlEnumToConnectorName",0,e=>e.toLowerCase().replace(/_/g,"-"),"isValidConnectorName",0,function(e){return ir.safeParse(e).success}],142643)}]);

